0	antiochus and think st thou to regain
0	thy right by sitting still or thus retiring 
0	so did not machabeus he indeed
0	retired unto the desert but with arms 
0	and o er a mighty king so oft prevailed
0	that by strong hand his family obtained 
0	though priests the crown and david s throne usurped 
0	with modin and her suburbs once content 
0	if kingdom move thee not let move thee zeal
0	and duty zeal and duty are not slow 
0	but on occasion s forelock watchful wait 
0	they themselves rather are occasion best 
0	zeal of thy father s house duty to free
0	thy country from her heathen servitude 
0	so shalt thou best fulfil best verify 
0	the prophets old who sung thy endless reign 
0	the happier reign the sooner it begins 
0	rein then what canst thou better do the while 
0	to whom our saviour answer thus returned 
0	 all things are best fulfilled in their due time 
0	and time there is for all things truth hath said 
0	if of my reign prophetic writ hath told
0	that it shall never end so when begin
0	the father in his purpose hath decreed 
0	he in whose hand all times and seasons rowl 
0	what if he hath decreed that i shall first
0	be tried in humble state and things adverse 
0	by tribulations injuries insults 
0	contempts and scorns and snares and violence 
0	suffering abstaining quietly expecting
0	without distrust or doubt that he may know
0	what i can suffer how obey who best
0	can suffer best can do best reign who first
0	well hath obeyed just trial ere i merit
0	my exaltation without change or end 
0	but what concerns it thee when i begin
0	my everlasting kingdom why art thou
0	solicitous what moves thy inquisition 
0	know st thou not that my rising is thy fall 
0	and my promotion will be thy destruction 
0	to whom the tempter inly racked replied 
0	 let that come when it comes all hope is lost
0	of my reception into grace what worse 
0	for where no hope is left is left no fear 
0	if there be worse the expectation more
0	of worse torments me than the feeling can 
0	i would be at the worst worst is my port 
0	my harbour and my ultimate repose 
0	the end i would attain my final good 
0	my error was my error and my crime
0	my crime whatever for itself condemned 
0	and will alike be punished whether thou
0	reign or reign not though to that gentle brow
0	willingly i could fly and hope thy reign 
0	from that placid aspect and meek regard 
0	rather than aggravate my evil state 
0	would stand between me and thy father s ire
0	 whose ire i dread more than the fire of hell 
0	a shelter and a kind of shading cool
0	interposition as a summer s cloud 
0	if i then to the worst that can be haste 
0	why move thy feet so slow to what is best 
0	happiest both to thyself and all the world 
0	that thou who worthiest art shouldst be their king 
0	perhaps thou linger st in deep thoughts detained
0	of the enterprise so hazardous and high 
0	no wonder for though in thee be united
0	what of perfection can in man be found 
0	or human nature can receive consider
0	thy life hath yet been private most part spent
0	at home scarce viewed the galilean towns 
0	and once a year jerusalem few days 
0	short sojourn and what thence couldst thou observe 
0	the world thou hast not seen much less her glory 
0	empires and monarchs and their radiant courts 
0	best school of best experience quickest in sight
0	in all things that to greatest actions lead 
0	the wisest unexperienced will be ever
0	timorous and loth with novice modesty
0	 as he who seeking asses found a kingdom 
