0	and regal mysteries that thou may st know
0	how best their opposition to withstand 
0	with that such power was given him then he took
0	the son of god up to a mountain high 
0	it was a mountain at whose verdant feet
0	a spacious plain outstretched in circuit wide
0	lay pleasant from his side two rivers flowed 
0	the one winding the other straight and left between
0	fair champaign with less rivers interveined 
0	then meeting joined their tribute to the sea 
0	fertil of corn the glebe of oil and wine 
0	with herds the pasture thronged with flocks the hills 
0	huge cities and high towered that well might seem
0	the seats of mightiest monarchs and so large
0	the prospect was that here and there was room
0	for barren desert fountainless and dry 
0	to this high mountain top the tempter brought
0	our saviour and new train of words began 
0	 well have we speeded and o er hill and dale 
0	forest and field and flood temples and towers 
0	cut shorter many a league here thou behold st
