0	all this fair sight thy kingdom though foretold
0	by prophet or by angel unless thou
0	endeavour as thy father david did 
0	thou never shalt obtain prediction still
0	in all things and all men supposes means 
0	without means used what it predicts revokes 
0	but say thou wert possessed of david s throne
0	by free consent of all none opposite 
0	long to enjoy it quiet and secure
0	between two such enclosing enemies 
0	roman and parthian therefore one of these
0	thou must make sure thy own the parthian first 
0	by my advice as nearer and of late
0	found able by invasion to annoy
0	thy country and captive lead away her kings 
0	antigonus and old hyrcanus bound 
0	maugre the roman it shall be my task
0	to render thee the parthian at dispose 
0	choose which thou wilt by conquest or by league 
0	by him thou shalt regain without him not 
0	that which alone can truly reinstall thee
0	in david s royal seat his true successor 
0	deliverance of thy brethren those ten tribes
0	whose offspring in his territory yet serve
