0	the fellows of his crime the followers rather
0	 far other once beheld in bliss condemned
0	for ever now to have their lot in pain 
0	millions of spirits for his fault amerced
0	of heaven and from eternal splendours flung
0	for his revolt yet faithful how they stood 
0	their glory withered as when heaven s fire
0	hath scathed the forest oaks or mountain pines 
