0	tears such as angels weep burst forth at last
0	words interwove with sighs found out their way 
0	 o myriads of immortal spirits o powers
0	matchless but with th almighty and that strife
0	was not inglorious though th event was dire 
0	as this place testifies and this dire change 
0	hateful to utter but what power of mind 
0	forseeing or presaging from the depth
0	of knowledge past or present could have feared
0	how such united force of gods how such
0	as stood like these could ever know repulse 
0	for who can yet believe though after loss 
0	that all these puissant legions whose exile
0	hath emptied heaven shall fail to re ascend 
0	self raised and repossess their native seat 
0	for me be witness all the host of heaven 
0	if counsels different or danger shunned
0	by me have lost our hopes but he who reigns
0	monarch in heaven till then as one secure
0	sat on his throne upheld by old repute 
0	consent or custom and his regal state
0	put forth at full but still his strength concealed 
0	which tempted our attempt and wrought our fall 
0	henceforth his might we know and know our own 
0	so as not either to provoke or dread
0	new war provoked our better part remains
0	to work in close design by fraud or guile 
0	what force effected not that he no less
0	at length from us may find who overcomes
0	by force hath overcome but half his foe 
0	space may produce new worlds whereof so rife
