0	there stood a hill not far whose grisly top
0	belched fire and rolling smoke the rest entire
0	shone with a glossy scurf undoubted sign
0	that in his womb was hid metallic ore 
0	the work of sulphur thither winged with speed 
0	a numerous brigade hastened as when bands
0	forerun the royal camp to trench a field 
0	or cast a rampart mammon led them on 
0	mammon the least erected spirit that fell
0	from heaven for even in heaven his looks and thoughts
0	were always downward bent admiring more
