0	what in an age they with incessant toil
0	and hands innumerable scarce perform 
0	nigh on the plain in many cells prepared 
0	that underneath had veins of liquid fire
0	sluiced from the lake a second multitude
0	with wondrous art founded the massy ore 
0	severing each kind and scummed the bullion dross 
0	a third as soon had formed within the ground
0	a various mould and from the boiling cells
0	by strange conveyance filled each hollow nook 
