0	behold a wonder they but now who seemed
0	in bigness to surpass earth s giant sons 
0	now less than smallest dwarfs in narrow room
0	throng numberless like that pygmean race
0	beyond the indian mount or faery elves 
0	whose midnight revels by a forest side
0	or fountain some belated peasant sees 
0	or dreams he sees while overhead the moon
0	sits arbitress and nearer to the earth
0	wheels her pale course they on their mirth and dance
0	intent with jocund music charm his ear 
0	at once with joy and fear his heart rebounds 
0	thus incorporeal spirits to smallest forms
0	reduced their shapes immense and were at large 
0	though without number still amidst the hall
