0	incapable of stain would soon expel
0	her mischief and purge off the baser fire 
0	victorious thus repulsed our final hope
0	is flat despair we must exasperate
0	th almighty victor to spend all his rage 
0	and that must end us that must be our cure 
0	to be no more sad cure for who would lose 
0	though full of pain this intellectual being 
0	those thoughts that wander through eternity 
0	to perish rather swallowed up and lost
0	in the wide womb of uncreated night 
0	devoid of sense and motion and who knows 
0	let this be good whether our angry foe
0	can give it or will ever how he can
0	is doubtful that he never will is sure 
0	will he so wise let loose at once his ire 
0	belike through impotence or unaware 
0	to give his enemies their wish and end
0	them in his anger whom his anger saves
0	to punish endless wherefore cease we then 
0	say they who counsel war we are decreed 
0	reserved and destined to eternal woe 
0	whatever doing what can we suffer more 
0	what can we suffer worse is this then worst 
0	thus sitting thus consulting thus in arms 
0	what when we fled amain pursued and struck
0	with heaven s afflicting thunder and besought
0	the deep to shelter us this hell then seemed
0	a refuge from those wounds or when we lay
0	chained on the burning lake that sure was worse 
0	what if the breath that kindled those grim fires 
0	awaked should blow them into sevenfold rage 
