0	ages of hopeless end this would be worse 
0	war therefore open or concealed alike
0	my voice dissuades for what can force or guile
0	with him or who deceive his mind whose eye
0	views all things at one view he from heaven s height
0	all these our motions vain sees and derides 
0	not more almighty to resist our might
0	than wise to frustrate all our plots and wiles 
0	shall we then live thus vile the race of heaven
0	thus trampled thus expelled to suffer here
0	chains and these torments better these than worse 
0	by my advice since fate inevitable
0	subdues us and omnipotent decree 
0	the victor s will to suffer as to do 
0	our strength is equal nor the law unjust
0	that so ordains this was at first resolved 
0	if we were wise against so great a foe
0	contending and so doubtful what might fall 
0	i laugh when those who at the spear are bold
0	and venturous if that fail them shrink and fear
0	what yet they know must follow to endure
0	exile or igominy or bonds or pain 
0	the sentence of their conqueror this is now
0	our doom which if we can sustain and bear 
0	our supreme foe in time may much remit
0	his anger and perhaps thus far removed 
0	not mind us not offending satisfied
0	with what is punished whence these raging fires
0	will slacken if his breath stir not their flames 
