0	a growing empire doubtless while we dream 
0	and know not that the king of heaven hath doomed
0	this place our dungeon not our safe retreat
0	beyond his potent arm to live exempt
0	from heaven s high jurisdiction in new league
0	banded against his throne but to remain
0	in strictest bondage though thus far removed 
0	under th inevitable curb reserved
0	his captive multitude for he to be sure 
0	in height or depth still first and last will reign
0	sole king and of his kingdom lose no part
0	by our revolt but over hell extend
0	his empire and with iron sceptre rule
0	us here as with his golden those in heaven 
0	what sit we then projecting peace and war 
0	war hath determined us and foiled with loss
0	irreparable terms of peace yet none
0	vouchsafed or sought for what peace will be given
0	to us enslaved but custody severe 
0	and stripes and arbitrary punishment
0	inflicted and what peace can we return 
0	but to our power hostility and hate 
0	untamed reluctance and revenge though slow 
0	yet ever plotting how the conqueror least
0	may reap his conquest and may least rejoice
0	in doing what we most in suffering feel 
0	nor will occasion want nor shall we need
0	with dangerous expedition to invade
0	heaven whose high walls fear no assault or siege 
0	or ambush from the deep what if we find
0	some easier enterprise there is a place
0	 if ancient and prophetic fame in heaven
0	err not another world the happy seat
0	of some new race called man about this time
0	to be created like to us though less
0	in power and excellence but favoured more
0	of him who rules above so was his will
0	pronounced among the gods and by an oath
0	that shook heaven s whole circumference confirmed 
0	thither let us bend all our thoughts to learn
0	what creatures there inhabit of what mould
0	or substance how endued and what their power
0	and where their weakness how attempted best 
0	by force of subtlety though heaven be shut 
0	and heaven s high arbitrator sit secure
0	in his own strength this place may lie exposed 
0	the utmost border of his kingdom left
0	to their defence who hold it here perhaps 
0	some advantageous act may be achieved
0	by sudden onset either with hell fire
0	to waste his whole creation or possess
0	all as our own and drive as we were driven 
0	the puny habitants or if not drive 
0	seduce them to our party that their god
0	may prove their foe and with repenting hand
0	abolish his own works this would surpass
0	common revenge and interrupt his joy
0	in our confusion and our joy upraise
0	in his disturbance when his darling sons 
0	hurled headlong to partake with us shall curse
0	their frail original and faded bliss 
0	faded so soon advise if this be worth
0	attempting or to sit in darkness here
0	hatching vain empires thus beelzebub
0	pleaded his devilish counsel first devised
0	by satan and in part proposed for whence 
0	but from the author of all ill could spring
0	so deep a malice to confound the race
0	of mankind in one root and earth with hell
0	to mingle and involve done all to spite
0	the great creator but their spite still serves
0	his glory to augment the bold design
0	pleased highly those infernal states and joy
0	sparkled in all their eyes with full assent
0	they vote whereat his speech he thus renews 
0	 well have ye judged well ended long debate 
0	synod of gods and like to what ye are 
0	great things resolved which from the lowest deep
0	will once more lift us up in spite of fate 
0	nearer our ancient seat perhaps in view
0	of those bright confines whence with neighbouring arms 
0	and opportune excursion we may chance
0	re enter heaven or else in some mild zone
0	dwell not unvisited of heaven s fair light 
0	secure and at the brightening orient beam
0	purge off this gloom the soft delicious air 
0	to heal the scar of these corrosive fires 
0	shall breathe her balm but first whom shall we send
0	in search of this new world whom shall we find
0	sufficient who shall tempt with wandering feet
0	the dark unbottomed infinite abyss 
0	and through the palpable obscure find out
0	his uncouth way or spread his airy flight 
0	upborne with indefatigable wings
0	over the vast abrupt ere he arrive
0	the happy isle what strength what art can then
0	suffice or what evasion bear him safe 
0	through the strict senteries and stations thick
0	of angels watching round here he had need
0	all circumspection and we now no less
0	choice in our suffrage for on whom we send
0	the weight of all and our last hope relies 
0	this said he sat and expectation held
0	his look suspense awaiting who appeared
0	to second or oppose or undertake
0	the perilous attempt but all sat mute 
0	pondering the danger with deep thoughts and each
0	in other s countenance read his own dismay 
0	astonished none among the choice and prime
0	of those heaven warring champions could be found
0	so hardy as to proffer or accept 
0	alone the dreadful voyage till at last 
0	satan whom now transcendent glory raised
0	above his fellows with monarchal pride
0	conscious of highest worth unmoved thus spake 
0	with reason hath deep silence and demur
0	seized us though undismayed long is the way
0	and hard that out of hell leads up to light 
0	our prison strong this huge convex of fire 
0	outrageous to devour immures us round
0	ninefold and gates of burning adamant 
0	barred over us prohibit all egress 
0	these passed if any pass the void profound
0	of unessential night receives him next 
0	wide gaping and with utter loss of being
0	threatens him plunged in that abortive gulf 
0	if thence he scape into whatever world 
0	or unknown region what remains him less
0	than unknown dangers and as hard escape 
0	but i should ill become this throne o peers 
0	and this imperial sovereignty adorned
0	with splendour armed with power if aught proposed
0	and judged of public moment in the shape
0	of difficulty or danger could deter
0	me from attempting wherefore do i assume
0	these royalties and not refuse to reign 
0	refusing to accept as great a share
0	of hazard as of honour due alike
0	to him who reigns and so much to him due
0	of hazard more as he above the rest
0	high honoured sits go therefore mighty powers 
0	terror of heaven though fallen intend at home 
0	while here shall be our home what best may ease
0	the present misery and render hell
0	more tolerable if there be cure or charm
0	to respite or deceive or slack the pain
0	of this ill mansion intermit no watch
0	against a wakeful foe while i abroad
0	through all the coasts of dark destruction seek
0	deliverance for us all this enterprise
0	none shall partake with me thus saying rose
0	the monarch and prevented all reply 
0	prudent lest from his resolution raised 
0	others among the chief might offer now 
0	certain to be refused what erst they feared 
0	and so refused might in opinion stand
0	his rivals winning cheap the high repute
0	which he through hazard huge must earn but they
0	dreaded not more th adventure than his voice
0	forbidding and at once with him they rose 
0	their rising all at once was as the sound
0	of thunder heard remote towards him they bend
0	with awful reverence prone and as a god
0	extol him equal to the highest in heaven 
0	nor failed they to express how much they praised
0	that for the general safety he despised
0	his own for neither do the spirits damned
0	lose all their virtue lest bad men should boast
0	their specious deeds on earth which glory excites 
0	or close ambition varnished o er with zeal 
0	thus they their doubtful consultations dark
0	ended rejoicing in their matchless chief 
0	as when from mountain tops the dusky clouds
0	ascending while the north wind sleeps o erspread
0	heaven s cheerful face the louring element
0	scowls o er the darkened landscape snow or shower 
0	if chance the radiant sun with farewell sweet 
0	extend his evening beam the fields revive 
0	the birds their notes renew and bleating herds
0	attest their joy that hill and valley rings 
0	o shame to men devil with devil damned
0	firm concord holds men only disagree
0	of creatures rational though under hope
0	of heavenly grace and god proclaiming peace 
0	yet live in hatred enmity and strife
0	among themselves and levy cruel wars
0	wasting the earth each other to destroy 
0	as if which might induce us to accord 
0	man had not hellish foes enow besides 
0	that day and night for his destruction wait 
0	the stygian council thus dissolved and forth
0	in order came the grand infernal peers 
0	midst came their mighty paramount and seemed
0	alone th antagonist of heaven nor less
