0	by doom of battle and complain that fate
0	free virtue should enthrall to force or chance 
0	their song was partial but the harmony
0	 what could it less when spirits immortal sing 
0	suspended hell and took with ravishment
0	the thronging audience in discourse more sweet
0	 for eloquence the soul song charms the sense 
0	others apart sat on a hill retired 
0	in thoughts more elevate and reasoned high
0	fixed fate free will foreknowledge absolute 
0	and found no end in wandering mazes lost 
0	of good and evil much they argued then 
0	of happiness and final misery 
0	passion and apathy and glory and shame 
0	vain wisdom all and false philosophy 
0	yet with a pleasing sorcery could charm
