0	whose waves of torrent fire inflame with rage 
0	far off from these a slow and silent stream 
0	lethe the river of oblivion rolls
0	her watery labyrinth whereof who drinks
0	forthwith his former state and being forgets 
0	forgets both joy and grief pleasure and pain 
0	beyond this flood a frozen continent
0	lies dark and wild beat with perpetual storms
0	of whirlwind and dire hail which on firm land
0	thaws not but gathers heap and ruin seems
