0	at thy right hand voluptuous as beseems
0	thy daughter and thy darling without end 
0	thus saying from her side the fatal key 
0	sad instrument of all our woe she took 
0	and towards the gate rolling her bestial train 
0	forthwith the huge portcullis high up drew 
0	which but herself not all the stygian powers
0	could once have moved then in the key hole turns
0	th intricate wards and every bolt and bar
0	of massy iron or solid rock with ease
0	unfastens on a sudden open fly 
0	with impetuous recoil and jarring sound 
0	th infernal doors and on their hinges grate
0	harsh thunder that the lowest bottom shook
0	of erebus she opened but to shut
0	excelled her power the gates wide open stood 
0	that with extended wings a bannered host 
0	under spread ensigns marching might pass through
0	with horse and chariots ranked in loose array 
0	so wide they stood and like a furnace mouth
0	cast forth redounding smoke and ruddy flame 
0	before their eyes in sudden view appear
0	the secrets of the hoary deep a dark
0	illimitable ocean without bound 
0	without dimension where length breadth and height 
0	and time and place are lost where eldest night
0	and chaos ancestors of nature hold
0	eternal anarchy amidst the noise
0	of endless wars and by confusion stand 
0	for hot cold moist and dry four champions fierce 
0	strive here for mastery and to battle bring
0	their embryon atoms they around the flag
0	of each his faction in their several clans 
0	light armed or heavy sharp smooth swift or slow 
0	swarm populous unnumbered as the sands
0	of barca or cyrene s torrid soil 
0	levied to side with warring winds and poise
0	their lighter wings to whom these most adhere
0	he rules a moment chaos umpire sits 
0	and by decision more embroils the fray
0	by which he reigns next him high arbiter 
0	chance governs all into this wild abyss 
0	the womb of nature and perhaps her grave 
0	of neither sea nor shore nor air nor fire 
0	but all these in their pregnant causes mixed
0	confusedly and which thus must ever fight 
0	unless th almighty maker them ordain
0	his dark materials to create more worlds 
0	into this wild abyss the wary fiend
0	stood on the brink of hell and looked a while 
0	pondering his voyage for no narrow frith
0	he had to cross nor was his ear less pealed
0	with noises loud and ruinous to compare
0	great things with small than when bellona storms
0	with all her battering engines bent to rase
0	some capital city or less than if this frame
0	of heaven were falling and these elements
0	in mutiny had from her axle torn
0	the steadfast earth at last his sail broad vans
0	he spread for flight and in the surging smoke
0	uplifted spurns the ground thence many a league 
0	as in a cloudy chair ascending rides
0	audacious but that seat soon failing meets
0	a vast vacuity all unawares 
0	fluttering his pennons vain plumb down he drops
0	ten thousand fathom deep and to this hour
0	down had been falling had not by ill chance 
0	the strong rebuff of some tumultuous cloud 
0	instinct with fire and nitre hurried him
0	as many miles aloft that fury stayed 
0	quenched in a boggy syrtis neither sea 
0	nor good dry land nigh foundered on he fares 
0	treading the crude consistence half on foot 
0	half flying behoves him now both oar and sail 
0	as when a gryphon through the wilderness
0	with winged course o er hill or moory dale 
0	pursues the arimaspian who by stealth
0	had from his wakeful custody purloined
0	the guarded gold so eagerly the fiend
0	o er bog or steep through strait rough dense or rare 
0	with head hands wings or feet pursues his way 
0	and swims or sinks or wades or creeps or flies 
0	at length a universal hubbub wild
0	of stunning sounds and voices all confused 
