0	over the promised land to god so dear 
0	by which to visit oft those happy tribes 
0	on high behests his angels to and fro
0	passed frequent and his eye with choice regard
0	from paneas the fount of jordan s flood 
0	to beersaba where the holy land
0	so wide the opening seemed where bounds were set
0	to darkness such as bound the ocean wave 
0	satan from hence now on the lower stair 
0	that scaled by steps of gold to heaven gate 
0	looks down with wonder at the sudden view
0	of all this world at once as when a scout 
0	through dark and desert ways with peril gone
0	all night at last by break of cheerful dawn
0	obtains the brow of some high climbing hill 
0	which to his eye discovers unaware
0	the goodly prospect of some foreign land
0	first seen or some renowned metropolis
0	with glistering spires and pinnacles adorned 
0	which now the rising sun gilds with his beams 
0	such wonder seised though after heaven seen 
0	the spirit malign but much more envy seised 
0	at sight of all this world beheld so fair 
0	round he surveys and well might where he stood
0	so high above the circling canopy
0	of night s extended shade from eastern point
0	of libra to the fleecy star that bears
0	andromeda far off atlantick seas
0	beyond the horizon then from pole to pole
0	he views in breadth and without longer pause
0	down right into the world s first region throws
0	his flight precipitant and winds with ease
0	through the pure marble air his oblique way
0	amongst innumerable stars that shone
0	stars distant but nigh hand seemed other worlds 
0	or other worlds they seemed or happy isles 
0	like those hesperian gardens famed of old 
0	fortunate fields and groves and flowery vales 
0	thrice happy isles but who dwelt happy there
0	he staid not to inquire above them all
0	the golden sun in splendour likest heaven 
0	allured his eye thither his course he bends
0	through the calm firmament but up or down 
0	by center or eccentrick hard to tell 
0	or longitude where the great luminary
0	aloof the vulgar constellations thick 
0	that from his lordly eye keep distance due 
0	dispenses light from far they as they move
0	their starry dance in numbers that compute
0	days months and years towards his all cheering lamp
0	turn swift their various motions or are turned
0	by his magnetick beam that gently warms
0	the universe and to each inward part
0	with gentle penetration though unseen 
0	shoots invisible virtue even to the deep 
0	so wonderously was set his station bright 
0	there lands the fiend a spot like which perhaps
0	astronomer in the sun s lucent orb
0	through his glazed optick tube yet never saw 
0	the place he found beyond expression bright 
0	compared with aught on earth metal or stone 
0	not all parts like but all alike informed
0	with radiant light as glowing iron with fire 
0	if metal part seemed gold part silver clear 
0	if stone carbuncle most or chrysolite 
0	ruby or topaz to the twelve that shone
0	in aaron s breast plate and a stone besides
0	imagined rather oft than elsewhere seen 
0	that stone or like to that which here below
0	philosophers in vain so long have sought 
0	in vain though by their powerful art they bind
0	volatile hermes and call up unbound
0	in various shapes old proteus from the sea 
0	drained through a limbeck to his native form 
0	what wonder then if fields and regions here
0	breathe forth elixir pure and rivers run
0	potable gold when with one virtuous touch
0	the arch chemick sun so far from us remote 
0	produces with terrestrial humour mixed 
0	here in the dark so many precious things
0	of colour glorious and effect so rare 
0	here matter new to gaze the devil met
0	undazzled far and wide his eye commands 
0	for sight no obstacle found here nor shade 
0	but all sun shine as when his beams at noon
0	culminate from the equator as they now
0	shot upward still direct whence no way round
0	shadow from body opaque can fall and the air 
0	no where so clear sharpened his visual ray
0	to objects distant far whereby he soon
0	saw within ken a glorious angel stand 
0	the same whom john saw also in the sun 
0	his back was turned but not his brightness hid 
0	of beaming sunny rays a golden tiar
0	circled his head nor less his locks behind
0	illustrious on his shoulders fledge with wings
0	lay waving round on some great charge employed
0	he seemed or fixed in cogitation deep 
0	glad was the spirit impure as now in hope
0	to find who might direct his wandering flight
0	to paradise the happy seat of man 
0	his journey s end and our beginning woe 
0	but first he casts to change his proper shape 
0	which else might work him danger or delay 
0	and now a stripling cherub he appears 
0	not of the prime yet such as in his face
0	youth smiled celestial and to every limb
0	suitable grace diffused so well he feigned 
0	under a coronet his flowing hair
0	in curls on either cheek played wings he wore
0	of many a coloured plume sprinkled with gold 
0	his habit fit for speed succinct and held
0	before his decent steps a silver wand 
0	he drew not nigh unheard the angel bright 
0	ere he drew nigh his radiant visage turned 
0	admonished by his ear and straight was known
0	the arch angel uriel one of the seven
0	who in god s presence nearest to his throne 
0	stand ready at command and are his eyes
0	that run through all the heavens or down to the earth
0	bear his swift errands over moist and dry 
0	o er sea and land him satan thus accosts 
0	uriel for thou of those seven spirits that stand
0	in sight of god s high throne gloriously bright 
0	the first art wont his great authentick will
0	interpreter through highest heaven to bring 
0	where all his sons thy embassy attend 
0	and here art likeliest by supreme decree
0	like honour to obtain and as his eye
0	to visit oft this new creation round 
0	unspeakable desire to see and know
0	all these his wonderous works but chiefly man 
0	his chief delight and favour him for whom
0	all these his works so wonderous he ordained 
0	hath brought me from the quires of cherubim
0	alone thus wandering brightest seraph tell
0	in which of all these shining orbs hath man
0	his fixed seat or fixed seat hath none 
0	but all these shining orbs his choice to dwell 
0	that i may find him and with secret gaze
0	or open admiration him behold 
0	on whom the great creator hath bestowed
0	worlds and on whom hath all these graces poured 
0	that both in him and all things as is meet 
0	the universal maker we may praise 
0	who justly hath driven out his rebel foes
0	to deepest hell and to repair that loss 
0	created this new happy race of men
0	to serve him better wise are all his ways 
0	so spake the false dissembler unperceived 
0	for neither man nor angel can discern
0	hypocrisy the only evil that walks
0	invisible except to god alone 
0	by his permissive will through heaven and earth 
0	and oft though wisdom wake suspicion sleeps
0	at wisdom s gate and to simplicity
0	resigns her charge while goodness thinks no ill
0	where no ill seems which now for once beguiled
0	uriel though regent of the sun and held
0	the sharpest sighted spirit of all in heaven 
0	who to the fraudulent impostor foul 
0	in his uprightness answer thus returned 
0	fair angel thy desire which tends to know
0	the works of god thereby to glorify
0	the great work master leads to no excess
0	that reaches blame but rather merits praise
0	the more it seems excess that led thee hither
0	from thy empyreal mansion thus alone 
0	to witness with thine eyes what some perhaps 
0	contented with report hear only in heaven 
0	for wonderful indeed are all his works 
0	pleasant to know and worthiest to be all
0	had in remembrance always with delight 
0	but what created mind can comprehend
0	their number or the wisdom infinite
0	that brought them forth but hid their causes deep 
0	i saw when at his word the formless mass 
0	this world s material mould came to a heap 
0	confusion heard his voice and wild uproar
0	stood ruled stood vast infinitude confined 
0	till at his second bidding darkness fled 
0	light shone and order from disorder sprung 
0	swift to their several quarters hasted then
0	the cumbrous elements earth flood air fire 
0	and this ethereal quintessence of heaven
0	flew upward spirited with various forms 
0	that rolled orbicular and turned to stars
0	numberless as thou seest and how they move 
0	each had his place appointed each his course 
0	the rest in circuit walls this universe 
0	look downward on that globe whose hither side
0	with light from hence though but reflected shines 
0	that place is earth the seat of man that light
0	his day which else as the other hemisphere 
0	night would invade but there the neighbouring moon
0	 so call that opposite fair star her aid
0	timely interposes and her monthly round
0	still ending still renewing through mid heaven 
0	with borrowed light her countenance triform
0	hence fills and empties to enlighten the earth 
0	and in her pale dominion checks the night 
0	that spot to which i point is paradise 
0	adam s abode those lofty shades his bower 
0	thy way thou canst not miss me mine requires 
0	thus said he turned and satan bowing low 
0	as to superiour spirits is wont in heaven 
0	where honour due and reverence none neglects 
0	took leave and toward the coast of earth beneath 
0	down from the ecliptick sped with hoped success 
0	throws his steep flight in many an aery wheel 
0	nor staid till on niphates top he lights 
0	o for that warning voice which he who saw
0	the apocalypse heard cry in heaven aloud 
0	then when the dragon put to second rout 
0	came furious down to be revenged on men 
0	woe to the inhabitants on earth that now 
0	while time was our first parents had been warned
0	the coming of their secret foe and scaped 
0	haply so scaped his mortal snare for now
0	satan now first inflamed with rage came down 
0	the tempter ere the accuser of mankind 
0	to wreak on innocent frail man his loss
0	of that first battle and his flight to hell 
0	yet not rejoicing in his speed though bold
0	far off and fearless nor with cause to boast 
0	begins his dire attempt which nigh the birth
0	now rolling boils in his tumultuous breast 
0	and like a devilish engine back recoils
0	upon himself horrour and doubt distract
0	his troubled thoughts and from the bottom stir
0	the hell within him for within him hell
0	he brings and round about him nor from hell
0	one step no more than from himself can fly
0	by change of place now conscience wakes despair 
0	that slumbered wakes the bitter memory
0	of what he was what is and what must be
0	worse of worse deeds worse sufferings must ensue 
0	sometimes towards eden which now in his view
0	lay pleasant his grieved look he fixes sad 
0	sometimes towards heaven and the full blazing sun 
0	which now sat high in his meridian tower 
0	then much revolving thus in sighs began 
0	o thou that with surpassing glory crowned 
0	lookest from thy sole dominion like the god
0	of this new world at whose sight all the stars
0	hide their diminished heads to thee i call 
0	but with no friendly voice and add thy name 
0	of sun to tell thee how i hate thy beams 
0	that bring to my remembrance from what state
0	i fell how glorious once above thy sphere 
0	till pride and worse ambition threw me down
0	warring in heaven against heaven s matchless king 
0	ah wherefore he deserved no such return
0	from me whom he created what i was
0	in that bright eminence and with his good
0	upbraided none nor was his service hard 
0	what could be less than to afford him praise 
0	the easiest recompence and pay him thanks 
0	how due yet all his good proved ill in me 
0	and wrought but malice lifted up so high
0	i sdeined subjection and thought one step higher
0	would set me highest and in a moment quit
0	the debt immense of endless gratitude 
0	so burdensome still paying still to owe 
0	forgetful what from him i still received 
0	and understood not that a grateful mind
0	by owing owes not but still pays at once
0	indebted and discharged what burden then
0	o had his powerful destiny ordained
0	me some inferiour angel i had stood
0	then happy no unbounded hope had raised
0	ambition yet why not some other power
0	as great might have aspired and me though mean 
0	drawn to his part but other powers as great
0	fell not but stand unshaken from within
0	or from without to all temptations armed 
0	hadst thou the same free will and power to stand 
0	thou hadst whom hast thou then or what to accuse 
0	but heaven s free love dealt equally to all 
0	be then his love accursed since love or hate 
0	to me alike it deals eternal woe 
0	nay cursed be thou since against his thy will
0	chose freely what it now so justly rues 
0	me miserable which way shall i fly
0	infinite wrath and infinite despair 
0	which way i fly is hell myself am hell 
0	and in the lowest deep a lower deep
0	still threatening to devour me opens wide 
0	to which the hell i suffer seems a heaven 
0	o then at last relent is there no place
0	left for repentance none for pardon left 
0	none left but by submission and that word
0	disdain forbids me and my dread of shame
0	among the spirits beneath whom i seduced
0	with other promises and other vaunts
0	than to submit boasting i could subdue
0	the omnipotent ay me they little know
0	how dearly i abide that boast so vain 
0	under what torments inwardly i groan 
0	while they adore me on the throne of hell 
0	with diadem and scepter high advanced 
0	the lower still i fall only supreme
0	in misery such joy ambition finds 
0	but say i could repent and could obtain 
0	by act of grace my former state how soon
0	would highth recall high thoughts how soon unsay
0	what feigned submission swore ease would recant
0	vows made in pain as violent and void 
0	for never can true reconcilement grow 
0	where wounds of deadly hate have pierced so deep 
0	which would but lead me to a worse relapse
0	and heavier fall so should i purchase dear
0	short intermission bought with double smart 
0	this knows my punisher therefore as far
0	from granting he as i from begging peace 
0	all hope excluded thus behold instead
0	of us out cast exil d his new delight 
0	mankind created and for him this world 
0	so farewell hope and with hope farewell fear 
0	farewell remorse all good to me is lost 
0	evil be thou my good by thee at least
0	divided empire with heaven s king i hold 
0	by thee and more than half perhaps will reign 
0	as man ere long and this new world shall know 
0	thus while he spake each passion dimmed his face
0	thrice changed with pale ire envy and despair 
0	which marred his borrowed visage and betrayed
0	him counterfeit if any eye beheld 
0	for heavenly minds from such distempers foul
0	are ever clear whereof he soon aware 
0	each perturbation smoothed with outward calm 
0	artificer of fraud and was the first
0	that practised falsehood under saintly show 
0	deep malice to conceal couched with revenge 
0	yet not enough had practised to deceive
0	uriel once warned whose eye pursued him down
0	the way he went and on the assyrian mount
0	saw him disfigured more than could befall
0	spirit of happy sort his gestures fierce
0	he marked and mad demeanour then alone 
0	as he supposed all unobserved unseen 
0	so on he fares and to the border comes
0	of eden where delicious paradise 
0	now nearer crowns with her enclosure green 
0	as with a rural mound the champaign head
0	of a steep wilderness whose hairy sides
0	with thicket overgrown grotesque and wild 
0	access denied and overhead upgrew
0	insuperable height of loftiest shade 
0	cedar and pine and fir and branching palm 
0	a sylvan scene and as the ranks ascend 
0	shade above shade a woody theatre
0	of stateliest view yet higher than their tops
0	the verdurous wall of paradise upsprung 
0	which to our general sire gave prospect large
0	into his nether empire neighbouring round 
0	and higher than that wall a circling row
0	of goodliest trees loaden with fairest fruit 
0	blossoms and fruits at once of golden hue 
0	appeared with gay enamelled colours mixed 
0	on which the sun more glad impressed his beams
0	than in fair evening cloud or humid bow 
0	when god hath showered the earth so lovely seemed
0	that landskip and of pure now purer air
0	meets his approach and to the heart inspires
0	vernal delight and joy able to drive
0	all sadness but despair now gentle gales 
0	fanning their odoriferous wings dispense
0	native perfumes and whisper whence they stole
0	those balmy spoils as when to them who fail
0	beyond the cape of hope and now are past
0	mozambick off at sea north east winds blow
0	sabean odours from the spicy shore
0	of araby the blest with such delay
0	well pleased they slack their course and many a league
0	cheered with the grateful smell old ocean smiles 
0	so entertained those odorous sweets the fiend 
0	who came their bane though with them better pleased
0	than asmodeus with the fishy fume
0	that drove him though enamoured from the spouse
0	of tobit s son and with a vengeance sent
0	now to the ascent of that steep savage hill
0	satan had journeyed on pensive and slow 
0	but further way found none so thick entwined 
0	as one continued brake the undergrowth
0	of shrubs and tangling bushes had perplexed
0	all path of man or beast that passed that way 
0	one gate there only was and that looked east
0	on the other side which when the arch felon saw 
0	due entrance he disdained and in contempt 
0	at one flight bound high over leaped all bound
0	of hill or highest wall and sheer within
0	lights on his feet as when a prowling wolf 
0	whom hunger drives to seek new haunt for prey 
0	watching where shepherds pen their flocks at eve
0	in hurdled cotes amid the field secure 
0	leaps o er the fence with ease into the fold 
0	or as a thief bent to unhoard the cash
0	of some rich burgher whose substantial doors 
0	cross barred and bolted fast fear no assault 
0	in at the window climbs or o er the tiles 
0	so clomb this first grand thief into god s fold 
0	so since into his church lewd hirelings climb 
0	thence up he flew and on the tree of life 
0	the middle tree and highest there that grew 
0	sat like a cormorant yet not true life
0	thereby regained but sat devising death
0	to them who lived nor on the virtue thought
0	of that life giving plant but only used
0	for prospect what well used had been the pledge
0	of immortality so little knows
0	any but god alone to value right
0	the good before him but perverts best things
0	to worst abuse or to their meanest use 
0	beneath him with new wonder now he views 
0	to all delight of human sense exposed 
0	in narrow room nature s whole wealth yea more 
0	a heaven on earth for blissful paradise
0	of god the garden was by him in the east
0	of eden planted eden stretched her line
0	from auran eastward to the royal towers
0	of great seleucia built by grecian kings 
0	or where the sons of eden long before
0	dwelt in telassar in this pleasant soil
0	his far more pleasant garden god ordained 
0	out of the fertile ground he caused to grow
0	all trees of noblest kind for sight smell taste 
0	and all amid them stood the tree of life 
0	high eminent blooming ambrosial fruit
0	of vegetable gold and next to life 
0	our death the tree of knowledge grew fast by 
0	knowledge of good bought dear by knowing ill 
0	southward through eden went a river large 
0	nor changed his course but through the shaggy hill
0	passed underneath ingulfed for god had thrown
0	that mountain as his garden mould high raised
0	upon the rapid current which through veins
0	of porous earth with kindly thirst up drawn 
0	rose a fresh fountain and with many a rill
0	watered the garden thence united fell
0	down the steep glade and met the nether flood 
0	which from his darksome passage now appears 
0	and now divided into four main streams 
0	runs diverse wandering many a famous realm
0	and country whereof here needs no account 
0	but rather to tell how if art could tell 
0	how from that sapphire fount the crisped brooks 
0	rolling on orient pearl and sands of gold 
0	with mazy errour under pendant shades
0	ran nectar visiting each plant and fed
0	flowers worthy of paradise which not nice art
0	in beds and curious knots but nature boon
0	poured forth profuse on hill and dale and plain 
0	both where the morning sun first warmly smote
0	the open field and where the unpierced shade
0	imbrowned the noontide bowers thus was this place
0	a happy rural seat of various view 
0	groves whose rich trees wept odorous gums and balm 
0	others whose fruit burnished with golden rind 
0	hung amiable hesperian fables true 
0	if true here only and of delicious taste 
0	betwixt them lawns or level downs and flocks
0	grazing the tender herb were interposed 
0	or palmy hillock or the flowery lap
0	of some irriguous valley spread her store 
0	flowers of all hue and without thorn the rose 
0	another side umbrageous grots and caves
0	of cool recess o er which the mantling vine
0	lays forth her purple grape and gently creeps
0	luxuriant mean while murmuring waters fall
0	down the slope hills dispersed or in a lake 
0	that to the fringed bank with myrtle crowned
0	her crystal mirrour holds unite their streams 
0	the birds their quire apply airs vernal airs 
0	breathing the smell of field and grove attune
0	the trembling leaves while universal pan 
0	knit with the graces and the hours in dance 
0	led on the eternal spring not that fair field
0	of enna where proserpine gathering flowers 
0	herself a fairer flower by gloomy dis
0	was gathered which cost ceres all that pain
0	to seek her through the world nor that sweet grove
0	of daphne by orontes and the inspired
0	castalian spring might with this paradise
0	of eden strive nor that nyseian isle
0	girt with the river triton where old cham 
0	whom gentiles ammon call and libyan jove 
0	hid amalthea and her florid son
0	young bacchus from his stepdame rhea s eye 
0	nor where abassin kings their issue guard 
0	mount amara though this by some supposed
0	true paradise under the ethiop line
0	by nilus head enclosed with shining rock 
0	a whole day s journey high but wide remote
0	from this assyrian garden where the fiend
0	saw undelighted all delight all kind
0	of living creatures new to sight and strange
0	two of far nobler shape erect and tall 
0	godlike erect with native honour clad
0	in naked majesty seemed lords of all 
0	and worthy seemed for in their looks divine
0	the image of their glorious maker shone 
0	truth wisdom sanctitude severe and pure 
0	 severe but in true filial freedom placed 
0	whence true authority in men though both
0	not equal as their sex not equal seemed 
0	for contemplation he and valour formed 
0	for softness she and sweet attractive grace 
0	he for god only she for god in him 
0	his fair large front and eye sublime declared
0	absolute rule and hyacinthine locks
0	round from his parted forelock manly hung
0	clustering but not beneath his shoulders broad 
0	she as a veil down to the slender waist
0	her unadorned golden tresses wore
0	dishevelled but in wanton ringlets waved
0	as the vine curls her tendrils which implied
0	subjection but required with gentle sway 
0	and by her yielded by him best received 
0	yielded with coy submission modest pride 
0	and sweet reluctant amorous delay 
0	nor those mysterious parts were then concealed 
0	then was not guilty shame dishonest shame
0	of nature s works honour dishonourable 
0	sin bred how have ye troubled all mankind
0	with shows instead mere shows of seeming pure 
0	and banished from man s life his happiest life 
0	simplicity and spotless innocence 
0	so passed they naked on nor shunned the sight
0	of god or angel for they thought no ill 
0	so hand in hand they passed the loveliest pair 
0	that ever since in love s embraces met 
0	adam the goodliest man of men since born
0	his sons the fairest of her daughters eve 
0	under a tuft of shade that on a green
0	stood whispering soft by a fresh fountain side
0	they sat them down and after no more toil
0	of their sweet gardening labour than sufficed
0	to recommend cool zephyr and made ease
0	more easy wholesome thirst and appetite
0	more grateful to their supper fruits they fell 
0	nectarine fruits which the compliant boughs
0	yielded them side long as they sat recline
0	on the soft downy bank damasked with flowers 
0	the savoury pulp they chew and in the rind 
0	still as they thirsted scoop the brimming stream 
0	nor gentle purpose nor endearing smiles
0	wanted nor youthful dalliance as beseems
0	fair couple linked in happy nuptial league 
0	alone as they about them frisking played
0	all beasts of the earth since wild and of all chase
0	in wood or wilderness forest or den 
0	sporting the lion ramped and in his paw
0	dandled the kid bears tigers ounces pards 
0	gambolled before them the unwieldy elephant 
0	to make them mirth used all his might and wreathed
0	his lithe proboscis close the serpent sly 
0	insinuating wove with gordian twine
0	his braided train and of his fatal guile
0	gave proof unheeded others on the grass
0	couched and now filled with pasture gazing sat 
0	or bedward ruminating for the sun 
0	declined was hasting now with prone career
0	to the ocean isles and in the ascending scale
0	of heaven the stars that usher evening rose 
0	when satan still in gaze as first he stood 
0	scarce thus at length failed speech recovered sad 
0	o hell what do mine eyes with grief behold 
0	into our room of bliss thus high advanced
0	creatures of other mould earth born perhaps 
0	not spirits yet to heavenly spirits bright
0	little inferiour whom my thoughts pursue
0	with wonder and could love so lively shines
0	in them divine resemblance and such grace
0	the hand that formed them on their shape hath poured 
0	ah gentle pair ye little think how nigh
0	your change approaches when all these delights
0	will vanish and deliver ye to woe 
0	more woe the more your taste is now of joy 
0	happy but for so happy ill secured
0	long to continue and this high seat your heaven
0	ill fenced for heaven to keep out such a foe
0	as now is entered yet no purposed foe
0	to you whom i could pity thus forlorn 
0	though i unpitied league with you i seek 
0	and mutual amity so strait so close 
0	that i with you must dwell or you with me
0	henceforth my dwelling haply may not please 
0	like this fair paradise your sense yet such
0	accept your maker s work he gave it me 
0	which i as freely give hell shall unfold 
0	to entertain you two her widest gates 
0	and send forth all her kings there will be room 
0	not like these narrow limits to receive
0	your numerous offspring if no better place 
0	thank him who puts me loth to this revenge
0	on you who wrong me not for him who wronged 
0	and should i at your harmless innocence
0	melt as i do yet publick reason just 
0	honour and empire with revenge enlarged 
0	by conquering this new world compels me now
0	to do what else though damned i should abhor 
0	so spake the fiend and with necessity 
0	the tyrant s plea excused his devilish deeds 
0	then from his lofty stand on that high tree
0	down he alights among the sportful herd
0	of those four footed kinds himself now one 
0	now other as their shape served best his end
0	nearer to view his prey and unespied 
0	to mark what of their state he more might learn 
0	by word or action marked about them round
0	a lion now he stalks with fiery glare 
0	then as a tiger who by chance hath spied
0	in some purlieu two gentle fawns at play 
0	straight couches close then rising changes oft
0	his couchant watch as one who chose his ground 
0	whence rushing he might surest seize them both 
0	griped in each paw when adam first of men
0	to first of women eve thus moving speech 
0	turned him all ear to hear new utterance flow 
0	sole partner and sole part of all these joys 
0	dearer thyself than all needs must the power
0	that made us and for us this ample world 
0	be infinitely good and of his good
0	as liberal and free as infinite 
0	that raised us from the dust and placed us here
0	in all this happiness who at his hand
0	have nothing merited nor can perform
0	aught whereof he hath need he who requires
0	from us no other service than to keep
0	this one this easy charge of all the trees
0	in paradise that bear delicious fruit
0	so various not to taste that only tree
0	of knowledge planted by the tree of life 
0	so near grows death to life whate er death is 
0	some dreadful thing no doubt for well thou knowest
0	god hath pronounced it death to taste that tree 
0	the only sign of our obedience left 
0	among so many signs of power and rule
0	conferred upon us and dominion given
0	over all other creatures that possess
0	earth air and sea then let us not think hard
0	one easy prohibition who enjoy
0	free leave so large to all things else and choice
0	unlimited of manifold delights 
0	but let us ever praise him and extol
0	his bounty following our delightful task 
0	to prune these growing plants and tend these flowers 
0	which were it toilsome yet with thee were sweet 
0	to whom thus eve replied o thou for whom
0	and from whom i was formed flesh of thy flesh 
0	and without whom am to no end my guide
0	and head what thou hast said is just and right 
0	for we to him indeed all praises owe 
0	and daily thanks i chiefly who enjoy
0	so far the happier lot enjoying thee
0	pre eminent by so much odds while thou
0	like consort to thyself canst no where find 
0	that day i oft remember when from sleep
0	i first awaked and found myself reposed
0	under a shade on flowers much wondering where
0	and what i was whence thither brought and how 
0	not distant far from thence a murmuring sound
0	of waters issued from a cave and spread
0	into a liquid plain then stood unmoved
0	pure as the expanse of heaven i thither went
0	with unexperienced thought and laid me down
0	on the green bank to look into the clear
0	smooth lake that to me seemed another sky 
0	as i bent down to look just opposite
0	a shape within the watery gleam appeared 
0	bending to look on me i started back 
0	it started back but pleased i soon returned 
0	pleased it returned as soon with answering looks
0	of sympathy and love there i had fixed
0	mine eyes till now and pined with vain desire 
0	had not a voice thus warned me what thou seest 
0	what there thou seest fair creature is thyself 
0	with thee it came and goes but follow me 
0	and i will bring thee where no shadow stays
0	thy coming and thy soft embraces he
0	whose image thou art him thou shalt enjoy
0	inseparably thine to him shalt bear
0	multitudes like thyself and thence be called
0	mother of human race what could i do 
0	but follow straight invisibly thus led 
0	till i espied thee fair indeed and tall 
0	under a platane yet methought less fair 
0	less winning soft less amiably mild 
0	than that smooth watery image back i turned 
0	thou following cryedst aloud return fair eve 
0	whom flyest thou whom thou flyest of him thou art 
0	his flesh his bone to give thee being i lent
0	out of my side to thee nearest my heart 
0	substantial life to have thee by my side
0	henceforth an individual solace dear 
0	part of my soul i seek thee and thee claim
0	my other half with that thy gentle hand
0	seised mine i yielded and from that time see
0	how beauty is excelled by manly grace 
0	and wisdom which alone is truly fair 
0	so spake our general mother and with eyes
0	of conjugal attraction unreproved 
0	and meek surrender half embracing leaned
0	on our first father half her swelling breast
0	naked met his under the flowing gold
0	of her loose tresses hid he in delight
0	both of her beauty and submissive charms 
0	smiled with superiour love as jupiter
0	on juno smiles when he impregns the clouds
0	that shed mayflowers and pressed her matron lip
0	with kisses pure aside the devil turned
0	for envy yet with jealous leer malign
0	eyed them askance and to himself thus plained 
0	sight hateful sight tormenting thus these two 
0	imparadised in one another s arms 
0	the happier eden shall enjoy their fill
0	of bliss on bliss while i to hell am thrust 
0	where neither joy nor love but fierce desire 
0	among our other torments not the least 
0	still unfulfilled with pain of longing pines 
0	yet let me not forget what i have gained
0	from their own mouths all is not theirs it seems 
0	one fatal tree there stands of knowledge called 
0	forbidden them to taste knowledge forbidden
0	suspicious reasonless why should their lord
0	envy them that can it be sin to know 
0	can it be death and do they only stand
0	by ignorance is that their happy state 
0	the proof of their obedience and their faith 
0	o fair foundation laid whereon to build
0	their ruin hence i will excite their minds
0	with more desire to know and to reject
0	envious commands invented with design
0	to keep them low whom knowledge might exalt
0	equal with gods aspiring to be such 
0	they taste and die what likelier can ensue
0	but first with narrow search i must walk round
0	this garden and no corner leave unspied 
0	a chance but chance may lead where i may meet
0	some wandering spirit of heaven by fountain side 
0	or in thick shade retired from him to draw
0	what further would be learned live while ye may 
0	yet happy pair enjoy till i return 
0	short pleasures for long woes are to succeed 
0	so saying his proud step he scornful turned 
0	but with sly circumspection and began
0	through wood through waste o er hill o er dale his roam
0	mean while in utmost longitude where heaven
0	with earth and ocean meets the setting sun
0	slowly descended and with right aspect
0	against the eastern gate of paradise
0	levelled his evening rays it was a rock
0	of alabaster piled up to the clouds 
0	conspicuous far winding with one ascent
0	accessible from earth one entrance high 
0	the rest was craggy cliff that overhung
0	still as it rose impossible to climb 
0	betwixt these rocky pillars gabriel sat 
0	chief of the angelick guards awaiting night 
0	about him exercised heroick games
0	the unarmed youth of heaven but nigh at hand
0	celestial armoury shields helms and spears 
0	hung high with diamond flaming and with gold 
0	thither came uriel gliding through the even
0	on a sun beam swift as a shooting star
0	in autumn thwarts the night when vapours fired
0	impress the air and shows the mariner
0	from what point of his compass to beware
0	impetuous winds he thus began in haste 
0	gabriel to thee thy course by lot hath given
0	charge and strict watch that to this happy place
0	no evil thing approach or enter in 
0	this day at highth of noon came to my sphere
0	a spirit zealous as he seemed to know
0	more of the almighty s works and chiefly man 
0	god s latest image i described his way
0	bent all on speed and marked his aery gait 
0	but in the mount that lies from eden north 
0	where he first lighted soon discerned his looks
0	alien from heaven with passions foul obscured 
0	mine eye pursued him still but under shade
0	lost sight of him one of the banished crew 
0	i fear hath ventured from the deep to raise
0	new troubles him thy care must be to find 
0	to whom the winged warriour thus returned 
0	uriel no wonder if thy perfect sight 
0	amid the sun s bright circle where thou sitst 
0	see far and wide in at this gate none pass
0	the vigilance here placed but such as come
0	well known from heaven and since meridian hour
0	no creature thence if spirit of other sort 
0	so minded have o er leaped these earthly bounds
0	on purpose hard thou knowest it to exclude
0	spiritual substance with corporeal bar 
0	but if within the circuit of these walks 
0	in whatsoever shape he lurk of whom
0	thou tellest by morrow dawning i shall know 
0	so promised he and uriel to his charge
0	returned on that bright beam whose point now raised
0	bore him slope downward to the sun now fallen
0	beneath the azores whether the prime orb 
0	incredible how swift had thither rolled
0	diurnal or this less volubil earth 
0	by shorter flight to the east had left him there
0	arraying with reflected purple and gold
0	the clouds that on his western throne attend 
0	now came still evening on and twilight gray
0	had in her sober livery all things clad 
0	silence accompanied for beast and bird 
0	they to their grassy couch these to their nests
0	were slunk all but the wakeful nightingale 
0	she all night long her amorous descant sung 
0	silence was pleased now glowed the firmament
0	with living sapphires hesperus that led
0	the starry host rode brightest till the moon 
0	rising in clouded majesty at length
0	apparent queen unveiled her peerless light 
0	and o er the dark her silver mantle threw 
0	when adam thus to eve fair consort the hour
0	of night and all things now retired to rest 
0	mind us of like repose since god hath set
0	labour and rest as day and night to men
0	successive and the timely dew of sleep 
0	now falling with soft slumbrous weight inclines
0	our eye lids other creatures all day long
0	rove idle unemployed and less need rest 
0	man hath his daily work of body or mind
0	appointed which declares his dignity 
0	and the regard of heaven on all his ways 
0	while other animals unactive range 
0	and of their doings god takes no account 
0	to morrow ere fresh morning streak the east
0	with first approach of light we must be risen 
0	and at our pleasant labour to reform
0	yon flowery arbours yonder alleys green 
0	our walk at noon with branches overgrown 
0	that mock our scant manuring and require
0	more hands than ours to lop their wanton growth 
0	those blossoms also and those dropping gums 
0	that lie bestrown unsightly and unsmooth 
0	ask riddance if we mean to tread with ease 
0	mean while as nature wills night bids us rest 
0	to whom thus eve with perfect beauty adorned
0	my author and disposer what thou bidst
0	unargued i obey so god ordains 
0	god is thy law thou mine to know no more
0	is woman s happiest knowledge and her praise 
0	with thee conversing i forget all time 
0	all seasons and their change all please alike 
0	sweet is the breath of morn her rising sweet 
0	with charm of earliest birds pleasant the sun 
0	when first on this delightful land he spreads
0	his orient beams on herb tree fruit and flower 
0	glistering with dew fragrant the fertile earth
0	after soft showers and sweet the coming on
0	of grateful evening mild then silent night 
0	with this her solemn bird and this fair moon 
0	and these the gems of heaven her starry train 
0	but neither breath of morn when she ascends
0	with charm of earliest birds nor rising sun
0	on this delightful land nor herb fruit flower 
0	glistering with dew nor fragrance after showers 
0	nor grateful evening mild nor silent night 
0	with this her solemn bird nor walk by moon 
0	or glittering star light without thee is sweet 
0	but wherefore all night long shine these for whom
0	this glorious sight when sleep hath shut all eyes 
0	to whom our general ancestor replied 
0	daughter of god and man accomplished eve 
0	these have their course to finish round the earth 
0	by morrow evening and from land to land
0	in order though to nations yet unborn 
0	ministring light prepared they set and rise 
0	lest total darkness should by night regain
0	her old possession and extinguish life
0	in nature and all things which these soft fires
0	not only enlighten but with kindly heat
0	of various influence foment and warm 
0	temper or nourish or in part shed down
0	their stellar virtue on all kinds that grow
0	on earth made hereby apter to receive
0	perfection from the sun s more potent ray 
0	these then though unbeheld in deep of night 
0	shine not in vain nor think though men were none 
0	that heaven would want spectators god want praise 
0	millions of spiritual creatures walk the earth
0	unseen both when we wake and when we sleep 
0	all these with ceaseless praise his works behold
0	both day and night how often from the steep
0	of echoing hill or thicket have we heard
0	celestial voices to the midnight air 
0	sole or responsive each to others note 
0	singing their great creator oft in bands
0	while they keep watch or nightly rounding walk 
0	with heavenly touch of instrumental sounds
0	in full harmonick number joined their songs
0	divide the night and lift our thoughts to heaven 
0	thus talking hand in hand alone they passed
0	on to their blissful bower it was a place
0	chosen by the sovran planter when he framed
0	all things to man s delightful use the roof
0	of thickest covert was inwoven shade
0	laurel and myrtle and what higher grew
0	of firm and fragrant leaf on either side
0	acanthus and each odorous bushy shrub 
0	fenced up the verdant wall each beauteous flower 
0	iris all hues roses and jessamin 
0	reared high their flourished heads between and wrought
0	mosaick underfoot the violet 
0	crocus and hyacinth with rich inlay
0	broidered the ground more coloured than with stone
0	of costliest emblem other creature here 
0	bird beast insect or worm durst enter none 
0	such was their awe of man in shadier bower
0	more sacred and sequestered though but feigned 
0	pan or sylvanus never slept nor nymph
0	nor faunus haunted here in close recess 
0	with flowers garlands and sweet smelling herbs 
0	espoused eve decked first her nuptial bed 
0	and heavenly quires the hymenaean sung 
0	what day the genial angel to our sire
0	brought her in naked beauty more adorned 
0	more lovely than pandora whom the gods
0	endowed with all their gifts and o too like
0	in sad event when to the unwiser son
0	mankind with her fair looks to be avenged
0	on him who had stole jove s authentick fire 
0	thus at their shady lodge arrived both stood 
0	both turned and under open sky adored
0	the god that made both sky air earth and heaven 
0	which they beheld the moon s resplendent globe 
0	and starry pole thou also madest the night 
0	maker omnipotent and thou the day 
0	which we in our appointed work employed 
0	have finished happy in our mutual help
0	and mutual love the crown of all our bliss
0	ordained by thee and this delicious place
0	for us too large where thy abundance wants
0	partakers and uncropt falls to the ground 
0	but thou hast promised from us two a race
0	to fill the earth who shall with us extol
0	thy goodness infinite both when we wake 
0	and when we seek as now thy gift of sleep 
0	this said unanimous and other rites
0	observing none but adoration pure
0	which god likes best into their inmost bower
0	handed they went and eased the putting off
0	these troublesome disguises which we wear 
0	straight side by side were laid nor turned i ween 
0	adam from his fair spouse nor eve the rites
0	mysterious of connubial love refused 
0	whatever hypocrites austerely talk
0	of purity and place and innocence 
0	defaming as impure what god declares
0	pure and commands to some leaves free to all 
0	our maker bids encrease who bids abstain
0	hail wedded love mysterious law true source
0	of human offspring sole propriety
0	in paradise of all things common else 
0	by thee adulterous lust was driven from men
0	among the bestial herds to range by thee
0	founded in reason loyal just and pure 
0	relations dear and all the charities
0	of father son and brother first were known 
0	far be it that i should write thee sin or blame 
0	or think thee unbefitting holiest place 
0	perpetual fountain of domestick sweets 
0	whose bed is undefiled and chaste pronounced 
0	present or past as saints and patriarchs used 
0	here love his golden shafts employs here lights
0	his constant lamp and waves his purple wings 
0	reigns here and revels not in the bought smile
0	of harlots loveless joyless unendeared 
0	casual fruition nor in court amours 
0	mixed dance or wanton mask or midnight ball 
0	or serenate which the starved lover sings
0	to his proud fair best quitted with disdain 
0	these lulled by nightingales embracing slept 
0	and on their naked limbs the flowery roof
0	showered roses which the morn repaired sleep on 
0	blest pair and o yet happiest if ye seek
0	no happier state and know to know no more 
0	now had night measured with her shadowy cone
0	half way up hill this vast sublunar vault 
0	and from their ivory port the cherubim 
0	forth issuing at the accustomed hour stood armed
0	to their night watches in warlike parade 
0	when gabriel to his next in power thus spake 
0	uzziel half these draw off and coast the south
0	with strictest watch these other wheel the north 
0	our circuit meets full west as flame they part 
0	half wheeling to the shield half to the spear 
0	from these two strong and subtle spirits he called
0	that near him stood and gave them thus in charge 
0	ithuriel and zephon with winged speed
0	search through this garden leave unsearched no nook 
0	but chiefly where those two fair creatures lodge 
0	now laid perhaps asleep secure of harm 
0	this evening from the sun s decline arrived 
0	who tells of some infernal spirit seen
0	hitherward bent who could have thought escaped
0	the bars of hell on errand bad no doubt 
0	such where ye find seise fast and hither bring 
0	so saying on he led his radiant files 
0	dazzling the moon these to the bower direct
0	in search of whom they sought him there they found
0	squat like a toad close at the ear of eve 
0	assaying by his devilish art to reach
0	the organs of her fancy and with them forge
0	illusions as he list phantasms and dreams 
0	or if inspiring venom he might taint
0	the animal spirits that from pure blood arise
0	like gentle breaths from rivers pure thence raise
0	at least distempered discontented thoughts 
0	vain hopes vain aims inordinate desires 
0	blown up with high conceits ingendering pride 
0	him thus intent ithuriel with his spear
0	touched lightly for no falshood can endure
0	touch of celestial temper but returns
0	of force to its own likeness up he starts
0	discovered and surprised as when a spark
0	lights on a heap of nitrous powder laid
0	fit for the tun some magazine to store
0	against a rumoured war the smutty grain 
0	with sudden blaze diffused inflames the air 
0	so started up in his own shape the fiend 
0	back stept those two fair angels half amazed
0	so sudden to behold the grisly king 
0	yet thus unmoved with fear accost him soon 
0	which of those rebel spirits adjudged to hell
0	comest thou escaped thy prison and transformed 
0	why sat st thou like an enemy in wait 
0	here watching at the head of these that sleep 
0	know ye not then said satan filled with scorn 
0	know ye not me ye knew me once no mate
0	for you there sitting where ye durst not soar 
0	not to know me argues yourselves unknown 
0	the lowest of your throng or if ye know 
0	why ask ye and superfluous begin
0	your message like to end as much in vain 
0	to whom thus zephon answering scorn with scorn 
0	think not revolted spirit thy shape the same 
0	or undiminished brightness to be known 
0	as when thou stoodest in heaven upright and pure 
0	that glory then when thou no more wast good 
0	departed from thee and thou resemblest now
0	thy sin and place of doom obscure and foul 
0	but come for thou be sure shalt give account
0	to him who sent us whose charge is to keep
0	this place inviolable and these from harm 
0	so spake the cherub and his grave rebuke 
0	severe in youthful beauty added grace
0	invincible abashed the devil stood 
0	and felt how awful goodness is and saw
0	virtue in her shape how lovely saw and pined
0	his loss but chiefly to find here observed
0	his lustre visibly impaired yet seemed
0	undaunted if i must contend said he 
0	best with the best the sender not the sent 
0	or all at once more glory will be won 
0	or less be lost thy fear said zephon bold 
0	will save us trial what the least can do
0	single against thee wicked and thence weak 
0	the fiend replied not overcome with rage 
0	but like a proud steed reined went haughty on 
0	champing his iron curb to strive or fly
0	he held it vain awe from above had quelled
0	his heart not else dismayed now drew they nigh
0	the western point where those half rounding guards
0	just met and closing stood in squadron joined 
0	a waiting next command to whom their chief 
0	gabriel from the front thus called aloud 
0	o friends i hear the tread of nimble feet
0	hasting this way and now by glimpse discern
0	ithuriel and zephon through the shade 
0	and with them comes a third of regal port 
0	but faded splendour wan who by his gait
0	and fierce demeanour seems the prince of hell 
0	not likely to part hence without contest 
0	stand firm for in his look defiance lours 
0	he scarce had ended when those two approached 
0	and brief related whom they brought where found 
0	how busied in what form and posture couched 
0	to whom with stern regard thus gabriel spake 
0	why hast thou satan broke the bounds prescribed
0	to thy transgressions and disturbed the charge
0	of others who approve not to transgress
0	by thy example but have power and right
0	to question thy bold entrance on this place 
0	employed it seems to violate sleep and those
0	whose dwelling god hath planted here in bliss 
0	to whom thus satan with contemptuous brow 
0	gabriel thou hadst in heaven the esteem of wise 
0	and such i held thee but this question asked
0	puts me in doubt lives there who loves his pain 
0	who would not finding way break loose from hell 
0	though thither doomed thou wouldst thyself no doubt
0	and boldly venture to whatever place
0	farthest from pain where thou mightst hope to change
0	torment with ease and soonest recompense
0	dole with delight which in this place i sought 
0	to thee no reason who knowest only good 
0	but evil hast not tried and wilt object
0	his will who bounds us let him surer bar
0	his iron gates if he intends our stay
0	in that dark durance thus much what was asked 
0	the rest is true they found me where they say 
0	but that implies not violence or harm 
0	thus he in scorn the warlike angel moved 
0	disdainfully half smiling thus replied 
0	o loss of one in heaven to judge of wise
0	since satan fell whom folly overthrew 
0	and now returns him from his prison scaped 
0	gravely in doubt whether to hold them wise
0	or not who ask what boldness brought him hither
0	unlicensed from his bounds in hell prescribed 
0	so wise he judges it to fly from pain
0	however and to scape his punishment 
0	so judge thou still presumptuous till the wrath 
0	which thou incurrest by flying meet thy flight
0	sevenfold and scourge that wisdom back to hell 
0	which taught thee yet no better that no pain
0	can equal anger infinite provoked 
0	but wherefore thou alone wherefore with thee
0	came not all hell broke loose or thou than they
0	less hardy to endure courageous chief 
0	the first in flight from pain hadst thou alleged
0	to thy deserted host this cause of flight 
0	thou surely hadst not come sole fugitive 
0	to which the fiend thus answered frowning stern 
0	not that i less endure or shrink from pain 
0	insulting angel well thou knowest i stood
0	thy fiercest when in battle to thy aid
0	the blasting vollied thunder made all speed 
0	and seconded thy else not dreaded spear 
0	but still thy words at random as before 
0	argue thy inexperience what behoves
0	from hard assays and ill successes past
0	a faithful leader not to hazard all
0	through ways of danger by himself untried 
0	i therefore i alone first undertook
0	to wing the desolate abyss and spy
0	this new created world whereof in hell
0	fame is not silent here in hope to find
0	better abode and my afflicted powers
0	to settle here on earth or in mid air 
0	though for possession put to try once more
0	what thou and thy gay legions dare against 
0	whose easier business were to serve their lord
0	high up in heaven with songs to hymn his throne 
0	and practised distances to cringe not fight 
0	to whom the warriour angel soon replied 
0	to say and straight unsay pretending first
0	wise to fly pain professing next the spy 
0	argues no leader but a liar traced 
0	satan and couldst thou faithful add o name 
0	o sacred name of faithfulness profaned 
0	faithful to whom to thy rebellious crew 
0	army of fiends fit body to fit head 
0	was this your discipline and faith engaged 
0	your military obedience to dissolve
0	allegiance to the acknowledged power supreme 
0	and thou sly hypocrite who now wouldst seem
0	patron of liberty who more than thou
0	once fawned and cringed and servilely adored
0	heaven s awful monarch wherefore but in hope
0	to dispossess him and thyself to reign 
0	but mark what i arreed thee now avant 
0	fly neither whence thou fledst if from this hour
0	within these hallowed limits thou appear 
0	back to the infernal pit i drag thee chained 
0	and seal thee so as henceforth not to scorn
0	the facile gates of hell too slightly barred 
0	so threatened he but satan to no threats
0	gave heed but waxing more in rage replied 
0	then when i am thy captive talk of chains 
0	proud limitary cherub but ere then
0	far heavier load thyself expect to feel
0	from my prevailing arm though heaven s king
0	ride on thy wings and thou with thy compeers 
0	us d to the yoke drawest his triumphant wheels
0	in progress through the road of heaven star paved 
0	while thus he spake the angelick squadron bright
0	turned fiery red sharpening in mooned horns
0	their phalanx and began to hem him round
0	with ported spears as thick as when a field
0	of ceres ripe for harvest waving bends
0	her bearded grove of ears which way the wind
0	sways them the careful plowman doubting stands 
0	left on the threshing floor his hopeless sheaves
0	prove chaff on the other side satan alarmed 
0	collecting all his might dilated stood 
0	like teneriff or atlas unremoved 
0	his stature reached the sky and on his crest
0	sat horrour plumed nor wanted in his grasp
0	what seemed both spear and shield now dreadful deeds
0	might have ensued nor only paradise
0	in this commotion but the starry cope
0	of heaven perhaps or all the elements
0	at least had gone to wrack disturbed and torn
0	with violence of this conflict had not soon
0	the eternal to prevent such horrid fray 
0	hung forth in heaven his golden scales yet seen
0	betwixt astrea and the scorpion sign 
0	wherein all things created first he weighed 
0	the pendulous round earth with balanced air
0	in counterpoise now ponders all events 
0	battles and realms in these he put two weights 
0	the sequel each of parting and of fight 
0	the latter quick up flew and kicked the beam 
0	which gabriel spying thus bespake the fiend 
0	satan i know thy strength and thou knowest mine 
0	neither our own but given what folly then
0	to boast what arms can do since thine no more
0	than heaven permits nor mine though doubled now
0	to trample thee as mire for proof look up 
0	and read thy lot in yon celestial sign 
0	where thou art weighed and shown how light how weak 
0	if thou resist the fiend looked up and knew
0	his mounted scale aloft nor more but fled
0	murmuring and with him fled the shades of night 
0	now morn her rosy steps in the eastern clime
0	advancing sowed the earth with orient pearl 
0	when adam waked so customed for his sleep
0	was aery light from pure digestion bred 
0	and temperate vapours bland which the only sound
0	of leaves and fuming rills aurora s fan 
0	lightly dispersed and the shrill matin song
0	of birds on every bough so much the more
0	his wonder was to find unwakened eve
0	with tresses discomposed and glowing cheek 
0	as through unquiet rest he on his side
0	leaning half raised with looks of cordial love
0	hung over her enamoured and beheld
0	beauty which whether waking or asleep 
0	shot forth peculiar graces then with voice
0	mild as when zephyrus on flora breathes 
0	her hand soft touching whispered thus awake 
0	my fairest my espoused my latest found 
0	heaven s last best gift my ever new delight 
0	awake the morning shines and the fresh field
0	calls us we lose the prime to mark how spring
0	our tender plants how blows the citron grove 
0	what drops the myrrh and what the balmy reed 
0	how nature paints her colours how the bee
0	sits on the bloom extracting liquid sweet 
0	such whispering waked her but with startled eye
0	on adam whom embracing thus she spake 
0	o sole in whom my thoughts find all repose 
0	my glory my perfection glad i see
0	thy face and morn returned for i this night
0	 such night till this i never passed have dreamed 
0	if dreamed not as i oft am wont of thee 
0	works of day past or morrow s next design 
0	but of offence and trouble which my mind
0	knew never till this irksome night methought 
0	close at mine ear one called me forth to walk
0	with gentle voice i thought it thine it said 
0	 why sleepest thou eve now is the pleasant time 
0	the cool the silent save where silence yields
0	to the night warbling bird that now awake
0	tunes sweetest his love laboured song now reigns
0	full orbed the moon and with more pleasing light
0	shadowy sets off the face of things in vain 
0	if none regard heaven wakes with all his eyes 
0	whom to behold but thee nature s desire 
0	in whose sight all things joy with ravishment
0	attracted by thy beauty still to gaze 
0	i rose as at thy call but found thee not 
0	to find thee i directed then my walk 
0	and on methought alone i passed through ways
0	that brought me on a sudden to the tree
0	of interdicted knowledge fair it seemed 
0	much fairer to my fancy than by day 
0	and as i wondering looked beside it stood
0	one shaped and winged like one of those from heaven
0	by us oft seen his dewy locks distilled
0	ambrosia on that tree he also gazed 
0	and o fair plant said he with fruit surcharged 
0	deigns none to ease thy load and taste thy sweet 
0	nor god nor man is knowledge so despised 
0	or envy or what reserve forbids to taste 
0	forbid who will none shall from me withhold
0	longer thy offered good why else set here 
0	this said he paused not but with venturous arm
0	he plucked he tasted me damp horrour chilled
0	at such bold words vouched with a deed so bold 
0	but he thus overjoyed o fruit divine 
0	sweet of thyself but much more sweet thus cropt 
0	forbidden here it seems as only fit
0	for gods yet able to make gods of men 
0	and why not gods of men since good the more
0	communicated more abundant grows 
0	the author not impaired but honoured more 
0	here happy creature fair angelick eve 
0	partake thou also happy though thou art 
0	happier thou mayest be worthier canst not be 
0	taste this and be henceforth among the gods
0	thyself a goddess not to earth confined 
0	but sometimes in the air as we sometimes
0	ascend to heaven by merit thine and see
0	what life the gods live there and such live thou 
0	so saying he drew nigh and to me held 
0	even to my mouth of that same fruit held part
0	which he had plucked the pleasant savoury smell
0	so quickened appetite that i methought 
0	could not but taste forthwith up to the clouds
0	with him i flew and underneath beheld
0	the earth outstretched immense a prospect wide
0	and various wondering at my flight and change
0	to this high exaltation suddenly
0	my guide was gone and i methought sunk down 
0	and fell asleep but o how glad i waked
0	to find this but a dream thus eve her night
0	related and thus adam answered sad 
0	best image of myself and dearer half 
0	the trouble of thy thoughts this night in sleep
0	affects me equally nor can i like
0	this uncouth dream of evil sprung i fear 
0	yet evil whence in thee can harbour none 
0	created pure but know that in the soul
0	are many lesser faculties that serve
0	reason as chief among these fancy next
0	her office holds of all external things
0	which the five watchful senses represent 
0	she forms imaginations aery shapes 
0	which reason joining or disjoining frames
0	all what we affirm or what deny and call
0	our knowledge or opinion then retires
0	into her private cell when nature rests 
0	oft in her absence mimick fancy wakes
0	to imitate her but misjoining shapes 
0	wild work produces oft and most in dreams 
0	ill matching words and deeds long past or late 
0	some such resemblances methinks i find
0	of our last evening s talk in this thy dream 
0	but with addition strange yet be not sad 
0	evil into the mind of god or man
0	may come and go so unreproved and leave
0	no spot or blame behind which gives me hope
0	that what in sleep thou didst abhor to dream 
0	waking thou never will consent to do 
0	be not disheartened then nor cloud those looks 
0	that wont to be more cheerful and serene 
0	than when fair morning first smiles on the world 
0	and let us to our fresh employments rise
0	among the groves the fountains and the flowers
0	that open now their choisest bosomed smells 
0	reserved from night and kept for thee in store 
0	so cheered he his fair spouse and she was cheered 
0	but silently a gentle tear let fall
0	from either eye and wiped them with her hair 
0	two other precious drops that ready stood 
0	each in their crystal sluice he ere they fell
0	kissed as the gracious signs of sweet remorse
0	and pious awe that feared to have offended 
0	so all was cleared and to the field they haste 
0	but first from under shady arborous roof
0	soon as they forth were come to open sight
0	of day spring and the sun who scarce up risen 
0	with wheels yet hovering o er the ocean brim 
0	shot parallel to the earth his dewy ray 
0	discovering in wide landskip all the east
0	of paradise and eden s happy plains 
0	lowly they bowed adoring and began
0	their orisons each morning duly paid
0	in various style for neither various style
0	nor holy rapture wanted they to praise
0	their maker in fit strains pronounced or sung
0	unmeditated such prompt eloquence
0	flowed from their lips in prose or numerous verse 
0	more tuneable than needed lute or harp
0	to add more sweetness and they thus began 
0	these are thy glorious works parent of good 
0	almighty thine this universal frame 
0	thus wonderous fair thyself how wonderous then 
0	unspeakable who sitst above these heavens
0	to us invisible or dimly seen
0	in these thy lowest works yet these declare
0	thy goodness beyond thought and power divine 
0	speak ye who best can tell ye sons of light 
0	angels for ye behold him and with songs
0	and choral symphonies day without night 
0	circle his throne rejoicing ye in heaven
0	on earth join all ye creatures to extol
0	him first him last him midst and without end 
0	fairest of stars last in the train of night 
0	if better thou belong not to the dawn 
0	sure pledge of day that crownest the smiling morn
0	with thy bright circlet praise him in thy sphere 
0	while day arises that sweet hour of prime 
0	thou sun of this great world both eye and soul 
0	acknowledge him thy greater sound his praise
0	in thy eternal course both when thou climbest 
0	and when high noon hast gained and when thou fallest 
0	moon that now meetest the orient sun now flyest 
0	with the fixed stars fixed in their orb that flies 
0	and ye five other wandering fires that move
0	in mystick dance not without song resound
0	his praise who out of darkness called up light 
0	air and ye elements the eldest birth
0	of nature s womb that in quaternion run
0	perpetual circle multiform and mix
0	and nourish all things let your ceaseless change
0	vary to our great maker still new praise 
0	ye mists and exhalations that now rise
0	from hill or steaming lake dusky or gray 
0	till the sun paint your fleecy skirts with gold 
0	in honour to the world s great author rise 
0	whether to deck with clouds the uncoloured sky 
0	or wet the thirsty earth with falling showers 
0	rising or falling still advance his praise 
0	his praise ye winds that from four quarters blow 
0	breathe soft or loud and wave your tops ye pines 
0	with every plant in sign of worship wave 
0	fountains and ye that warble as ye flow 
0	melodious murmurs warbling tune his praise 
0	join voices all ye living souls ye birds 
0	that singing up to heaven gate ascend 
0	bear on your wings and in your notes his praise 
0	ye that in waters glide and ye that walk
0	the earth and stately tread or lowly creep 
0	witness if i be silent morn or even 
0	to hill or valley fountain or fresh shade 
0	made vocal by my song and taught his praise 
0	hail universal lord be bounteous still
0	to give us only good and if the night
0	have gathered aught of evil or concealed 
0	disperse it as now light dispels the dark 
0	so prayed they innocent and to their thoughts
0	firm peace recovered soon and wonted calm 
0	on to their morning s rural work they haste 
0	among sweet dews and flowers where any row
0	of fruit trees over woody reached too far
0	their pampered boughs and needed hands to check
0	fruitless embraces or they led the vine
0	to wed her elm she spoused about him twines
0	her marriageable arms and with him brings
0	her dower the adopted clusters to adorn
0	his barren leaves them thus employed beheld
0	with pity heaven s high king and to him called
0	raphael the sociable spirit that deigned
0	to travel with tobias and secured
0	his marriage with the seventimes wedded maid 
0	raphael said he thou hearest what stir on earth
0	satan from hell scaped through the darksome gulf 
0	hath raised in paradise and how disturbed
0	this night the human pair how he designs
0	in them at once to ruin all mankind 
0	go therefore half this day as friend with friend
0	converse with adam in what bower or shade
0	thou findest him from the heat of noon retired 
0	to respite his day labour with repast 
0	or with repose and such discourse bring on 
0	as may advise him of his happy state 
0	happiness in his power left free to will 
0	left to his own free will his will though free 
0	yet mutable whence warn him to beware
0	he swerve not too secure tell him withal
0	his danger and from whom what enemy 
0	late fallen himself from heaven is plotting now
0	the fall of others from like state of bliss 
0	by violence no for that shall be withstood 
0	but by deceit and lies this let him know 
0	lest wilfully transgressing he pretend
0	surprisal unadmonished unforewarned 
0	so spake the eternal father and fulfilled
0	all justice nor delayed the winged saint
0	after his charge received but from among
0	thousand celestial ardours where he stood
0	veiled with his gorgeous wings up springing light 
0	flew through the midst of heaven the angelick quires 
0	on each hand parting to his speed gave way
0	through all the empyreal road till at the gate
0	of heaven arrived the gate self opened wide
0	on golden hinges turning as by work
0	divine the sovran architect had framed 
0	from hence no cloud or to obstruct his sight 
0	star interposed however small he sees 
0	not unconformed to other shining globes 
0	earth and the garden of god with cedars crowned
0	above all hills as when by night the glass
0	of galileo less assured observes
0	imagined lands and regions in the moon 
0	or pilot from amidst the cyclades
0	delos or samos first appearing kens
0	a cloudy spot down thither prone in flight
0	he speeds and through the vast ethereal sky
0	sails between worlds and worlds with steady wing
0	now on the polar winds then with quick fan
0	winnows the buxom air till within soar
0	of towering eagles to all the fowls he seems
0	a phoenix gazed by all as that sole bird 
0	when to enshrine his reliques in the sun s
0	at once on the eastern cliff of paradise
0	he lights and to his proper shape returns
0	a seraph winged six wings he wore to shade
0	his lineaments divine the pair that clad
0	each shoulder broad came mantling o er his breast
0	with regal ornament the middle pair
0	girt like a starry zone his waist and round
0	skirted his loins and thighs with downy gold
0	and colours dipt in heaven the third his feet
0	shadowed from either heel with feathered mail 
