0	berry or grape to whom thus adam called 
0	haste hither eve and worth thy sight behold
0	eastward among those trees what glorious shape
0	comes this way moving seems another morn
0	risen on mid noon some great behest from heaven
0	to us perhaps he brings and will vouchsafe
0	this day to be our guest but go with speed 
0	and what thy stores contain bring forth and pour
0	abundance fit to honour and receive
0	our heavenly stranger well we may afford
0	our givers their own gifts and large bestow
0	from large bestowed where nature multiplies
0	her fertile growth and by disburthening grows
0	more fruitful which instructs us not to spare 
0	to whom thus eve adam earth s hallowed mould 
0	of god inspired small store will serve where store 
0	all seasons ripe for use hangs on the stalk 
0	save what by frugal storing firmness gains
0	to nourish and superfluous moist consumes 
0	but i will haste and from each bough and brake 
0	each plant and juciest gourd will pluck such choice
0	to entertain our angel guest as he
0	beholding shall confess that here on earth
0	god hath dispensed his bounties as in heaven 
0	so saying with dispatchful looks in haste
0	she turns on hospitable thoughts intent
0	what choice to choose for delicacy best 
0	what order so contrived as not to mix
0	tastes not well joined inelegant but bring
0	taste after taste upheld with kindliest change 
0	bestirs her then and from each tender stalk
0	whatever earth all bearing mother yields
0	in india east or west or middle shore
0	in pontus or the punick coast or where
0	alcinous reigned fruit of all kinds in coat
0	rough or smooth rind or bearded husk or shell 
0	she gathers tribute large and on the board
0	heaps with unsparing hand for drink the grape
0	she crushes inoffensive must and meaths
0	from many a berry and from sweet kernels pressed
0	she tempers dulcet creams nor these to hold
0	wants her fit vessels pure then strows the ground
0	with rose and odours from the shrub unfumed 
0	mean while our primitive great sire to meet
0	his god like guest walks forth without more train
0	accompanied than with his own complete
0	perfections in himself was all his state 
0	more solemn than the tedious pomp that waits
0	on princes when their rich retinue long
0	of horses led and grooms besmeared with gold 
0	dazzles the croud and sets them all agape 
0	nearer his presence adam though not awed 
0	yet with submiss approach and reverence meek 
0	as to a superiour nature bowing low 
0	thus said native of heaven for other place
0	none can than heaven such glorious shape contain 
0	since by descending from the thrones above 
0	those happy places thou hast deigned a while
0	to want and honour these vouchsafe with us
0	two only who yet by sovran gift possess
0	this spacious ground in yonder shady bower
