0	their table was and mossy seats had round 
0	and on her ample square from side to side
0	all autumn piled though spring and autumn here
0	danced hand in hand a while discourse they hold 
0	no fear lest dinner cool when thus began
0	our author heavenly stranger please to taste
0	these bounties which our nourisher from whom
0	all perfect good unmeasured out descends 
0	to us for food and for delight hath caused
0	the earth to yield unsavoury food perhaps
0	to spiritual natures only this i know 
0	that one celestial father gives to all 
0	to whom the angel therefore what he gives
0	 whose praise be ever sung to man in part
0	spiritual may of purest spirits be found
0	no ingrateful food and food alike those pure
0	intelligential substances require 
0	as doth your rational and both contain
0	within them every lower faculty
0	of sense whereby they hear see smell touch taste 
0	tasting concoct digest assimilate 
0	and corporeal to incorporeal turn 
0	for know whatever was created needs
0	to be sustained and fed of elements
0	the grosser feeds the purer earth the sea 
0	earth and the sea feed air the air those fires
0	ethereal and as lowest first the moon 
0	whence in her visage round those spots unpurged
0	vapours not yet into her substance turned 
0	nor doth the moon no nourishment exhale
0	from her moist continent to higher orbs 
0	the sun that light imparts to all receives
0	from all his alimental recompence
0	in humid exhalations and at even
0	sups with the ocean though in heaven the trees
