0	varied his bounty so with new delights 
0	as may compare with heaven and to taste
0	think not i shall be nice so down they sat 
0	and to their viands fell nor seemingly
0	the angel nor in mist the common gloss
0	of theologians but with keen dispatch
0	of real hunger and concoctive heat
0	to transubstantiate what redounds transpires
0	through spirits with ease nor wonder if by fire
0	of sooty coal the empirick alchemist
0	can turn or holds it possible to turn 
0	metals of drossiest ore to perfect gold 
0	as from the mine mean while at table eve
0	ministered naked and their flowing cups
