0	thus when with meats and drinks they had sufficed 
0	not burdened nature sudden mind arose
0	in adam not to let the occasion pass
0	given him by this great conference to know
0	of things above his world and of their being
0	who dwell in heaven whose excellence he saw
0	transcend his own so far whose radiant forms 
0	divine effulgence whose high power so far
0	exceeded human and his wary speech
0	thus to the empyreal minister he framed 
0	inhabitant with god now know i well
0	thy favour in this honour done to man 
0	under whose lowly roof thou hast vouchsafed
0	to enter and these earthly fruits to taste 
0	food not of angels yet accepted so 
0	as that more willingly thou couldst not seem
0	at heaven s high feasts to have fed yet what compare
0	to whom the winged hierarch replied 
0	o adam one almighty is from whom
0	all things proceed and up to him return 
0	if not depraved from good created all
0	such to perfection one first matter all 
0	endued with various forms various degrees
0	of substance and in things that live of life 
0	but more refined more spiritous and pure 
0	as nearer to him placed or nearer tending
0	each in their several active spheres assigned 
0	till body up to spirit work in bounds
0	proportioned to each kind so from the root
0	springs lighter the green stalk from thence the leaves
0	more aery last the bright consummate flower
0	spirits odorous breathes flowers and their fruit 
0	man s nourishment by gradual scale sublimed 
0	to vital spirits aspire to animal 
0	to intellectual give both life and sense 
0	fancy and understanding whence the soul
0	reason receives and reason is her being 
0	discursive or intuitive discourse
0	is oftest yours the latter most is ours 
0	differing but in degree of kind the same 
0	wonder not then what god for you saw good
0	if i refuse not but convert as you
0	to proper substance time may come when men
0	with angels may participate and find
0	no inconvenient diet nor too light fare 
0	and from these corporal nutriments perhaps
0	your bodies may at last turn all to spirit 
0	improved by tract of time and winged ascend
0	ethereal as we or may at choice 
0	here or in heavenly paradises dwell 
0	if ye be found obedient and retain
0	unalterably firm his love entire 
0	whose progeny you are mean while enjoy
0	your fill what happiness this happy state
0	can comprehend incapable of more 
0	to whom the patriarch of mankind replied 
0	o favourable spirit propitious guest 
0	well hast thou taught the way that might direct
0	our knowledge and the scale of nature set
0	from center to circumference whereon 
0	in contemplation of created things 
0	by steps we may ascend to god but say 
0	what meant that caution joined if ye be found
0	obedient can we want obedience then
0	to him or possibly his love desert 
0	who formed us from the dust and placed us here
0	full to the utmost measure of what bliss
0	human desires can seek or apprehend 
0	to whom the angel son of heaven and earth 
0	attend that thou art happy owe to god 
0	that thou continuest such owe to thyself 
0	that is to thy obedience therein stand 
0	this was that caution given thee be advised 
0	god made thee perfect not immutable 
0	and good he made thee but to persevere
0	he left it in thy power ordained thy will
0	by nature free not over ruled by fate
0	inextricable or strict necessity 
0	our voluntary service he requires 
0	not our necessitated such with him
0	finds no acceptance nor can find for how
0	can hearts not free be tried whether they serve
0	willing or no who will but what they must
0	by destiny and can no other choose 
0	myself and all the angelick host that stand
0	in sight of god enthroned our happy state
0	hold as you yours while our obedience holds 
0	on other surety none freely we serve 
0	because we freely love as in our will
0	to love or not in this we stand or fall 
0	and some are fallen to disobedience fallen 
0	and so from heaven to deepest hell o fall
0	from what high state of bliss into what woe 
0	to whom our great progenitor thy words
0	attentive and with more delighted ear 
0	divine instructer i have heard than when
0	cherubick songs by night from neighbouring hills
0	aereal musick send nor knew i not
0	to be both will and deed created free 
0	yet that we never shall forget to love
0	our maker and obey him whose command
0	single is yet so just my constant thoughts
0	assured me and still assure though what thou tellest
0	hath passed in heaven some doubt within me move 
0	but more desire to hear if thou consent 
0	the full relation which must needs be strange 
0	worthy of sacred silence to be heard 
0	and we have yet large day for scarce the sun
0	hath finished half his journey and scarce begins
0	his other half in the great zone of heaven 
0	thus adam made request and raphael 
0	after short pause assenting thus began 
0	high matter thou enjoinest me o prime of men 
0	sad task and hard for how shall i relate
0	to human sense the invisible exploits
0	of warring spirits how without remorse 
0	the ruin of so many glorious once
0	and perfect while they stood how last unfold
0	the secrets of another world perhaps
0	not lawful to reveal yet for thy good
0	this is dispensed and what surmounts the reach
0	of human sense i shall delineate so 
0	by likening spiritual to corporal forms 
0	as may express them best though what if earth
0	be but a shadow of heaven and things therein
0	each to other like more than on earth is thought 
0	as yet this world was not and chaos wild
0	reigned where these heavens now roll where earth now rests
0	upon her center poised when on a day
0	 for time though in eternity applied
0	to motion measures all things durable
0	by present past and future on such day
0	as heaven s great year brings forth the empyreal host
0	of angels by imperial summons called 
0	innumerable before the almighty s throne
0	forthwith from all the ends of heaven appeared
0	under their hierarchs in orders bright 
0	ten thousand thousand ensigns high advanced 
0	standards and gonfalons twixt van and rear
0	stream in the air and for distinction serve
0	of hierarchies of orders and degrees 
0	or in their glittering tissues bear imblazed
0	holy memorials acts of zeal and love
0	recorded eminent thus when in orbs
0	of circuit inexpressible they stood 
0	orb within orb the father infinite 
0	by whom in bliss imbosomed sat the son 
0	amidst as from a flaming mount whose top
0	brightness had made invisible thus spake 
0	hear all ye angels progeny of light 
0	hear my decree which unrevoked shall stand 
0	this day i have begot whom i declare
0	my only son and on this holy hill
0	him have anointed whom ye now behold
0	at my right hand your head i him appoint 
0	and by myself have sworn to him shall bow
0	all knees in heaven and shall confess him lord 
0	under his great vice gerent reign abide
0	united as one individual soul 
0	for ever happy him who disobeys 
0	me disobeys breaks union and that day 
0	cast out from god and blessed vision falls
0	into utter darkness deep ingulfed his place
0	ordained without redemption without end 
0	so spake the omnipotent and with his words
0	all seemed well pleased all seemed but were not all 
0	that day as other solemn days they spent
0	in song and dance about the sacred hill 
0	mystical dance which yonder starry sphere
0	of planets and of fixed in all her wheels
0	resembles nearest mazes intricate 
0	eccentrick intervolved yet regular
0	then most when most irregular they seem 
0	and in their motions harmony divine
0	so smooths her charming tones that god s own ear
0	listens delighted evening now approached 
0	 for we have also our evening and our morn 
0	we ours for change delectable not need 
0	forthwith from dance to sweet repast they turn
0	desirous all in circles as they stood 
0	tables are set and on a sudden piled
0	with angels food and rubied nectar flows
0	in pearl in diamond and massy gold 
0	fruit of delicious vines the growth of heaven 
0	on flowers reposed and with fresh flowerets crowned 
0	they eat they drink and in communion sweet
0	quaff immortality and joy secure
0	of surfeit where full measure only bounds
0	excess before the all bounteous king who showered
0	with copious hand rejoicing in their joy 
0	now when ambrosial night with clouds exhaled
0	from that high mount of god whence light and shade
0	spring both the face of brightest heaven had changed
0	to grateful twilight for night comes not there
0	in darker veil and roseate dews disposed
0	all but the unsleeping eyes of god to rest 
0	wide over all the plain and wider far
0	than all this globous earth in plain outspread 
0	 such are the courts of god the angelick throng 
0	dispersed in bands and files their camp extend
0	by living streams among the trees of life 
0	pavilions numberless and sudden reared 
0	celestial tabernacles where they slept
0	fanned with cool winds save those who in their course 
0	melodious hymns about the sovran throne
0	alternate all night long but not so waked
0	satan so call him now his former name
0	is heard no more in heaven he of the first 
0	if not the first arch angel great in power 
0	in favour and pre eminence yet fraught
0	with envy against the son of god that day
0	honoured by his great father and proclaimed
0	messiah king anointed could not bear
0	through pride that sight and thought himself impaired 
0	deep malice thence conceiving and disdain 
0	soon as midnight brought on the dusky hour
0	friendliest to sleep and silence he resolved
0	with all his legions to dislodge and leave
0	unworshipt unobeyed the throne supreme 
0	contemptuous and his next subordinate
0	awakening thus to him in secret spake 
0	sleepest thou companion dear what sleep can close
0	thy eye lids and rememberest what decree
0	of yesterday so late hath passed the lips
0	of heaven s almighty thou to me thy thoughts
0	wast wont i mine to thee was wont to impart 
0	both waking we were one how then can now
0	thy sleep dissent new laws thou seest imposed 
0	new laws from him who reigns new minds may raise
0	in us who serve new counsels to debate
0	what doubtful may ensue more in this place
0	to utter is not safe assemble thou
0	of all those myriads which we lead the chief 
0	tell them that by command ere yet dim night
0	her shadowy cloud withdraws i am to haste 
0	and all who under me their banners wave 
0	homeward with flying march where we possess
0	the quarters of the north there to prepare
0	fit entertainment to receive our king 
0	the great messiah and his new commands 
0	who speedily through all the hierarchies
0	intends to pass triumphant and give laws 
0	so spake the false arch angel and infused
0	bad influence into the unwary breast
0	of his associate he together calls 
0	or several one by one the regent powers 
0	under him regent tells as he was taught 
0	that the most high commanding now ere night 
0	now ere dim night had disincumbered heaven 
0	the great hierarchal standard was to move 
0	tells the suggested cause and casts between
0	ambiguous words and jealousies to sound
0	or taint integrity but all obeyed
0	the wonted signal and superiour voice
0	of their great potentate for great indeed
0	his name and high was his degree in heaven 
0	his countenance as the morning star that guides
0	the starry flock allured them and with lies
0	drew after him the third part of heaven s host 
0	mean while the eternal eye whose sight discerns
0	abstrusest thoughts from forth his holy mount 
0	and from within the golden lamps that burn
0	nightly before him saw without their light
0	rebellion rising saw in whom how spread
0	among the sons of morn what multitudes
0	were banded to oppose his high decree 
0	and smiling to his only son thus said 
0	son thou in whom my glory i behold
0	in full resplendence heir of all my might 
0	nearly it now concerns us to be sure
0	of our omnipotence and with what arms
0	we mean to hold what anciently we claim
0	of deity or empire such a foe
0	is rising who intends to erect his throne
0	equal to ours throughout the spacious north 
0	nor so content hath in his thought to try
0	in battle what our power is or our right 
0	let us advise and to this hazard draw
0	with speed what force is left and all employ
0	in our defence lest unawares we lose
0	this our high place our sanctuary our hill 
0	to whom the son with calm aspect and clear 
0	lightning divine ineffable serene 
0	made answer mighty father thou thy foes
0	justly hast in derision and secure 
0	laughest at their vain designs and tumults vain 
0	matter to me of glory whom their hate
0	illustrates when they see all regal power
0	given me to quell their pride and in event
0	know whether i be dextrous to subdue
0	thy rebels or be found the worst in heaven 
0	so spake the son but satan with his powers 
0	far was advanced on winged speed an host
0	innumerable as the stars of night 
0	or stars of morning dew drops which the sun
0	impearls on every leaf and every flower 
0	regions they passed the mighty regencies
0	in their triple degrees regions to which
0	all thy dominion adam is no more
0	than what this garden is to all the earth 
0	and all the sea from one entire globose
0	stretched into longitude which having passed 
0	at length into the limits of the north
0	they came and satan to his royal seat
0	high on a hill far blazing as a mount
0	raised on a mount with pyramids and towers
0	from diamond quarries hewn and rocks of gold 
0	the palace of great lucifer so call
0	that structure in the dialect of men
0	interpreted which not long after he
0	affecting all equality with god 
0	in imitation of that mount whereon
0	messiah was declared in sight of heaven 
0	the mountain of the congregation called 
0	for thither he assembled all his train 
0	pretending so commanded to consult
0	about the great reception of their king 
0	thither to come and with calumnious art
0	of counterfeited truth thus held their ears 
0	if these magnifick titles yet remain
0	not merely titular since by decree
0	another now hath to himself engrossed
0	all power and us eclipsed under the name
0	of king anointed for whom all this haste
0	of midnight march and hurried meeting here 
0	this only to consult how we may best 
0	with what may be devised of honours new 
0	receive him coming to receive from us
0	knee tribute yet unpaid prostration vile 
0	too much to one but double how endured 
0	to one and to his image now proclaimed 
0	but what if better counsels might erect
0	our minds and teach us to cast off this yoke 
0	will ye submit your necks and choose to bend
0	the supple knee ye will not if i trust
0	to know ye right or if ye know yourselves
0	natives and sons of heaven possessed before
0	by none and if not equal all yet free 
0	equally free for orders and degrees
0	jar not with liberty but well consist 
0	who can in reason then or right assume
0	monarchy over such as live by right
0	his equals if in power and splendour less 
0	in freedom equal or can introduce
0	law and edict on us who without law
0	err not much less for this to be our lord 
0	and look for adoration to the abuse
0	of those imperial titles which assert
0	our being ordained to govern not to serve 
0	thus far his bold discourse without controul
0	had audience when among the seraphim
0	abdiel than whom none with more zeal adored
0	the deity and divine commands obeyed 
0	stood up and in a flame of zeal severe
0	the current of his fury thus opposed 
0	o argument blasphemous false and proud 
0	words which no ear ever to hear in heaven
0	expected least of all from thee ingrate 
0	in place thyself so high above thy peers 
0	canst thou with impious obloquy condemn
0	the just decree of god pronounced and sworn 
0	that to his only son by right endued
0	with regal scepter every soul in heaven
0	shall bend the knee and in that honour due
0	confess him rightful king unjust thou sayest 
0	flatly unjust to bind with laws the free 
0	and equal over equals to let reign 
0	one over all with unsucceeded power 
0	shalt thou give law to god shalt thou dispute
0	with him the points of liberty who made
0	thee what thou art and formed the powers of heaven
0	such as he pleased and circumscribed their being 
0	yet by experience taught we know how good 
0	and of our good and of our dignity
0	how provident he is how far from thought
0	to make us less bent rather to exalt
0	our happy state under one head more near
0	united but to grant it thee unjust 
0	that equal over equals monarch reign 
0	thyself though great and glorious dost thou count 
0	or all angelick nature joined in one 
0	equal to him begotten son by whom 
0	as by his word the mighty father made
0	all things even thee and all the spirits of heaven
0	by him created in their bright degrees 
0	crowned them with glory and to their glory named
0	essential powers nor by his reign obscured 
0	but more illustrious made since he the head
0	one of our number thus reduced becomes 
0	his laws our laws all honour to him done
0	returns our own cease then this impious rage 
0	and tempt not these but hasten to appease
0	the incensed father and the incensed son 
0	while pardon may be found in time besought 
0	so spake the fervent angel but his zeal
0	none seconded as out of season judged 
0	or singular and rash whereat rejoiced
0	the apostate and more haughty thus replied 
0	that we were formed then sayest thou and the work
0	of secondary hands by task transferred
0	from father to his son strange point and new 
0	doctrine which we would know whence learned who saw
0	when this creation was rememberest thou
0	thy making while the maker gave thee being 
0	we know no time when we were not as now 
0	know none before us self begot self raised
0	by our own quickening power when fatal course
0	had circled his full orb the birth mature
0	of this our native heaven ethereal sons 
0	our puissance is our own our own right hand
0	shall teach us highest deeds by proof to try
0	who is our equal then thou shalt behold
0	whether by supplication we intend
0	address and to begirt the almighty throne
0	beseeching or besieging this report 
0	these tidings carry to the anointed king 
0	and fly ere evil intercept thy flight 
0	he said and as the sound of waters deep 
0	hoarse murmur echoed to his words applause
0	through the infinite host nor less for that
0	the flaming seraph fearless though alone
0	encompassed round with foes thus answered bold 
0	o alienate from god o spirit accursed 
0	forsaken of all good i see thy fall
0	determined and thy hapless crew involved
0	in this perfidious fraud contagion spread
0	both of thy crime and punishment henceforth
0	no more be troubled how to quit the yoke
0	of god s messiah those indulgent laws
0	will not be now vouchsafed other decrees
0	against thee are gone forth without recall 
0	that golden scepter which thou didst reject 
0	is now an iron rod to bruise and break
0	thy disobedience well thou didst advise 
0	yet not for thy advice or threats i fly
0	these wicked tents devoted lest the wrath
0	impendent raging into sudden flame 
0	distinguish not for soon expect to feel
0	his thunder on thy head devouring fire 
0	then who created thee lamenting learn 
0	when who can uncreate thee thou shalt know 
0	so spake the seraph abdiel faithful found
0	among the faithless faithful only he 
0	among innumerable false unmoved 
0	unshaken unseduced unterrified 
0	his loyalty he kept his love his zeal 
0	nor number nor example with him wrought
0	to swerve from truth or change his constant mind 
0	though single from amidst them forth he passed 
0	long way through hostile scorn which he sustained
0	superiour nor of violence feared aught 
0	and with retorted scorn his back he turned
0	on those proud towers to swift destruction doomed 
0	all night the dreadless angel unpursued 
0	through heaven s wide champain held his way till morn 
0	waked by the circling hours with rosy hand
0	unbarred the gates of light there is a cave
0	within the mount of god fast by his throne 
0	where light and darkness in perpetual round
0	lodge and dislodge by turns which makes through heaven
0	grateful vicissitude like day and night 
0	light issues forth and at the other door
0	obsequious darkness enters till her hour
0	to veil the heaven though darkness there might well
0	seem twilight here and now went forth the morn
0	such as in highest heaven arrayed in gold
0	empyreal from before her vanished night 
0	shot through with orient beams when all the plain
0	covered with thick embattled squadrons bright 
0	chariots and flaming arms and fiery steeds 
0	reflecting blaze on blaze first met his view 
0	war he perceived war in procinct and found
0	already known what he for news had thought
0	to have reported gladly then he mixed
0	among those friendly powers who him received
0	with joy and acclamations loud that one 
0	that of so many myriads fallen yet one
0	returned not lost on to the sacred hill
0	they led him high applauded and present
0	before the seat supreme from whence a voice 
0	from midst a golden cloud thus mild was heard 
0	servant of god well done well hast thou fought
0	the better fight who single hast maintained
0	against revolted multitudes the cause
0	of truth in word mightier than they in arms 
0	and for the testimony of truth hast borne
0	universal reproach far worse to bear
0	than violence for this was all thy care
0	to stand approved in sight of god though worlds
0	judged thee perverse the easier conquest now
0	remains thee aided by this host of friends 
0	back on thy foes more glorious to return 
0	than scorned thou didst depart and to subdue
0	by force who reason for their law refuse 
0	right reason for their law and for their king
0	messiah who by right of merit reigns 
0	go michael of celestial armies prince 
0	and thou in military prowess next 
0	gabriel lead forth to battle these my sons
0	invincible lead forth my armed saints 
0	by thousands and by millions ranged for fight 
0	equal in number to that godless crew
0	rebellious them with fire and hostile arms
0	fearless assault and to the brow of heaven
0	pursuing drive them out from god and bliss 
0	into their place of punishment the gulf
0	of tartarus which ready opens wide
0	his fiery chaos to receive their fall 
0	so spake the sovran voice and clouds began
0	to darken all the hill and smoke to roll
