0	a dreadful interval and front to front
0	presented stood in terrible array
0	of hideous length before the cloudy van 
0	on the rough edge of battle ere it joined 
0	satan with vast and haughty strides advanced 
0	came towering armed in adamant and gold 
0	abdiel that sight endured not where he stood
0	among the mightiest bent on highest deeds 
0	and thus his own undaunted heart explores 
0	o heaven that such resemblance of the highest
0	should yet remain where faith and realty
0	remain not wherefore should not strength and might
0	there fail where virtue fails or weakest prove
0	where boldest though to fight unconquerable 
0	his puissance trusting in the almighty s aid 
0	i mean to try whose reason i have tried
0	unsound and false nor is it aught but just 
0	that he who in debate of truth hath won 
0	should win in arms in both disputes alike
0	victor though brutish that contest and foul 
0	when reason hath to deal with force yet so
0	most reason is that reason overcome 
0	so pondering and from his armed peers
0	forth stepping opposite half way he met
0	his daring foe at this prevention more
0	incensed and thus securely him defied 
0	proud art thou met thy hope was to have reached
0	the highth of thy aspiring unopposed 
0	the throne of god unguarded and his side
0	abandoned at the terrour of thy power
0	or potent tongue fool not to think how vain
0	against the omnipotent to rise in arms 
0	who out of smallest things could without end 
0	have raised incessant armies to defeat
