0	reaching beyond all limit at one blow 
0	unaided could have finished thee and whelmed
0	thy legions under darkness but thou seest
0	all are not of thy train there be who faith
0	prefer and piety to god though then
0	to thee not visible when i alone
0	seemed in thy world erroneous to dissent
0	from all my sect thou seest now learn too late
0	how few sometimes may know when thousands err 
0	whom the grand foe with scornful eye askance 
0	thus answered ill for thee but in wished hour
0	of my revenge first sought for thou returnest
0	from flight seditious angel to receive
0	thy merited reward the first assay
0	of this right hand provoked since first that tongue 
0	inspired with contradiction durst oppose
0	a third part of the gods in synod met
0	their deities to assert who while they feel
0	vigour divine within them can allow
0	omnipotence to none but well thou comest
0	before thy fellows ambitious to win
0	from me some plume that thy success may show
0	destruction to the rest this pause between 
0	 unanswered lest thou boast to let thee know 
0	at first i thought that liberty and heaven
0	to heavenly souls had been all one but now
0	i see that most through sloth had rather serve 
0	ministring spirits trained up in feast and song 
0	such hast thou armed the minstrelsy of heaven 
0	servility with freedom to contend 
0	as both their deeds compared this day shall prove 
0	to whom in brief thus abdiel stern replied 
0	apostate still thou errest nor end wilt find
0	of erring from the path of truth remote 
0	unjustly thou depravest it with the name
0	of servitude to serve whom god ordains 
0	or nature god and nature bid the same 
0	when he who rules is worthiest and excels
0	them whom he governs this is servitude 
0	to serve the unwise or him who hath rebelled
0	against his worthier as thine now serve thee 
0	thyself not free but to thyself enthralled 
0	yet lewdly darest our ministring upbraid 
0	reign thou in hell thy kingdom let me serve
0	in heaven god ever blest and his divine
0	behests obey worthiest to be obeyed 
0	yet chains in hell not realms expect mean while
0	from me returned as erst thou saidst from flight 
0	this greeting on thy impious crest receive 
0	so saying a noble stroke he lifted high 
0	which hung not but so swift with tempest fell
0	on the proud crest of satan that no sight 
0	nor motion of swift thought less could his shield 
0	such ruin intercept ten paces huge
0	he back recoiled the tenth on bended knee
0	his massy spear upstaid as if on earth
0	winds under ground or waters forcing way 
0	sidelong had pushed a mountain from his seat 
0	half sunk with all his pines amazement seised
0	the rebel thrones but greater rage to see
