0	enjoyment of our right as gods yet hard
0	for gods and too unequal work we find 
0	against unequal arms to fight in pain 
0	against unpained impassive from which evil
0	ruin must needs ensue for what avails
0	valour or strength though matchless quelled with pain
0	which all subdues and makes remiss the hands
0	of mightiest sense of pleasure we may well
0	spare out of life perhaps and not repine 
0	but live content which is the calmest life 
0	but pain is perfect misery the worst
0	of evils and excessive overturns
0	all patience he who therefore can invent
0	with what more forcible we may offend
0	our yet unwounded enemies or arm
0	ourselves with like defence to me deserves
0	no less than for deliverance what we owe 
0	whereto with look composed satan replied 
0	not uninvented that which thou aright
0	believest so main to our success i bring 
0	which of us who beholds the bright surface
0	of this ethereous mould whereon we stand 
0	this continent of spacious heaven adorned
0	with plant fruit flower ambrosial gems and gold 
0	whose eye so superficially surveys
0	these things as not to mind from whence they grow
0	deep under ground materials dark and crude 
