0	the affable arch angel had forewarned
0	adam by dire example to beware
0	apostasy by what befel in heaven
0	to those apostates lest the like befall
0	in paradise to adam or his race 
0	charged not to touch the interdicted tree 
0	if they transgress and slight that sole command 
0	so easily obeyed amid the choice
0	of all tastes else to please their appetite 
0	though wandering he with his consorted eve 
0	the story heard attentive and was filled
0	with admiration and deep muse to hear
0	of things so high and strange things to their thought
0	so unimaginable as hate in heaven 
0	and war so near the peace of god in bliss 
0	with such confusion but the evil soon
0	driven back redounded as a flood on those
0	from whom it sprung impossible to mix
0	with blessedness whence adam soon repealed
0	the doubts that in his heart arose and now
0	led on yet sinless with desire to know
0	what nearer might concern him how this world
0	of heaven and earth conspicuous first began 
0	when and whereof created for what cause 
0	what within eden or without was done
0	before his memory as one whose drouth
0	yet scarce allayed still eyes the current stream 
0	whose liquid murmur heard new thirst excites 
0	proceeded thus to ask his heavenly guest 
0	great things and full of wonder in our ears 
0	far differing from this world thou hast revealed 
0	divine interpreter by favour sent
0	down from the empyrean to forewarn
0	us timely of what might else have been our loss 
0	unknown which human knowledge could not reach 
0	for which to the infinitely good we owe
0	immortal thanks and his admonishment
0	receive with solemn purpose to observe
0	immutably his sovran will the end
0	of what we are but since thou hast vouchsafed
0	gently for our instruction to impart
0	things above earthly thought which yet concerned
0	our knowing as to highest wisdom seemed 
0	deign to descend now lower and relate
0	what may no less perhaps avail us known 
0	how first began this heaven which we behold
0	distant so high with moving fires adorned
0	innumerable and this which yields or fills
0	all space the ambient air wide interfused
0	embracing round this floried earth what cause
0	moved the creator in his holy rest
0	through all eternity so late to build
0	in chaos and the work begun how soon
0	absolved if unforbid thou mayest unfold
0	what we not to explore the secrets ask
0	of his eternal empire but the more
0	to magnify his works the more we know 
0	and the great light of day yet wants to run
0	much of his race though steep suspense in heaven 
0	held by thy voice thy potent voice he hears 
0	and longer will delay to hear thee tell
0	his generation and the rising birth
0	of nature from the unapparent deep 
0	or if the star of evening and the moon
0	haste to thy audience night with her will bring 
0	silence and sleep listening to thee will watch 
0	or we can bid his absence till thy song
0	end and dismiss thee ere the morning shine 
0	thus adam his illustrious guest besought 
0	and thus the godlike angel answered mild 
0	this also thy request with caution asked 
0	obtain though to recount almighty works
0	what words or tongue of seraph can suffice 
0	or heart of man suffice to comprehend 
0	yet what thou canst attain which best may serve
0	to glorify the maker and infer
0	thee also happier shall not be withheld
0	thy hearing such commission from above
0	i have received to answer thy desire
0	of knowledge within bounds beyond abstain
0	to ask nor let thine own inventions hope
0	things not revealed which the invisible king 
0	only omniscient hath suppressed in night 
0	to none communicable in earth or heaven 
0	enough is left besides to search and know 
0	but knowledge is as food and needs no less
0	her temperance over appetite to know
0	in measure what the mind may well contain 
0	oppresses else with surfeit and soon turns
0	wisdom to folly as nourishment to wind 
0	know then that after lucifer from heaven
0	 so call him brighter once amidst the host
0	of angels than that star the stars among 
