0	from thee their names and pay thee fealty
0	with low subjection understand the same
0	of fish within their watery residence 
0	not hither summoned since they cannot change
0	their element to draw the thinner air 
0	as thus he spake each bird and beast behold
0	approaching two and two these cowering low
0	with blandishment each bird stooped on his wing 
0	i named them as they passed and understood
0	their nature with such knowledge god endued
0	my sudden apprehension but in these
0	i found not what methought i wanted still 
0	and to the heavenly vision thus presumed 
0	o by what name for thou above all these 
0	above mankind or aught than mankind higher 
0	surpassest far my naming how may i
0	adore thee author of this universe 
0	and all this good to man for whose well being
0	so amply and with hands so liberal 
0	thou hast provided all things but with me
0	i see not who partakes in solitude
0	what happiness who can enjoy alone 
0	or all enjoying what contentment find 
0	thus i presumptuous and the vision bright 
0	as with a smile more brightened thus replied 
0	what callest thou solitude is not the earth
0	with various living creatures and the air
0	replenished and all these at thy command
0	to come and play before thee knowest thou not
0	their language and their ways they also know 
0	and reason not contemptibly with these
0	find pastime and bear rule thy realm is large 
0	so spake the universal lord and seemed
0	so ordering i with leave of speech implored 
0	and humble deprecation thus replied 
0	let not my words offend thee heavenly power 
0	my maker be propitious while i speak 
0	hast thou not made me here thy substitute 
0	and these inferiour far beneath me set 
0	among unequals what society
0	can sort what harmony or true delight 
0	which must be mutual in proportion due
0	given and received but in disparity
0	the one intense the other still remiss 
0	cannot well suit with either but soon prove
0	tedious alike of fellowship i speak
0	such as i seek fit to participate
0	all rational delight wherein the brute
0	cannot be human consort they rejoice
0	each with their kind lion with lioness 
0	so fitly them in pairs thou hast combined 
0	much less can bird with beast or fish with fowl
0	so well converse nor with the ox the ape 
0	worse then can man with beast and least of all 
0	whereto the almighty answered not displeased 
0	a nice and subtle happiness i see 
0	thou to thyself proposest in the choice
0	of thy associates adam and wilt taste
0	no pleasure though in pleasure solitary 
0	what thinkest thou then of me and this my state 
0	seem i to thee sufficiently possessed
0	of happiness or not who am alone
0	from all eternity for none i know
0	second to me or like equal much less 
0	how have i then with whom to hold converse 
0	save with the creatures which i made and those
0	to me inferiour infinite descents
0	beneath what other creatures are to thee 
0	he ceased i lowly answered to attain
