0	thus far to try thee adam i was pleased 
0	and find thee knowing not of beasts alone 
0	which thou hast rightly named but of thyself 
0	expressing well the spirit within thee free 
0	my image not imparted to the brute 
0	whose fellowship therefore unmeet for thee
0	good reason was thou freely shouldst dislike 
0	and be so minded still i ere thou spakest 
0	knew it not good for man to be alone 
0	and no such company as then thou sawest
