0	thus have i told thee all my state and brought
0	my story to the sum of earthly bliss 
0	which i enjoy and must confess to find
0	in all things else delight indeed but such
0	as used or not works in the mind no change 
0	nor vehement desire these delicacies
0	i mean of taste sight smell herbs fruits and flowers 
0	walks and the melody of birds but here
0	far otherwise transported i behold 
0	transported touch here passion first i felt 
0	commotion strange in all enjoyments else
0	superiour and unmoved here only weak
0	against the charm of beauty s powerful glance 
0	or nature failed in me and left some part
0	not proof enough such object to sustain 
0	or from my side subducting took perhaps
0	more than enough at least on her bestowed
0	too much of ornament in outward show
0	elaborate of inward less exact 
0	for well i understand in the prime end
0	of nature her the inferiour in the mind
0	and inward faculties which most excel 
0	in outward also her resembling less
0	his image who made both and less expressing
0	the character of that dominion given
0	o er other creatures yet when i approach
0	her loveliness so absolute she seems
0	and in herself complete so well to know
