0	seems wisest virtuousest discreetest best 
0	all higher knowledge in her presence falls
0	degraded wisdom in discourse with her
0	loses discountenanced and like folly shows 
0	authority and reason on her wait 
0	as one intended first not after made
0	occasionally and to consummate all 
0	greatness of mind and nobleness their seat
0	build in her loveliest and create an awe
0	about her as a guard angelick placed 
0	to whom the angel with contracted brow 
0	accuse not nature she hath done her part 
0	do thou but thine and be not diffident
0	of wisdom she deserts thee not if thou
0	dismiss not her when most thou needest her nigh 
0	by attributing overmuch to things
0	less excellent as thou thyself perceivest 
0	for what admirest thou what transports thee so 
0	an outside fair no doubt and worthy well
0	thy cherishing thy honouring and thy love 
0	not thy subjection weigh with her thyself 
0	then value oft times nothing profits more
0	than self esteem grounded on just and right
0	well managed of that skill the more thou knowest 
0	the more she will acknowledge thee her head 
0	and to realities yield all her shows 
0	made so adorn for thy delight the more 
0	so awful that with honour thou mayest love
0	thy mate who sees when thou art seen least wise 
0	but if the sense of touch whereby mankind
