0	at joust and tournament then marshall d feast
0	serv d up in hall with sewers and seneshals 
0	the skill of artifice or office mean 
0	not that which justly gives heroick name
0	to person or to poem me of these
0	nor skill d nor studious higher argument
0	remains sufficient of itself to raise
0	that name unless an age too late or cold
0	climate or years damp my intended wing
0	depress d and much they may if all be mine 
0	not hers who brings it nightly to my ear 
0	the sun was sunk and after him the star
0	of hesperus whose office is to bring
0	twilight upon the earth short arbiter
0	 twixt day and night and now from end to end
0	night s hemisphere had veil d the horizon round 
0	when satan who late fled before the threats
0	of gabriel out of eden now improv d
0	in meditated fraud and malice bent
0	on man s destruction maugre what might hap
0	of heavier on himself fearless returned
0	by night he fled and at midnight returned
0	from compassing the earth cautious of day 
0	since uriel regent of the sun descried
0	his entrance and foreworned the cherubim
0	that kept their watch thence full of anguish driven 
0	the space of seven continued nights he rode
0	with darkness thrice the equinoctial line
0	he circled four times crossed the car of night
0	from pole to pole traversing each colure 
0	on the eighth returned and on the coast averse
0	from entrance or cherubick watch by stealth
0	found unsuspected way there was a place 
0	now not though sin not time first wrought the change 
0	where tigris at the foot of paradise 
0	into a gulf shot under ground till part
0	rose up a fountain by the tree of life 
0	in with the river sunk and with it rose
0	satan involved in rising mist then sought
0	where to lie hid sea he had searched and land 
0	from eden over pontus and the pool
0	maeotis up beyond the river ob 
0	downward as far antarctick and in length 
0	west from orontes to the ocean barred
0	at darien thence to the land where flows
0	ganges and indus thus the orb he roamed
0	with narrow search and with inspection deep
0	considered every creature which of all
0	most opportune might serve his wiles and found
0	the serpent subtlest beast of all the field 
0	him after long debate irresolute
0	of thoughts revolved his final sentence chose
0	fit vessel fittest imp of fraud in whom
0	to enter and his dark suggestions hide
0	from sharpest sight for in the wily snake
0	whatever sleights none would suspicious mark 
0	as from his wit and native subtlety
0	proceeding which in other beasts observed 
0	doubt might beget of diabolick power
0	active within beyond the sense of brute 
0	thus he resolved but first from inward grief
0	his bursting passion into plaints thus poured 
0	more justly seat worthier of gods as built
0	with second thoughts reforming what was old 
0	o earth how like to heaven if not preferred
0	for what god after better worse would build 
0	terrestrial heaven danced round by other heavens
0	that shine yet bear their bright officious lamps 
0	light above light for thee alone as seems 
0	in thee concentring all their precious beams
0	of sacred influence as god in heaven
0	is center yet extends to all so thou 
0	centring receivest from all those orbs in thee 
0	not in themselves all their known virtue appears
0	productive in herb plant and nobler birth
0	of creatures animate with gradual life
0	of growth sense reason all summed up in man 
0	with what delight could i have walked thee round 
0	if i could joy in aught sweet interchange
0	of hill and valley rivers woods and plains 
0	now land now sea and shores with forest crowned 
0	rocks dens and caves but i in none of these
0	find place or refuge and the more i see
0	pleasures about me so much more i feel
0	torment within me as from the hateful siege
0	of contraries all good to me becomes
0	bane and in heaven much worse would be my state 
0	but neither here seek i no nor in heaven
0	to dwell unless by mastering heaven s supreme 
0	nor hope to be myself less miserable
0	by what i seek but others to make such
0	as i though thereby worse to me redound 
0	for only in destroying i find ease
0	to my relentless thoughts and him destroyed 
0	or won to what may work his utter loss 
0	for whom all this was made all this will soon
0	follow as to him linked in weal or woe 
0	in woe then that destruction wide may range 
0	to me shall be the glory sole among
0	the infernal powers in one day to have marred
0	what he almighty styled six nights and days
0	continued making and who knows how long
0	before had been contriving though perhaps
0	not longer than since i in one night freed
0	from servitude inglorious well nigh half
0	the angelick name and thinner left the throng
0	of his adorers he to be avenged 
0	and to repair his numbers thus impaired 
0	whether such virtue spent of old now failed
0	more angels to create if they at least
0	are his created or to spite us more 
0	determined to advance into our room
0	a creature formed of earth and him endow 
0	exalted from so base original 
0	with heavenly spoils our spoils what he decreed 
0	he effected man he made and for him built
0	magnificent this world and earth his seat 
0	him lord pronounced and o indignity 
0	subjected to his service angel wings 
0	and flaming ministers to watch and tend
0	their earthly charge of these the vigilance
0	i dread and to elude thus wrapt in mist
0	of midnight vapour glide obscure and pry
0	in every bush and brake where hap may find
0	the serpent sleeping in whose mazy folds
0	to hide me and the dark intent i bring 
0	o foul descent that i who erst contended
0	with gods to sit the highest am now constrained
0	into a beast and mixed with bestial slime 
0	this essence to incarnate and imbrute 
0	that to the highth of deity aspired 
0	but what will not ambition and revenge
0	descend to who aspires must down as low
0	as high he soared obnoxious first or last 
0	to basest things revenge at first though sweet 
0	bitter ere long back on itself recoils 
0	let it i reck not so it light well aimed 
0	since higher i fall short on him who next
0	provokes my envy this new favourite
0	of heaven this man of clay son of despite 
0	whom us the more to spite his maker raised
0	from dust spite then with spite is best repaid 
0	so saying through each thicket dank or dry 
0	like a black mist low creeping he held on
0	his midnight search where soonest he might find
0	the serpent him fast sleeping soon he found
0	in labyrinth of many a round self rolled 
0	his head the midst well stored with subtile wiles 
0	not yet in horrid shade or dismal den 
0	nor nocent yet but on the grassy herb 
0	fearless unfeared he slept in at his mouth
0	the devil entered and his brutal sense 
0	in heart or head possessing soon inspired
0	with act intelligential but his sleep
0	disturbed not waiting close the approach of morn 
0	now when as sacred light began to dawn
0	in eden on the humid flowers that breathed
0	their morning incense when all things that breathe 
0	from the earth s great altar send up silent praise
0	to the creator and his nostrils fill
0	with grateful smell forth came the human pair 
0	and joined their vocal worship to the quire
0	of creatures wanting voice that done partake
0	the season prime for sweetest scents and airs 
0	then commune how that day they best may ply
0	their growing work for much their work out grew
0	the hands dispatch of two gardening so wide 
0	and eve first to her husband thus began 
0	adam well may we labour still to dress
0	this garden still to tend plant herb and flower 
0	our pleasant task enjoined but till more hands
0	aid us the work under our labour grows 
0	luxurious by restraint what we by day
0	lop overgrown or prune or prop or bind 
0	one night or two with wanton growth derides
0	tending to wild thou therefore now advise 
0	or bear what to my mind first thoughts present 
0	let us divide our labours thou where choice
0	leads thee or where most needs whether to wind
0	the woodbine round this arbour or direct
0	the clasping ivy where to climb while i 
0	in yonder spring of roses intermixed
0	with myrtle find what to redress till noon 
0	for while so near each other thus all day
0	our task we choose what wonder if so near
0	looks intervene and smiles or object new
0	casual discourse draw on which intermits
0	our day s work brought to little though begun
0	early and the hour of supper comes unearned 
0	to whom mild answer adam thus returned 
0	sole eve associate sole to me beyond
0	compare above all living creatures dear 
0	well hast thou motioned well thy thoughts employed 
0	how we might best fulfil the work which here
0	god hath assigned us nor of me shalt pass
0	unpraised for nothing lovelier can be found
0	in woman than to study houshold good 
0	and good works in her husband to promote 
0	yet not so strictly hath our lord imposed
0	labour as to debar us when we need
0	refreshment whether food or talk between 
0	food of the mind or this sweet intercourse
0	of looks and smiles for smiles from reason flow 
0	to brute denied and are of love the food 
0	love not the lowest end of human life 
0	for not to irksome toil but to delight 
0	he made us and delight to reason joined 
0	these paths and bowers doubt not but our joint hands
0	will keep from wilderness with ease as wide
0	as we need walk till younger hands ere long
0	assist us but if much converse perhaps
0	thee satiate to short absence i could yield 
0	for solitude sometimes is best society 
0	and short retirement urges sweet return 
0	but other doubt possesses me lest harm
0	befall thee severed from me for thou knowest
0	what hath been warned us what malicious foe
0	envying our happiness and of his own
0	despairing seeks to work us woe and shame
0	by sly assault and somewhere nigh at hand
0	watches no doubt with greedy hope to find
0	his wish and best advantage us asunder 
0	hopeless to circumvent us joined where each
0	to other speedy aid might lend at need 
0	whether his first design be to withdraw
0	our fealty from god or to disturb
0	conjugal love than which perhaps no bliss
0	enjoyed by us excites his envy more 
0	or this or worse leave not the faithful side
0	that gave thee being still shades thee and protects 
0	the wife where danger or dishonour lurks 
0	safest and seemliest by her husband stays 
0	who guards her or with her the worst endures 
0	to whom the virgin majesty of eve 
0	as one who loves and some unkindness meets 
0	with sweet austere composure thus replied 
0	offspring of heaven and earth and all earth s lord 
0	that such an enemy we have who seeks
0	our ruin both by thee informed i learn 
0	and from the parting angel over heard 
0	as in a shady nook i stood behind 
0	just then returned at shut of evening flowers 
0	but that thou shouldst my firmness therefore doubt
0	to god or thee because we have a foe
0	may tempt it i expected not to hear 
0	his violence thou fearest not being such
0	as we not capable of death or pain 
0	can either not receive or can repel 
0	his fraud is then thy fear which plain infers
0	thy equal fear that my firm faith and love
0	can by his fraud be shaken or seduced 
0	thoughts which how found they harbour in thy breast 
0	adam mis thought of her to thee so dear 
0	to whom with healing words adam replied 
0	daughter of god and man immortal eve 
0	for such thou art from sin and blame entire 
0	not diffident of thee do i dissuade
0	thy absence from my sight but to avoid
0	the attempt itself intended by our foe 
0	for he who tempts though in vain at least asperses
0	the tempted with dishonour foul supposed
0	not incorruptible of faith not proof
0	against temptation thou thyself with scorn
0	and anger wouldst resent the offered wrong 
0	though ineffectual found misdeem not then 
0	if such affront i labour to avert
0	from thee alone which on us both at once
0	the enemy though bold will hardly dare 
0	or daring first on me the assault shall light 
0	nor thou his malice and false guile contemn 
0	subtle he needs must be who could seduce
0	angels nor think superfluous other s aid 
0	i from the influence of thy looks receive
0	access in every virtue in thy sight
0	more wise more watchful stronger if need were
0	of outward strength while shame thou looking on 
0	shame to be overcome or over reached 
0	would utmost vigour raise and raised unite 
0	why shouldst not thou like sense within thee feel
0	when i am present and thy trial choose
0	with me best witness of thy virtue tried 
0	so spake domestick adam in his care
0	and matrimonial love but eve who thought
0	less attributed to her faith sincere 
0	thus her reply with accent sweet renewed 
0	if this be our condition thus to dwell
0	in narrow circuit straitened by a foe 
0	subtle or violent we not endued
0	single with like defence wherever met 
0	how are we happy still in fear of harm 
0	but harm precedes not sin only our foe 
0	tempting affronts us with his foul esteem
0	of our integrity his foul esteem
0	sticks no dishonour on our front but turns
0	foul on himself then wherefore shunned or feared
0	by us who rather double honour gain
0	from his surmise proved false find peace within 
0	favour from heaven our witness from the event 
0	and what is faith love virtue unassayed
0	alone without exteriour help sustained 
0	let us not then suspect our happy state
0	left so imperfect by the maker wise 
0	as not secure to single or combined 
0	frail is our happiness if this be so 
0	and eden were no eden thus exposed 
0	to whom thus adam fervently replied 
0	o woman best are all things as the will
0	of god ordained them his creating hand
0	nothing imperfect or deficient left
0	of all that he created much less man 
0	or aught that might his happy state secure 
0	secure from outward force within himself
0	the danger lies yet lies within his power 
0	against his will he can receive no harm 
0	but god left free the will for what obeys
0	reason is free and reason he made right 
0	but bid her well be ware and still erect 
0	lest by some fair appearing good surprised 
0	she dictate false and mis inform the will
0	to do what god expressly hath forbid 
0	not then mistrust but tender love enjoins 
0	that i should mind thee oft and mind thou me 
0	firm we subsist yet possible to swerve 
0	since reason not impossibly may meet
0	some specious object by the foe suborned 
0	and fall into deception unaware 
0	not keeping strictest watch as she was warned 
0	seek not temptation then which to avoid
0	were better and most likely if from me
0	thou sever not trial will come unsought 
0	wouldst thou approve thy constancy approve
0	first thy obedience the other who can know 
0	not seeing thee attempted who attest 
0	but if thou think trial unsought may find
0	us both securer than thus warned thou seemest 
0	go for thy stay not free absents thee more 
0	go in thy native innocence rely
0	on what thou hast of virtue summon all 
0	for god towards thee hath done his part do thine 
0	so spake the patriarch of mankind but eve
0	persisted yet submiss though last replied 
0	with thy permission then and thus forewarned
0	chiefly by what thy own last reasoning words
0	touched only that our trial when least sought 
0	may find us both perhaps far less prepared 
0	the willinger i go nor much expect
0	a foe so proud will first the weaker seek 
0	so bent the more shall shame him his repulse 
0	thus saying from her husband s hand her hand
0	soft she withdrew and like a wood nymph light 
0	oread or dryad or of delia s train 
0	betook her to the groves but delia s self
0	in gait surpassed and goddess like deport 
0	though not as she with bow and quiver armed 
0	but with such gardening tools as art yet rude 
0	guiltless of fire had formed or angels brought 
0	to pales or pomona thus adorned 
0	likest she seemed pomona when she fled
0	vertumnus or to ceres in her prime 
0	yet virgin of proserpina from jove 
0	her long with ardent look his eye pursued
0	delighted but desiring more her stay 
0	oft he to her his charge of quick return
0	repeated she to him as oft engaged
0	to be returned by noon amid the bower 
0	and all things in best order to invite
0	noontide repast or afternoon s repose 
0	o much deceived much failing hapless eve 
0	of thy presumed return event perverse 
0	thou never from that hour in paradise
0	foundst either sweet repast or sound repose 
0	such ambush hid among sweet flowers and shades 
0	waited with hellish rancour imminent
0	to intercept thy way or send thee back
0	despoiled of innocence of faith of bliss 
0	for now and since first break of dawn the fiend 
0	mere serpent in appearance forth was come 
0	and on his quest where likeliest he might find
0	the only two of mankind but in them
0	the whole included race his purposed prey 
0	in bower and field he sought where any tuft
0	of grove or garden plot more pleasant lay 
0	their tendance or plantation for delight 
0	by fountain or by shady rivulet
0	he sought them both but wished his hap might find
0	eve separate he wished but not with hope
0	of what so seldom chanced when to his wish 
0	beyond his hope eve separate he spies 
0	veiled in a cloud of fragrance where she stood 
0	half spied so thick the roses blushing round
0	about her glowed oft stooping to support
0	each flower of slender stalk whose head though gay
0	carnation purple azure or specked with gold 
0	hung drooping unsustained them she upstays
0	gently with myrtle band mindless the while
0	herself though fairest unsupported flower 
0	from her best prop so far and storm so nigh 
0	nearer he drew and many a walk traversed
0	of stateliest covert cedar pine or palm 
0	then voluble and bold now hid now seen 
0	among thick woven arborets and flowers
0	imbordered on each bank the hand of eve 
0	spot more delicious than those gardens feigned
0	or of revived adonis or renowned
0	alcinous host of old laertes son 
0	or that not mystick where the sapient king
0	much he the place admired the person more 
0	as one who long in populous city pent 
0	where houses thick and sewers annoy the air 
0	forth issuing on a summer s morn to breathe
0	among the pleasant villages and farms
0	adjoined from each thing met conceives delight 
0	the smell of grain or tedded grass or kine 
0	or dairy each rural sight each rural sound 
0	if chance with nymph like step fair virgin pass 
0	what pleasing seemed for her now pleases more 
0	she most and in her look sums all delight 
0	such pleasure took the serpent to behold
0	this flowery plat the sweet recess of eve
0	thus early thus alone her heavenly form
0	angelick but more soft and feminine 
0	her graceful innocence her every air
0	of gesture or least action overawed
0	his malice and with rapine sweet bereaved
0	his fierceness of the fierce intent it brought 
0	that space the evil one abstracted stood
0	from his own evil and for the time remained
0	stupidly good of enmity disarmed 
0	of guile of hate of envy of revenge 
0	but the hot hell that always in him burns 
0	though in mid heaven soon ended his delight 
0	and tortures him now more the more he sees
0	of pleasure not for him ordained then soon
0	fierce hate he recollects and all his thoughts
0	of mischief gratulating thus excites 
0	thoughts whither have ye led me with what sweet
0	compulsion thus transported to forget
0	what hither brought us hate not love nor hope
0	of paradise for hell hope here to taste
0	of pleasure but all pleasure to destroy 
0	save what is in destroying other joy
0	to me is lost then let me not let pass
0	occasion which now smiles behold alone
0	the woman opportune to all attempts 
0	her husband for i view far round not nigh 
0	whose higher intellectual more i shun 
0	and strength of courage haughty and of limb
0	heroick built though of terrestrial mould 
0	foe not informidable exempt from wound 
0	i not so much hath hell debased and pain
0	enfeebled me to what i was in heaven 
0	she fair divinely fair fit love for gods 
0	not terrible though terrour be in love
0	and beauty not approached by stronger hate 
0	hate stronger under show of love well feigned 
0	the way which to her ruin now i tend 
0	so spake the enemy of mankind enclosed
0	in serpent inmate bad and toward eve
0	addressed his way not with indented wave 
0	prone on the ground as since but on his rear 
0	circular base of rising folds that towered
0	fold above fold a surging maze his head
0	crested aloft and carbuncle his eyes 
0	with burnished neck of verdant gold erect
0	amidst his circling spires that on the grass
0	floated redundant pleasing was his shape
0	and lovely never since of serpent kind
0	lovelier not those that in illyria changed 
0	in epidaurus nor to which transformed
0	ammonian jove or capitoline was seen 
0	he with olympias this with her who bore
0	scipio the highth of rome with tract oblique
0	at first as one who sought access but feared
0	to interrupt side long he works his way 
0	as when a ship by skilful steersmen wrought
0	nigh river s mouth or foreland where the wind
0	veers oft as oft so steers and shifts her sail 
0	so varied he and of his tortuous train
0	curled many a wanton wreath in sight of eve 
0	to lure her eye she busied heard the sound
0	of rusling leaves but minded not as used
0	to such disport before her through the field 
0	from every beast more duteous at her call 
0	than at circean call the herd disguised 
0	he bolder now uncalled before her stood 
0	but as in gaze admiring oft he bowed
0	his turret crest and sleek enamelled neck 
0	fawning and licked the ground whereon she trod 
0	the eye of eve to mark his play he glad
0	of her attention gained with serpent tongue
0	organick or impulse of vocal air 
0	his fraudulent temptation thus began 
0	wonder not sovran mistress if perhaps
0	thou canst who art sole wonder much less arm
0	thy looks the heaven of mildness with disdain 
0	displeased that i approach thee thus and gaze
0	insatiate i thus single nor have feared
0	thy awful brow more awful thus retired 
0	fairest resemblance of thy maker fair 
0	thee all things living gaze on all things thine
0	by gift and thy celestial beauty adore
0	with ravishment beheld there best beheld 
0	where universally admired but here
0	in this enclosure wild these beasts among 
0	beholders rude and shallow to discern
0	half what in thee is fair one man except 
0	who sees thee and what is one who should be seen
0	a goddess among gods adored and served
0	by angels numberless thy daily train 
0	so glozed the tempter and his proem tuned 
0	into the heart of eve his words made way 
0	though at the voice much marvelling at length 
0	not unamazed she thus in answer spake 
0	what may this mean language of man pronounced
0	by tongue of brute and human sense expressed 
0	the first at least of these i thought denied
0	to beasts whom god on their creation day 
0	created mute to all articulate sound 
0	the latter i demur for in their looks
0	much reason and in their actions oft appears 
0	thee serpent subtlest beast of all the field
0	i knew but not with human voice endued 
0	redouble then this miracle and say 
0	how camest thou speakable of mute and how
0	to me so friendly grown above the rest
0	of brutal kind that daily are in sight 
0	say for such wonder claims attention due 
0	to whom the guileful tempter thus replied 
0	empress of this fair world resplendent eve 
0	easy to me it is to tell thee all
0	what thou commandest and right thou shouldst be obeyed 
0	i was at first as other beasts that graze
0	the trodden herb of abject thoughts and low 
0	as was my food nor aught but food discerned
0	or sex and apprehended nothing high 
0	till on a day roving the field i chanced
0	a goodly tree far distant to behold
0	loaden with fruit of fairest colours mixed 
0	ruddy and gold i nearer drew to gaze 
0	when from the boughs a savoury odour blown 
0	grateful to appetite more pleased my sense
0	than smell of sweetest fennel or the teats
0	of ewe or goat dropping with milk at even 
0	unsucked of lamb or kid that tend their play 
0	to satisfy the sharp desire i had
0	of tasting those fair apples i resolved
0	not to defer hunger and thirst at once 
0	powerful persuaders quickened at the scent
0	of that alluring fruit urged me so keen 
0	about the mossy trunk i wound me soon 
0	for high from ground the branches would require
0	thy utmost reach or adam s round the tree
0	all other beasts that saw with like desire
0	longing and envying stood but could not reach 
0	amid the tree now got where plenty hung
0	tempting so nigh to pluck and eat my fill
0	i spared not for such pleasure till that hour 
0	at feed or fountain never had i found 
0	sated at length ere long i might perceive
0	strange alteration in me to degree
0	of reason in my inward powers and speech
0	wanted not long though to this shape retained 
0	thenceforth to speculations high or deep
0	i turned my thoughts and with capacious mind
0	considered all things visible in heaven 
0	or earth or middle all things fair and good 
0	but all that fair and good in thy divine
0	semblance and in thy beauty s heavenly ray 
0	united i beheld no fair to thine
0	equivalent or second which compelled
0	me thus though importune perhaps to come
0	and gaze and worship thee of right declared
0	sovran of creatures universal dame 
0	so talked the spirited sly snake and eve 
0	yet more amazed unwary thus replied 
0	serpent thy overpraising leaves in doubt
0	the virtue of that fruit in thee first proved 
0	but say where grows the tree from hence how far 
0	for many are the trees of god that grow
0	in paradise and various yet unknown
0	to us in such abundance lies our choice 
0	as leaves a greater store of fruit untouched 
0	still hanging incorruptible till men
0	grow up to their provision and more hands
0	help to disburden nature of her birth 
0	to whom the wily adder blithe and glad 
0	empress the way is ready and not long 
0	beyond a row of myrtles on a flat 
0	fast by a fountain one small thicket past
0	of blowing myrrh and balm if thou accept
0	my conduct i can bring thee thither soon
0	lead then said eve he leading swiftly rolled
0	in tangles and made intricate seem straight 
0	to mischief swift hope elevates and joy
0	brightens his crest as when a wandering fire 
0	compact of unctuous vapour which the night
0	condenses and the cold environs round 
0	kindled through agitation to a flame 
0	which oft they say some evil spirit attends 
0	hovering and blazing with delusive light 
0	misleads the amazed night wanderer from his way
0	to bogs and mires and oft through pond or pool 
0	there swallowed up and lost from succour far 
0	so glistered the dire snake and into fraud
0	led eve our credulous mother to the tree
0	of prohibition root of all our woe 
0	which when she saw thus to her guide she spake 
0	serpent we might have spared our coming hither 
0	fruitless to me though fruit be here to excess 
0	the credit of whose virtue rest with thee 
0	wonderous indeed if cause of such effects 
0	but of this tree we may not taste nor touch 
0	god so commanded and left that command
0	sole daughter of his voice the rest we live
0	law to ourselves our reason is our law 
0	to whom the tempter guilefully replied 
0	indeed hath god then said that of the fruit
0	of all these garden trees ye shall not eat 
0	yet lords declared of all in earth or air 
0	to whom thus eve yet sinless of the fruit
0	of each tree in the garden we may eat 
0	but of the fruit of this fair tree amidst
0	the garden god hath said ye shall not eat
0	thereof nor shall ye touch it lest ye die 
0	she scarce had said though brief when now more bold
0	the tempter but with show of zeal and love
0	to man and indignation at his wrong 
0	new part puts on and as to passion moved 
0	fluctuates disturbed yet comely and in act
0	raised as of some great matter to begin 
0	as when of old some orator renowned 
0	in athens or free rome where eloquence
0	flourished since mute to some great cause addressed 
0	stood in himself collected while each part 
0	motion each act won audience ere the tongue 
0	sometimes in highth began as no delay
0	of preface brooking through his zeal of right 
0	so standing moving or to highth up grown 
0	the tempter all impassioned thus began 
0	o sacred wise and wisdom giving plant 
0	mother of science now i feel thy power
0	within me clear not only to discern
0	things in their causes but to trace the ways
0	of highest agents deemed however wise 
0	queen of this universe do not believe
0	those rigid threats of death ye shall not die 
0	how should you by the fruit it gives you life
0	to knowledge by the threatener look on me 
0	me who have touched and tasted yet both live 
0	and life more perfect have attained than fate
0	meant me by venturing higher than my lot 
0	shall that be shut to man which to the beast
0	is open or will god incense his ire
0	for such a petty trespass and not praise
0	rather your dauntless virtue whom the pain
0	of death denounced whatever thing death be 
0	deterred not from achieving what might lead
0	to happier life knowledge of good and evil 
0	of good how just of evil if what is evil
0	be real why not known since easier shunned 
0	god therefore cannot hurt ye and be just 
0	not just not god not feared then nor obeyed 
0	your fear itself of death removes the fear 
0	why then was this forbid why but to awe 
0	why but to keep ye low and ignorant 
0	his worshippers he knows that in the day
0	ye eat thereof your eyes that seem so clear 
0	yet are but dim shall perfectly be then
0	opened and cleared and ye shall be as gods 
0	knowing both good and evil as they know 
0	that ye shall be as gods since i as man 
0	internal man is but proportion meet 
0	i of brute human ye of human gods 
0	so ye shall die perhaps by putting off
0	human to put on gods death to be wished 
0	though threatened which no worse than this can bring 
0	and what are gods that man may not become
0	as they participating god like food 
0	the gods are first and that advantage use
0	on our belief that all from them proceeds 
0	i question it for this fair earth i see 
0	warmed by the sun producing every kind 
0	them nothing if they all things who enclosed
0	knowledge of good and evil in this tree 
0	that whoso eats thereof forthwith attains
0	wisdom without their leave and wherein lies
0	the offence that man should thus attain to know 
0	what can your knowledge hurt him or this tree
0	impart against his will if all be his 
0	or is it envy and can envy dwell
0	in heavenly breasts these these and many more
0	causes import your need of this fair fruit 
0	goddess humane reach then and freely taste 
0	he ended and his words replete with guile 
0	into her heart too easy entrance won 
0	fixed on the fruit she gazed which to behold
0	might tempt alone and in her ears the sound
0	yet rung of his persuasive words impregned
0	with reason to her seeming and with truth 
0	mean while the hour of noon drew on and waked
0	an eager appetite raised by the smell
0	so savoury of that fruit which with desire 
0	inclinable now grown to touch or taste 
0	solicited her longing eye yet first
0	pausing a while thus to herself she mused 
0	great are thy virtues doubtless best of fruits 
0	though kept from man and worthy to be admired 
0	whose taste too long forborn at first assay
0	gave elocution to the mute and taught
0	the tongue not made for speech to speak thy praise 
0	thy praise he also who forbids thy use 
0	conceals not from us naming thee the tree
0	of knowledge knowledge both of good and evil 
0	forbids us then to taste but his forbidding
0	commends thee more while it infers the good
0	by thee communicated and our want 
0	for good unknown sure is not had or had
0	and yet unknown is as not had at all 
0	in plain then what forbids he but to know 
0	forbids us good forbids us to be wise 
0	such prohibitions bind not but if death
0	bind us with after bands what profits then
0	our inward freedom in the day we eat
0	of this fair fruit our doom is we shall die 
0	how dies the serpent he hath eaten and lives 
0	and knows and speaks and reasons and discerns 
0	irrational till then for us alone
0	was death invented or to us denied
0	this intellectual food for beasts reserved 
0	for beasts it seems yet that one beast which first
0	hath tasted envies not but brings with joy
0	the good befallen him author unsuspect 
0	friendly to man far from deceit or guile 
0	what fear i then rather what know to fear
0	under this ignorance of good and evil 
0	of god or death of law or penalty 
0	here grows the cure of all this fruit divine 
0	fair to the eye inviting to the taste 
0	of virtue to make wise what hinders then
0	of man s first disobedience and the fruit
0	to reach and feed at once both body and mind 
0	so saying her rash hand in evil hour
0	forth reaching to the fruit she plucked she eat 
0	earth felt the wound and nature from her seat 
0	sighing through all her works gave signs of woe 
0	that all was lost back to the thicket slunk
0	the guilty serpent and well might for eve 
0	intent now wholly on her taste nought else
0	regarded such delight till then as seemed 
0	in fruit she never tasted whether true
0	or fancied so through expectation high
0	of knowledge not was godhead from her thought 
0	greedily she ingorged without restraint 
0	and knew not eating death satiate at length 
0	and hightened as with wine jocund and boon 
0	thus to herself she pleasingly began 
0	o sovran virtuous precious of all trees
0	in paradise of operation blest
0	to sapience hitherto obscured infamed 
0	and thy fair fruit let hang as to no end
0	created but henceforth my early care 
0	not without song each morning and due praise 
0	shall tend thee and the fertile burden ease
0	of thy full branches offered free to all 
0	till dieted by thee i grow mature
0	in knowledge as the gods who all things know 
0	though others envy what they cannot give 
0	for had the gift been theirs it had not here
0	thus grown experience next to thee i owe 
0	best guide not following thee i had remained
0	in ignorance thou openest wisdom s way 
0	and givest access though secret she retire 
0	and i perhaps am secret heaven is high 
0	high and remote to see from thence distinct
0	each thing on earth and other care perhaps
0	may have diverted from continual watch
0	our great forbidder safe with all his spies
0	about him but to adam in what sort
0	shall i appear shall i to him make known
0	as yet my change and give him to partake
0	full happiness with me or rather not 
0	but keeps the odds of knowledge in my power
0	without copartner so to add what wants
0	in female sex the more to draw his love 
0	and render me more equal and perhaps 
0	a thing not undesirable sometime
0	superiour for inferiour who is free
0	this may be well but what if god have seen 
0	and death ensue then i shall be no more 
0	and adam wedded to another eve 
0	shall live with her enjoying i extinct 
0	a death to think confirmed then i resolve 
0	adam shall share with me in bliss or woe 
0	so dear i love him that with him all deaths
0	i could endure without him live no life 
0	so saying from the tree her step she turned 
0	but first low reverence done as to the power
0	that dwelt within whose presence had infused
0	into the plant sciential sap derived
0	from nectar drink of gods adam the while 
0	waiting desirous her return had wove
0	of choicest flowers a garland to adorn
0	her tresses and her rural labours crown 
0	as reapers oft are wont their harvest queen 
0	great joy he promised to his thoughts and new
0	solace in her return so long delayed 
0	yet oft his heart divine of something ill 
0	misgave him he the faltering measure felt 
0	and forth to meet her went the way she took
0	that morn when first they parted by the tree
0	of knowledge he must pass there he her met 
0	scarce from the tree returning in her hand
0	a bough of fairest fruit that downy smiled 
0	new gathered and ambrosial smell diffused 
0	to him she hasted in her face excuse
0	came prologue and apology too prompt 
0	which with bland words at will she thus addressed 
0	hast thou not wondered adam at my stay 
0	thee i have missed and thought it long deprived
0	thy presence agony of love till now
0	not felt nor shall be twice for never more
0	mean i to try what rash untried i sought 
0	the pain of absence from thy sight but strange
0	hath been the cause and wonderful to hear 
0	this tree is not as we are told a tree
0	of danger tasted nor to evil unknown
0	opening the way but of divine effect
0	to open eyes and make them gods who taste 
0	and hath been tasted such the serpent wise 
0	or not restrained as we or not obeying 
0	hath eaten of the fruit and is become 
0	not dead as we are threatened but thenceforth
0	endued with human voice and human sense 
0	reasoning to admiration and with me
0	persuasively hath so prevailed that i
0	have also tasted and have also found
0	the effects to correspond opener mine eyes 
0	dim erst dilated spirits ampler heart 
0	and growing up to godhead which for thee
0	chiefly i sought without thee can despise 
0	for bliss as thou hast part to me is bliss 
0	tedious unshared with thee and odious soon 
0	thou therefore also taste that equal lot
0	may join us equal joy as equal love 
0	lest thou not tasting different degree
0	disjoin us and i then too late renounce
0	deity for thee when fate will not permit 
0	thus eve with countenance blithe her story told 
0	but in her cheek distemper flushing glowed 
0	on the other side adam soon as he heard
0	the fatal trespass done by eve amazed 
0	astonied stood and blank while horrour chill
0	ran through his veins and all his joints relaxed 
0	from his slack hand the garland wreathed for eve
0	down dropt and all the faded roses shed 
0	speechless he stood and pale till thus at length
0	first to himself he inward silence broke 
0	o fairest of creation last and best
0	of all god s works creature in whom excelled
0	whatever can to sight or thought be formed 
0	holy divine good amiable or sweet 
0	how art thou lost how on a sudden lost 
0	defaced deflowered and now to death devote 
0	rather how hast thou yielded to transgress
0	the strict forbiddance how to violate
0	the sacred fruit forbidden some cursed fraud
0	of enemy hath beguiled thee yet unknown 
0	and me with thee hath ruined for with thee
0	certain my resolution is to die 
0	how can i live without thee how forego
0	thy sweet converse and love so dearly joined 
0	to live again in these wild woods forlorn 
0	should god create another eve and i
0	another rib afford yet loss of thee
0	would never from my heart no no i feel
0	the link of nature draw me flesh of flesh 
0	bone of my bone thou art and from thy state
0	mine never shall be parted bliss or woe 
0	so having said as one from sad dismay
0	recomforted and after thoughts disturbed
0	submitting to what seemed remediless 
0	thus in calm mood his words to eve he turned 
0	bold deed thou hast presumed adventurous eve 
0	and peril great provoked who thus hast dared 
0	had it been only coveting to eye
0	that sacred fruit sacred to abstinence 
0	much more to taste it under ban to touch 
0	but past who can recall or done undo 
0	perhaps thou shalt not die perhaps the fact
0	is not so heinous now foretasted fruit 
0	profaned first by the serpent by him first
0	made common and unhallowed ere our taste 
0	nor yet on him found deadly yet he lives 
0	lives as thou saidst and gains to live as man 
0	higher degree of life inducement strong
0	to us as likely tasting to attain
0	proportional ascent which cannot be
0	but to be gods or angels demi gods 
0	nor can i think that god creator wise 
0	though threatening will in earnest so destroy
0	us his prime creatures dignified so high 
0	set over all his works which in our fall 
0	for us created needs with us must fail 
0	dependant made so god shall uncreate 
0	be frustrate do undo and labour lose 
0	not well conceived of god who though his power
0	creation could repeat yet would be loth
0	us to abolish lest the adversary
0	triumph and say fickle their state whom god
0	most favours who can please him long me first
0	he ruined now mankind whom will he next 
0	matter of scorn not to be given the foe 
0	however i with thee have fixed my lot 
0	certain to undergo like doom if death
0	consort with thee death is to me as life 
0	so forcible within my heart i feel
0	the bond of nature draw me to my own 
0	my own in thee for what thou art is mine 
0	our state cannot be severed we are one 
0	one flesh to lose thee were to lose myself 
0	so adam and thus eve to him replied 
0	o glorious trial of exceeding love 
0	illustrious evidence example high 
0	engaging me to emulate but short
0	of thy perfection how shall i attain 
0	adam from whose dear side i boast me sprung 
0	and gladly of our union hear thee speak 
0	one heart one soul in both whereof good proof
0	this day affords declaring thee resolved 
0	rather than death or aught than death more dread 
0	shall separate us linked in love so dear 
0	to undergo with me one guilt one crime 
0	if any be of tasting this fair fruit 
0	whose virtue for of good still good proceeds 
0	direct or by occasion hath presented
0	this happy trial of thy love which else
0	so eminently never had been known 
0	were it i thought death menaced would ensue
0	this my attempt i would sustain alone
0	the worst and not persuade thee rather die
0	deserted than oblige thee with a fact
0	pernicious to thy peace chiefly assured
0	remarkably so late of thy so true 
0	so faithful love unequalled but i feel
0	far otherwise the event not death but life
0	augmented opened eyes new hopes new joys 
0	taste so divine that what of sweet before
0	hath touched my sense flat seems to this and harsh 
0	on my experience adam freely taste 
0	and fear of death deliver to the winds 
0	so saying she embraced him and for joy
0	tenderly wept much won that he his love
0	had so ennobled as of choice to incur
0	divine displeasure for her sake or death 
0	in recompence for such compliance bad
0	such recompence best merits from the bough
0	she gave him of that fair enticing fruit
0	with liberal hand he scrupled not to eat 
0	against his better knowledge not deceived 
0	but fondly overcome with female charm 
0	earth trembled from her entrails as again
0	in pangs and nature gave a second groan 
0	sky loured and muttering thunder some sad drops
0	wept at completing of the mortal sin
0	original while adam took no thought 
0	eating his fill nor eve to iterate
0	her former trespass feared the more to sooth
0	him with her loved society that now 
