0	oppressed them wearied with their amorous play 
0	soon as the force of that fallacious fruit 
0	that with exhilarating vapour bland
0	about their spirits had played and inmost powers
0	made err was now exhaled and grosser sleep 
0	bred of unkindly fumes with conscious dreams
0	incumbered now had left them up they rose
0	as from unrest and each the other viewing 
0	soon found their eyes how opened and their minds
0	how darkened innocence that as a veil
0	had shadowed them from knowing ill was gone 
0	just confidence and native righteousness 
0	and honour from about them naked left
0	to guilty shame he covered but his robe
0	uncovered more so rose the danite strong 
0	herculean samson from the harlot lap
0	of philistean dalilah and waked
0	shorn of his strength they destitute and bare
0	of all their virtue silent and in face
