0	till adam though not less than eve abashed 
0	at length gave utterance to these words constrained 
0	o eve in evil hour thou didst give ear
0	to that false worm of whomsoever taught
0	to counterfeit man s voice true in our fall 
0	false in our promised rising since our eyes
0	opened we find indeed and find we know
0	both good and evil good lost and evil got 
0	bad fruit of knowledge if this be to know 
0	which leaves us naked thus of honour void 
0	of innocence of faith of purity 
0	our wonted ornaments now soiled and stained 
0	and in our faces evident the signs
0	of foul concupiscence whence evil store 
0	even shame the last of evils of the first
0	be sure then how shall i behold the face
0	henceforth of god or angel erst with joy
0	and rapture so oft beheld those heavenly shapes
0	will dazzle now this earthly with their blaze
0	insufferably bright o might i here
0	in solitude live savage in some glade
0	obscured where highest woods impenetrable
0	to star or sun light spread their umbrage broad
0	and brown as evening cover me ye pines 
0	ye cedars with innumerable boughs
0	hide me where i may never see them more 
0	but let us now as in bad plight devise
0	what best may for the present serve to hide
0	the parts of each from other that seem most
0	to shame obnoxious and unseemliest seen 
0	some tree whose broad smooth leaves together sewed 
0	and girded on our loins may cover round
0	those middle parts that this new comer shame 
0	there sit not and reproach us as unclean 
0	so counselled he and both together went
0	into the thickest wood there soon they chose
0	the fig tree not that kind for fruit renowned 
0	but such as at this day to indians known 
0	in malabar or decan spreads her arms
0	branching so broad and long that in the ground
0	the bended twigs take root and daughters grow
0	about the mother tree a pillared shade
0	high over arched and echoing walks between 
0	there oft the indian herdsman shunning heat 
0	shelters in cool and tends his pasturing herds
0	at loop holes cut through thickest shade those leaves
0	they gathered broad as amazonian targe 
0	and with what skill they had together sewed 
0	to gird their waist vain covering if to hide
0	their guilt and dreaded shame o how unlike
0	to that first naked glory such of late
0	columbus found the american so girt
0	with feathered cincture naked else and wild
0	among the trees on isles and woody shores 
0	thus fenced and as they thought their shame in part
0	covered but not at rest or ease of mind 
0	they sat them down to weep nor only tears
0	rained at their eyes but high winds worse within
0	began to rise high passions anger hate 
0	mistrust suspicion discord and shook sore
0	their inward state of mind calm region once
0	and full of peace now tost and turbulent 
0	for understanding ruled not and the will
0	heard not her lore both in subjection now
0	to sensual appetite who from beneath
0	usurping over sovran reason claimed
0	superiour sway from thus distempered breast 
0	adam estranged in look and altered style 
0	speech intermitted thus to eve renewed 
0	would thou hadst hearkened to my words and staid
