0	desire of wandering this unhappy morn 
0	i know not whence possessed thee we had then
0	remained still happy not as now despoiled
0	of all our good shamed naked miserable 
0	let none henceforth seek needless cause to approve
0	the faith they owe when earnestly they seek
0	such proof conclude they then begin to fail 
0	to whom soon moved with touch of blame thus eve 
0	what words have passed thy lips adam severe 
0	imputest thou that to my default or will
0	of wandering as thou callest it which who knows
0	but might as ill have happened thou being by 
0	or to thyself perhaps hadst thou been there 
0	or here the attempt thou couldst not have discerned
0	fraud in the serpent speaking as he spake 
0	no ground of enmity between us known 
0	why he should mean me ill or seek to harm 
0	was i to have never parted from thy side 
0	as good have grown there still a lifeless rib 
0	being as i am why didst not thou the head 
0	command me absolutely not to go 
0	going into such danger as thou saidst 
0	too facile then thou didst not much gainsay 
0	nay didst permit approve and fair dismiss 
0	hadst thou been firm and fixed in thy dissent 
0	neither had i transgressed nor thou with me 
0	to whom then first incensed adam replied 
0	is this the love is this the recompence
0	of mine to thee ingrateful eve expressed
0	immutable when thou wert lost not i 
0	who might have lived and joyed immortal bliss 
0	yet willingly chose rather death with thee 
0	and am i now upbraided as the cause
0	of thy transgressing not enough severe 
0	it seems in thy restraint what could i more
0	i warned thee i admonished thee foretold
0	the danger and the lurking enemy
0	that lay in wait beyond this had been force 
0	and force upon free will hath here no place 
0	but confidence then bore thee on secure
0	either to meet no danger or to find
0	matter of glorious trial and perhaps
0	i also erred in overmuch admiring
0	what seemed in thee so perfect that i thought
0	no evil durst attempt thee but i rue
0	the errour now which is become my crime 
0	and thou the accuser thus it shall befall
0	him who to worth in women overtrusting 
0	lets her will rule restraint she will not brook 
0	and left to herself if evil thence ensue 
0	she first his weak indulgence will accuse 
0	thus they in mutual accusation spent
0	the fruitless hours but neither self condemning 
0	and of their vain contest appeared no end 
0	mean while the heinous and despiteful act
0	of satan done in paradise and how
0	he in the serpent had perverted eve 
0	her husband she to taste the fatal fruit 
0	was known in heaven for what can scape the eye
0	of god all seeing or deceive his heart
0	omniscient who in all things wise and just 
0	hindered not satan to attempt the mind
0	of man with strength entire and free will armed 
0	complete to have discovered and repulsed
0	whatever wiles of foe or seeming friend 
0	for still they knew and ought to have still remembered 
0	the high injunction not to taste that fruit 
0	whoever tempted which they not obeying 
0	 incurred what could they less the penalty 
0	and manifold in sin deserved to fall 
0	up into heaven from paradise in haste
0	the angelick guards ascended mute and sad 
0	for man for of his state by this they knew 
0	much wondering how the subtle fiend had stolen
0	entrance unseen soon as the unwelcome news
0	from earth arrived at heaven gate displeased
0	all were who heard dim sadness did not spare
0	that time celestial visages yet mixed
0	with pity violated not their bliss 
0	about the new arrived in multitudes
0	the ethereal people ran to hear and know
0	how all befel they towards the throne supreme 
0	accountable made haste to make appear 
0	with righteous plea their utmost vigilance
0	and easily approved when the most high
0	eternal father from his secret cloud 
0	amidst in thunder uttered thus his voice 
0	assembled angels and ye powers returned
0	from unsuccessful charge be not dismayed 
0	nor troubled at these tidings from the earth 
0	which your sincerest care could not prevent 
0	foretold so lately what would come to pass 
0	when first this tempter crossed the gulf from hell 
0	i told ye then he should prevail and speed
0	on his bad errand man should be seduced 
0	and flattered out of all believing lies
0	against his maker no decree of mine
0	concurring to necessitate his fall 
0	or touch with lightest moment of impulse
0	his free will to her own inclining left
0	in even scale but fallen he is and now
0	what rests but that the mortal sentence pass
0	on his transgression death denounced that day 
0	which he presumes already vain and void 
0	because not yet inflicted as he feared 
0	by some immediate stroke but soon shall find
0	forbearance no acquittance ere day end 
0	justice shall not return as bounty scorned 
0	but whom send i to judge them whom but thee 
0	vicegerent son to thee i have transferred
0	all judgement whether in heaven or earth or hell 
0	easy it may be seen that i intend
0	mercy colleague with justice sending thee
0	man s friend his mediator his designed
0	both ransom and redeemer voluntary 
0	and destined man himself to judge man fallen 
0	so spake the father and unfolding bright
0	toward the right hand his glory on the son
0	blazed forth unclouded deity he full
0	resplendent all his father manifest
0	expressed and thus divinely answered mild 
0	father eternal thine is to decree 
0	mine both in heaven and earth to do thy will
0	supreme that thou in me thy son beloved 
0	mayest ever rest well pleased i go to judge
0	on earth these thy transgressours but thou knowest 
0	whoever judged the worst on me must light 
0	when time shall be for so i undertook
0	before thee and not repenting this obtain
0	of right that i may mitigate their doom
0	on me derived yet i shall temper so
0	justice with mercy as may illustrate most
0	them fully satisfied and thee appease 
0	attendance none shall need nor train where none
0	are to behold the judgement but the judged 
0	those two the third best absent is condemned 
0	convict by flight and rebel to all law 
0	conviction to the serpent none belongs 
0	thus saying from his radiant seat he rose
0	of high collateral glory him thrones and powers 
0	princedoms and dominations ministrant 
0	accompanied to heaven gate from whence
0	eden and all the coast in prospect lay 
0	down he descended straight the speed of gods
0	time counts not though with swiftest minutes winged 
0	now was the sun in western cadence low
0	from noon and gentle airs due at their hour 
0	to fan the earth now waked and usher in
0	the evening cool when he from wrath more cool 
0	came the mild judge and intercessour both 
0	to sentence man the voice of god they heard
0	now walking in the garden by soft winds
0	brought to their ears while day declined they heard 
0	and from his presence hid themselves among
0	the thickest trees both man and wife till god 
0	approaching thus to adam called aloud 
0	where art thou adam wont with joy to meet
0	my coming seen far off i miss thee here 
0	not pleased thus entertained with solitude 
0	where obvious duty ere while appeared unsought 
0	or come i less conspicuous or what change
0	absents thee or what chance detains come forth 
0	he came and with him eve more loth though first
0	to offend discountenanced both and discomposed 
0	love was not in their looks either to god 
0	or to each other but apparent guilt 
0	and shame and perturbation and despair 
0	anger and obstinacy and hate and guile 
0	whence adam faltering long thus answered brief 
0	i heard thee in the garden and of thy voice
0	afraid being naked hid myself to whom
0	the gracious judge without revile replied 
0	my voice thou oft hast heard and hast not feared 
0	but still rejoiced how is it now become
0	so dreadful to thee that thou art naked who
0	hath told thee hast thou eaten of the tree 
0	whereof i gave thee charge thou shouldst not eat 
0	to whom thus adam sore beset replied 
0	o heaven in evil strait this day i stand
0	before my judge either to undergo
0	myself the total crime or to accuse
0	my other self the partner of my life 
0	whose failing while her faith to me remains 
0	i should conceal and not expose to blame
0	by my complaint but strict necessity
0	subdues me and calamitous constraint 
0	lest on my head both sin and punishment 
0	however insupportable be all
0	devolved though should i hold my peace yet thou
0	wouldst easily detect what i conceal 
0	this woman whom thou madest to be my help 
0	and gavest me as thy perfect gift so good 
0	so fit so acceptable so divine 
0	that from her hand i could suspect no ill 
0	and what she did whatever in itself 
0	her doing seemed to justify the deed 
0	she gave me of the tree and i did eat 
0	to whom the sovran presence thus replied 
0	was she thy god that her thou didst obey
0	before his voice or was she made thy guide 
0	superiour or but equal that to her
0	thou didst resign thy manhood and the place
0	wherein god set thee above her made of thee 
0	and for thee whose perfection far excelled
0	hers in all real dignity adorned
0	she was indeed and lovely to attract
0	thy love not thy subjection and her gifts
0	were such as under government well seemed 
0	unseemly to bear rule which was thy part
0	and person hadst thou known thyself aright 
0	so having said he thus to eve in few 
0	say woman what is this which thou hast done 
0	to whom sad eve with shame nigh overwhelmed 
0	confessing soon yet not before her judge
0	bold or loquacious thus abashed replied 
0	the serpent me beguiled and i did eat 
0	which when the lord god heard without delay
0	to judgement he proceeded on the accused
0	serpent though brute unable to transfer
0	the guilt on him who made him instrument
0	of mischief and polluted from the end
0	of his creation justly then accursed 
0	as vitiated in nature more to know
0	concerned not man since he no further knew 
0	nor altered his offence yet god at last
0	to satan first in sin his doom applied 
0	though in mysterious terms judged as then best 
0	and on the serpent thus his curse let fall 
0	because thou hast done this thou art accursed
0	above all cattle each beast of the field 
0	upon thy belly groveling thou shalt go 
0	and dust shalt eat all the days of thy life 
0	between thee and the woman i will put
0	enmity and between thine and her seed 
0	her seed shall bruise thy head thou bruise his heel 
0	so spake this oracle then verified
0	when jesus son of mary second eve 
0	saw satan fall like lightning down from heaven 
0	prince of the air then rising from his grave
0	spoiled principalities and powers triumphed
0	in open show and with ascension bright 
0	captivity led captive through the air 
0	the realm itself of satan long usurped 
0	whom he shall tread at last under our feet 
0	even he who now foretold his fatal bruise 
0	and to the woman thus his sentence turned 
0	thy sorrow i will greatly multiply
0	by thy conception children thou shalt bring
0	in sorrow forth and to thy husband s will
0	thine shall submit he over thee shall rule 
0	on adam last thus judgement he pronounced 
0	because thou hast hearkened to the voice of thy wife 
0	and eaten of the tree concerning which
0	i charged thee saying thou shalt not eat thereof 
0	cursed is the ground for thy sake thou in sorrow
0	shalt eat thereof all the days of thy life 
0	thorns also and thistles it shall bring thee forth
0	unbid and thou shalt eat the herb of the field 
0	in the sweat of thy face shalt thou eat bread 
0	till thou return unto the ground for thou
0	out of the ground wast taken know thy birth 
0	for dust thou art and shalt to dust return 
0	so judged he man both judge and saviour sent 
0	and the instant stroke of death denounced that day 
0	removed far off then pitying how they stood
0	before him naked to the air that now
0	must suffer change disdained not to begin
0	thenceforth the form of servant to assume 
0	as when he washed his servants feet so now 
0	as father of his family he clad
0	their nakedness with skins of beasts or slain 
0	or as the snake with youthful coat repaid 
0	and thought not much to clothe his enemies 
0	nor he their outward only with the skins
0	of beasts but inward nakedness much more 
0	opprobrious with his robe of righteousness 
0	arraying covered from his father s sight 
0	to him with swift ascent he up returned 
0	into his blissful bosom reassumed
0	in glory as of old to him appeased
0	all though all knowing what had passed with man
0	recounted mixing intercession sweet 
0	mean while ere thus was sinned and judged on earth 
0	within the gates of hell sat sin and death 
0	in counterview within the gates that now
0	stood open wide belching outrageous flame
0	far into chaos since the fiend passed through 
0	sin opening who thus now to death began 
0	o son why sit we here each other viewing
0	idly while satan our great author thrives
0	in other worlds and happier seat provides
0	for us his offspring dear it cannot be
0	but that success attends him if mishap 
0	ere this he had returned with fury driven
0	by his avengers since no place like this
0	can fit his punishment or their revenge 
0	methinks i feel new strength within me rise 
0	wings growing and dominion given me large
0	beyond this deep whatever draws me on 
0	or sympathy or some connatural force 
0	powerful at greatest distance to unite 
0	with secret amity things of like kind 
0	by secretest conveyance thou my shade
0	inseparable must with me along 
0	for death from sin no power can separate 
0	but lest the difficulty of passing back
0	stay his return perhaps over this gulf
0	impassable impervious let us try
0	adventurous work yet to thy power and mine
0	not unagreeable to found a path
0	over this main from hell to that new world 
0	where satan now prevails a monument
0	of merit high to all the infernal host 
0	easing their passage hence for intercourse 
0	or transmigration as their lot shall lead 
0	nor can i miss the way so strongly drawn
0	by this new felt attraction and instinct 
0	whom thus the meager shadow answered soon 
0	go whither fate and inclination strong 
0	leads thee i shall not lag behind nor err
0	the way thou leading such a scent i draw
0	of carnage prey innumerable and taste
0	the savour of death from all things there that live 
0	nor shall i to the work thou enterprisest
0	be wanting but afford thee equal aid 
0	so saying with delight he snuffed the smell
0	of mortal change on earth as when a flock
0	of ravenous fowl though many a league remote 
0	against the day of battle to a field 
0	where armies lie encamped come flying lured
0	with scent of living carcasses designed
0	for death the following day in bloody fight 
0	so scented the grim feature and upturned
0	his nostril wide into the murky air 
0	sagacious of his quarry from so far 
0	then both from out hell gates into the waste
0	wide anarchy of chaos damp and dark 
0	flew diverse and with power their power was great 
0	hovering upon the waters what they met
0	solid or slimy as in raging sea
0	tost up and down together crouded drove 
0	from each side shoaling towards the mouth of hell 
0	as when two polar winds blowing adverse
0	upon the cronian sea together drive
0	mountains of ice that stop the imagined way
0	beyond petsora eastward to the rich
0	cathaian coast the aggregated soil
0	death with his mace petrifick cold and dry 
0	as with a trident smote and fixed as firm
0	as delos floating once the rest his look
0	bound with gorgonian rigour not to move 
0	and with asphaltick slime broad as the gate 
0	deep to the roots of hell the gathered beach
0	they fastened and the mole immense wrought on
0	over the foaming deep high arched a bridge
0	of length prodigious joining to the wall
0	immoveable of this now fenceless world 
0	forfeit to death from hence a passage broad 
0	smooth easy inoffensive down to hell 
0	so if great things to small may be compared 
0	xerxes the liberty of greece to yoke 
0	from susa his memnonian palace high 
0	came to the sea and over hellespont
0	bridging his way europe with asia joined 
0	and scourged with many a stroke the indignant waves 
0	now had they brought the work by wonderous art
0	pontifical a ridge of pendant rock 
0	over the vexed abyss following the track
0	of satan to the self same place where he
0	first lighted from his wing and landed safe
0	from out of chaos to the outside bare
0	of this round world with pins of adamant
0	and chains they made all fast too fast they made
0	and durable and now in little space
0	the confines met of empyrean heaven 
0	and of this world and on the left hand hell
0	with long reach interposed three several ways
0	in sight to each of these three places led 
0	and now their way to earth they had descried 
0	to paradise first tending when behold 
0	satan in likeness of an angel bright 
0	betwixt the centaur and the scorpion steering
0	his zenith while the sun in aries rose 
0	disguised he came but those his children dear
0	their parent soon discerned though in disguise 
0	he after eve seduced unminded slunk
0	into the wood fast by and changing shape 
0	to observe the sequel saw his guileful act
0	by eve though all unweeting seconded
0	upon her husband saw their shame that sought
0	vain covertures but when he saw descend
0	the son of god to judge them terrified
0	he fled not hoping to escape but shun
0	the present fearing guilty what his wrath
0	might suddenly inflict that past returned
0	by night and listening where the hapless pair
0	sat in their sad discourse and various plaint 
0	thence gathered his own doom which understood
0	not instant but of future time with joy
0	and tidings fraught to hell he now returned 
0	and at the brink of chaos near the foot
0	of this new wonderous pontifice unhoped
0	met who to meet him came his offspring dear 
0	great joy was at their meeting and at sight
0	of that stupendous bridge his joy encreased 
0	long he admiring stood till sin his fair
0	enchanting daughter thus the silence broke 
0	o parent these are thy magnifick deeds 
0	thy trophies which thou viewest as not thine own 
0	thou art their author and prime architect 
0	for i no sooner in my heart divined 
0	my heart which by a secret harmony
0	still moves with thine joined in connexion sweet 
0	that thou on earth hadst prospered which thy looks
0	now also evidence but straight i felt 
0	though distant from thee worlds between yet felt 
0	that i must after thee with this thy son 
0	such fatal consequence unites us three 
0	hell could no longer hold us in our bounds 
0	nor this unvoyageable gulf obscure
0	detain from following thy illustrious track 
0	thou hast achieved our liberty confined
0	within hell gates till now thou us impowered
0	to fortify thus far and overlay 
0	with this portentous bridge the dark abyss 
0	thine now is all this world thy virtue hath won
0	what thy hands builded not thy wisdom gained
0	with odds what war hath lost and fully avenged
0	our foil in heaven here thou shalt monarch reign 
0	there didst not there let him still victor sway 
0	as battle hath adjudged from this new world
0	retiring by his own doom alienated 
0	and henceforth monarchy with thee divide
0	of all things parted by the empyreal bounds 
0	his quadrature from thy orbicular world 
0	or try thee now more dangerous to his throne 
0	whom thus the prince of darkness answered glad 
0	fair daughter and thou son and grandchild both 
0	high proof ye now have given to be the race
0	of satan for i glory in the name 
0	antagonist of heaven s almighty king 
0	amply have merited of me of all
0	the infernal empire that so near heaven s door
0	triumphal with triumphal act have met 
0	mine with this glorious work and made one realm 
0	hell and this world one realm one continent
0	of easy thorough fare therefore while i
0	descend through darkness on your road with ease 
0	to my associate powers them to acquaint
0	with these successes and with them rejoice 
0	you two this way among these numerous orbs 
0	all yours right down to paradise descend 
0	there dwell and reign in bliss thence on the earth
0	dominion exercise and in the air 
0	chiefly on man sole lord of all declared 
0	him first make sure your thrall and lastly kill 
0	my substitutes i send ye and create
0	plenipotent on earth of matchless might
0	issuing from me on your joint vigour now
0	my hold of this new kingdom all depends 
0	through sin to death exposed by my exploit 
0	if your joint power prevail the affairs of hell
0	no detriment need fear go and be strong 
0	so saying he dismissed them they with speed
0	their course through thickest constellations held 
0	spreading their bane the blasted stars looked wan 
0	and planets planet struck real eclipse
0	then suffered the other way satan went down
0	the causey to hell gate on either side
0	disparted chaos overbuilt exclaimed 
0	and with rebounding surge the bars assailed 
0	that scorned his indignation through the gate 
0	wide open and unguarded satan passed 
0	and all about found desolate for those 
0	appointed to sit there had left their charge 
0	flown to the upper world the rest were all
0	far to the inland retired about the walls
0	of pandemonium city and proud seat
0	of lucifer so by allusion called
0	of that bright star to satan paragoned 
0	there kept their watch the legions while the grand
0	in council sat solicitous what chance
0	might intercept their emperour sent so he
0	departing gave command and they observed 
0	as when the tartar from his russian foe 
0	by astracan over the snowy plains 
0	retires or bactrin sophi from the horns
0	of turkish crescent leaves all waste beyond
0	the realm of aladule in his retreat
0	to tauris or casbeen so these the late
0	heaven banished host left desart utmost hell
0	many a dark league reduced in careful watch
0	round their metropolis and now expecting
0	each hour their great adventurer from the search
0	of foreign worlds he through the midst unmarked 
0	in show plebeian angel militant
0	of lowest order passed and from the door
0	of that plutonian hall invisible
0	ascended his high throne which under state
0	of richest texture spread at the upper end
0	was placed in regal lustre down a while
0	he sat and round about him saw unseen 
0	at last as from a cloud his fulgent head
0	and shape star bright appeared or brighter clad
0	with what permissive glory since his fall
0	was left him or false glitter all amazed
0	at that so sudden blaze the stygian throng
0	bent their aspect and whom they wished beheld 
0	their mighty chief returned loud was the acclaim 
0	forth rushed in haste the great consulting peers 
0	raised from their dark divan and with like joy
0	congratulant approached him who with hand
0	silence and with these words attention won 
0	for in possession such not only of right 
0	i call ye and declare ye now returned
0	successful beyond hope to lead ye forth
0	triumphant out of this infernal pit
0	abominable accursed the house of woe 
0	and dungeon of our tyrant now possess 
0	as lords a spacious world to our native heaven
0	little inferiour by my adventure hard
0	with peril great achieved long were to tell
0	what i have done what suffered with what pain
0	voyaged th unreal vast unbounded deep
0	of horrible confusion over which
0	by sin and death a broad way now is paved 
0	to expedite your glorious march but i
0	toiled out my uncouth passage forced to ride
0	the untractable abyss plunged in the womb
0	of unoriginal night and chaos wild 
0	that jealous of their secrets fiercely opposed
0	my journey strange with clamorous uproar
0	protesting fate supreme thence how i found
0	the new created world which fame in heaven
0	long had foretold a fabrick wonderful
0	of absolute perfection therein man
0	placed in a paradise by our exile
0	made happy him by fraud i have seduced
0	from his creator and the more to encrease
0	your wonder with an apple he thereat
0	offended worth your laughter hath given up
0	both his beloved man and all his world 
0	to sin and death a prey and so to us 
0	without our hazard labour or alarm 
0	to range in and to dwell and over man
0	to rule as over all he should have ruled 
0	true is me also he hath judged or rather
0	me not but the brute serpent in whose shape
0	man i deceived that which to me belongs 
0	is enmity which he will put between
0	me and mankind i am to bruise his heel 
0	his seed when is not set shall bruise my head 
0	a world who would not purchase with a bruise 
0	or much more grievous pain ye have the account
0	of my performance what remains ye gods 
0	but up and enter now into full bliss 
0	so having said a while he stood expecting
0	their universal shout and high applause 
0	to fill his ear when contrary he hears
0	on all sides from innumerable tongues 
0	a dismal universal hiss the sound
0	of publick scorn he wondered but not long
0	had leisure wondering at himself now more 
0	his visage drawn he felt to sharp and spare 
0	his arms clung to his ribs his legs entwining
0	each other till supplanted down he fell
0	a monstrous serpent on his belly prone 
0	reluctant but in vain a greater power
0	now ruled him punished in the shape he sinned 
0	according to his doom he would have spoke 
0	but hiss for hiss returned with forked tongue
0	to forked tongue for now were all transformed
0	alike to serpents all as accessories
0	to his bold riot dreadful was the din
0	of hissing through the hall thick swarming now
0	with complicated monsters head and tail 
0	scorpion and asp and amphisbaena dire 
0	cerastes horned hydrus and elops drear 
0	and dipsas not so thick swarmed once the soil
0	bedropt with blood of gorgon or the isle
0	ophiusa but still greatest he the midst 
0	now dragon grown larger than whom the sun
0	ingendered in the pythian vale or slime 
0	huge python and his power no less he seemed
0	above the rest still to retain they all
0	him followed issuing forth to the open field 
0	where all yet left of that revolted rout 
0	heaven fallen in station stood or just array 
0	sublime with expectation when to see
0	in triumph issuing forth their glorious chief 
0	they saw but other sight instead a croud
0	of ugly serpents horrour on them fell 
0	and horrid sympathy for what they saw 
0	they felt themselves now changing down their arms 
0	down fell both spear and shield down they as fast 
0	and the dire hiss renewed and the dire form
0	catched by contagion like in punishment 
0	as in their crime thus was the applause they meant 
0	turned to exploding hiss triumph to shame
0	cast on themselves from their own mouths there stood
0	a grove hard by sprung up with this their change 
0	his will who reigns above to aggravate
0	their penance laden with fair fruit like that
0	which grew in paradise the bait of eve
0	used by the tempter on that prospect strange
0	their earnest eyes they fixed imagining
0	for one forbidden tree a multitude
0	now risen to work them further woe or shame 
0	yet parched with scalding thirst and hunger fierce 
0	though to delude them sent could not abstain 
0	but on they rolled in heaps and up the trees
0	climbing sat thicker than the snaky locks
0	that curled megaera greedily they plucked
0	the fruitage fair to sight like that which grew
0	near that bituminous lake where sodom flamed 
0	this more delusive not the touch but taste
0	deceived they fondly thinking to allay
0	their appetite with gust instead of fruit
0	chewed bitter ashes which the offended taste
0	with spattering noise rejected oft they assayed 
0	hunger and thirst constraining drugged as oft 
0	with hatefullest disrelish writhed their jaws 
0	with soot and cinders filled so oft they fell
0	into the same illusion not as man
0	whom they triumphed once lapsed thus were they plagued
0	and worn with famine long and ceaseless hiss 
0	till their lost shape permitted they resumed 
0	yearly enjoined some say to undergo 
0	this annual humbling certain numbered days 
0	to dash their pride and joy for man seduced 
0	however some tradition they dispersed
0	among the heathen of their purchase got 
0	and fabled how the serpent whom they called
0	ophion with eurynome the wide 
0	encroaching eve perhaps had first the rule
0	of high olympus thence by saturn driven
0	and ops ere yet dictaean jove was born 
0	mean while in paradise the hellish pair
0	too soon arrived sin there in power before 
0	once actual now in body and to dwell
0	habitual habitant behind her death 
0	close following pace for pace not mounted yet
0	on his pale horse to whom sin thus began 
0	second of satan sprung all conquering death 
0	what thinkest thou of our empire now though earned
0	with travel difficult not better far
0	than still at hell s dark threshold to have sat watch 
0	unnamed undreaded and thyself half starved 
0	whom thus the sin born monster answered soon 
0	to me who with eternal famine pine 
0	there best where most with ravine i may meet 
0	which here though plenteous all too little seems
0	to stuff this maw this vast unhide bound corps 
0	to whom the incestuous mother thus replied 
0	thou therefore on these herbs and fruits and flowers 
0	feed first on each beast next and fish and fowl 
0	no homely morsels and whatever thing
0	the sithe of time mows down devour unspared 
0	till i in man residing through the race 
0	his thoughts his looks words actions all infect 
0	and season him thy last and sweetest prey 
0	this said they both betook them several ways 
0	both to destroy or unimmortal make
0	all kinds and for destruction to mature
0	sooner or later which the almighty seeing 
0	from his transcendent seat the saints among 
0	to those bright orders uttered thus his voice 
0	see with what heat these dogs of hell advance
0	to waste and havock yonder world which i
0	so fair and good created and had still
0	kept in that state had not the folly of man
0	let in these wasteful furies who impute
0	folly to me so doth the prince of hell
0	and his adherents that with so much ease
0	i suffer them to enter and possess
0	a place so heavenly and conniving seem
0	to gratify my scornful enemies 
0	that laugh as if transported with some fit
0	of passion i to them had quitted all 
0	at random yielded up to their misrule 
0	and know not that i called and drew them thither 
0	my hell hounds to lick up the draff and filth
0	which man s polluting sin with taint hath shed
0	on what was pure til crammed and gorged nigh burst
0	with sucked and glutted offal at one sling
0	of thy victorious arm well pleasing son 
0	both sin and death and yawning grave at last 
0	through chaos hurled obstruct the mouth of hell
0	for ever and seal up his ravenous jaws 
0	then heaven and earth renewed shall be made pure
0	to sanctity that shall receive no stain 
0	till then the curse pronounced on both precedes 
0	he ended and the heavenly audience loud
0	sung halleluiah as the sound of seas 
0	through multitude that sung just are thy ways 
0	righteous are thy decrees on all thy works 
0	who can extenuate thee next to the son 
0	destined restorer of mankind by whom
0	new heaven and earth shall to the ages rise 
0	or down from heaven descend such was their song 
0	while the creator calling forth by name
0	his mighty angels gave them several charge 
0	as sorted best with present things the sun
0	had first his precept so to move so shine 
0	as might affect the earth with cold and heat
0	scarce tolerable and from the north to call
0	decrepit winter from the south to bring
0	solstitial summer s heat to the blanc moon
0	her office they prescribed to the other five
0	their planetary motions and aspects 
0	in sextile square and trine and opposite 
0	of noxious efficacy and when to join
0	in synod unbenign and taught the fixed
0	their influence malignant when to shower 
0	which of them rising with the sun or falling 
0	should prove tempestuous to the winds they set
0	their corners when with bluster to confound
0	sea air and shore the thunder when to roll
0	with terrour through the dark aereal hall 
0	some say he bid his angels turn ascanse
0	the poles of earth twice ten degrees and more 
0	from the sun s axle they with labour pushed
0	oblique the centrick globe some say the sun
0	was bid turn reins from the equinoctial road
0	like distant breadth to taurus with the seven
0	up to the tropick crab thence down amain
0	as deep as capricorn to bring in change
0	of seasons to each clime else had the spring
0	perpetual smiled on earth with vernant flowers 
0	equal in days and nights except to those
0	beyond the polar circles to them day
0	had unbenighted shone while the low sun 
0	to recompense his distance in their sight
0	had rounded still the horizon and not known
0	or east or west which had forbid the snow
0	from cold estotiland and south as far
0	beneath magellan at that tasted fruit
0	the sun as from thyestean banquet turned
0	his course intended else how had the world
0	inhabited though sinless more than now 
0	avoided pinching cold and scorching heat 
0	these changes in the heavens though slow produced
0	like change on sea and land sideral blast 
0	vapour and mist and exhalation hot 
0	corrupt and pestilent now from the north
0	of norumbega and the samoed shore 
0	bursting their brazen dungeon armed with ice 
0	and snow and hail and stormy gust and flaw 
0	boreas and caecias and argestes loud 
0	and thrascias rend the woods and seas upturn 
0	with adverse blast upturns them from the south
0	notus and afer black with thunderous clouds
0	from serraliona thwart of these as fierce 
0	forth rush the levant and the ponent winds 
0	eurus and zephyr with their lateral noise 
0	sirocco and libecchio thus began
0	outrage from lifeless things but discord first 
0	daughter of sin among the irrational
0	death introduced through fierce antipathy 
0	beast now with beast gan war and fowl with fowl 
0	and fish with fish to graze the herb all leaving 
0	devoured each other nor stood much in awe
0	of man but fled him or with countenance grim 
0	glared on him passing these were from without
0	the growing miseries which adam saw
0	already in part though hid in gloomiest shade 
0	to sorrow abandoned but worse felt within 
0	and in a troubled sea of passion tost 
0	thus to disburden sought with sad complaint 
0	o miserable of happy is this the end
0	of this new glorious world and me so late
0	the glory of that glory who now become
0	accursed of blessed hide me from the face
0	of god whom to behold was then my highth
0	of happiness yet well if here would end
0	the misery i deserved it and would bear
0	my own deservings but this will not serve 
0	all that i eat or drink or shall beget 
0	is propagated curse o voice once heard
0	delightfully encrease and multiply 
0	now death to hear for what can i encrease 
0	or multiply but curses on my head 
0	who of all ages to succeed but feeling
0	the evil on him brought by me will curse
0	my head ill fare our ancestor impure 
0	for this we may thank adam but his thanks
0	shall be the execration so besides
0	mine own that bide upon me all from me
0	shall with a fierce reflux on me rebound 
0	on me as on their natural center light
0	heavy though in their place o fleeting joys
0	of paradise dear bought with lasting woes 
0	did i request thee maker from my clay
0	to mould me man did i solicit thee
0	from darkness to promote me or here place
0	in this delicious garden as my will
0	concurred not to my being it were but right
0	and equal to reduce me to my dust 
0	desirous to resign and render back
0	all i received unable to perform
0	thy terms too hard by which i was to hold
0	the good i sought not to the loss of that 
0	sufficient penalty why hast thou added
0	the sense of endless woes inexplicable
0	thy justice seems yet to say truth too late
0	i thus contest then should have been refused
0	those terms whatever when they were proposed 
0	thou didst accept them wilt thou enjoy the good 
0	then cavil the conditions and though god
0	made thee without thy leave what if thy son
0	prove disobedient and reproved retort 
0	 wherefore didst thou beget me i sought it not 
0	wouldst thou admit for his contempt of thee
0	that proud excuse yet him not thy election 
0	but natural necessity begot 
0	god made thee of choice his own and of his own
0	to serve him thy reward was of his grace 
0	thy punishment then justly is at his will 
0	be it so for i submit his doom is fair 
0	that dust i am and shall to dust return 
0	o welcome hour whenever why delays
0	his hand to execute what his decree
0	fixed on this day why do i overlive 
0	why am i mocked with death and lengthened out
0	to deathless pain how gladly would i meet
0	mortality my sentence and be earth
0	insensible how glad would lay me down
0	as in my mother s lap there i should rest 
0	and sleep secure his dreadful voice no more
0	would thunder in my ears no fear of worse
0	to me and to my offspring would torment me
0	with cruel expectation yet one doubt
0	pursues me still lest all i cannot die 
0	lest that pure breath of life the spirit of man
0	which god inspired cannot together perish
0	with this corporeal clod then in the grave 
0	or in some other dismal place who knows
0	but i shall die a living death o thought
0	horrid if true yet why it was but breath
0	of life that sinned what dies but what had life
0	and sin the body properly had neither 
0	all of me then shall die let this appease
0	the doubt since human reach no further knows 
0	for though the lord of all be infinite 
0	is his wrath also be it man is not so 
0	but mortal doomed how can he exercise
0	wrath without end on man whom death must end 
0	can he make deathless death that were to make
0	strange contradiction which to god himself
0	impossible is held as argument
0	of weakness not of power will he draw out 
0	for anger s sake finite to infinite 
0	in punished man to satisfy his rigour 
0	satisfied never that were to extend
0	his sentence beyond dust and nature s law 
0	by which all causes else according still
0	to the reception of their matter act 
0	not to the extent of their own sphere but say
0	that death be not one stroke as i supposed 
0	bereaving sense but endless misery
0	from this day onward which i feel begun
0	both in me and without me and so last
0	to perpetuity ay me that fear
0	comes thundering back with dreadful revolution
0	on my defenceless head both death and i
0	am found eternal and incorporate both 
0	nor i on my part single in me all
0	posterity stands cursed fair patrimony
0	that i must leave ye sons o were i able
0	to waste it all myself and leave ye none 
0	so disinherited how would you bless
0	me now your curse ah why should all mankind 
0	for one man s fault thus guiltless be condemned 
0	it guiltless but from me what can proceed 
0	but all corrupt both mind and will depraved
0	not to do only but to will the same
0	with me how can they then acquitted stand
0	in sight of god him after all disputes 
0	forced i absolve all my evasions vain 
0	and reasonings though through mazes lead me still
0	but to my own conviction first and last
0	on me me only as the source and spring
0	of all corruption all the blame lights due 
0	so might the wrath fond wish couldst thou support
0	that burden heavier than the earth to bear 
0	than all the world much heavier though divided
0	with that bad woman thus what thou desirest 
0	and what thou fearest alike destroys all hope
0	of refuge and concludes thee miserable
0	beyond all past example and future 
0	to satan only like both crime and doom 
0	o conscience into what abyss of fears
0	and horrours hast thou driven me out of which
0	i find no way from deep to deeper plunged 
0	thus adam to himself lamented loud 
0	through the still night not now as ere man fell 
0	wholesome and cool and mild but with black air
0	accompanied with damps and dreadful gloom 
0	which to his evil conscience represented
0	all things with double terrour on the ground
0	outstretched he lay on the cold ground and oft
0	cursed his creation death as oft accused
0	the day of his offence why comes not death 
0	said he with one thrice acceptable stroke
0	to end me shall truth fail to keep her word 
0	justice divine not hasten to be just 
0	but death comes not at call justice divine
0	mends not her slowest pace for prayers or cries 
0	o woods o fountains hillocks dales and bowers 
0	with other echo late i taught your shades
0	to answer and resound far other song 
0	whom thus afflicted when sad eve beheld 
0	desolate where she sat approaching nigh 
0	soft words to his fierce passion she assayed 
0	but her with stern regard he thus repelled 
0	out of my sight thou serpent that name best
0	befits thee with him leagued thyself as false
0	and hateful nothing wants but that thy shape 
0	like his and colour serpentine may show
0	thy inward fraud to warn all creatures from thee
0	henceforth lest that too heavenly form pretended
0	to hellish falshood snare them but for thee
0	i had persisted happy had not thy pride
0	and wandering vanity when least was safe 
0	rejected my forewarning and disdained
0	not to be trusted longing to be seen 
0	though by the devil himself him overweening
0	to over reach but with the serpent meeting 
0	fooled and beguiled by him thou i by thee
0	to trust thee from my side imagined wise 
0	constant mature proof against all assaults 
0	and understood not all was but a show 
0	rather than solid virtue all but a rib
0	crooked by nature bent as now appears 
0	more to the part sinister from me drawn 
0	well if thrown out as supernumerary
0	to my just number found o why did god 
0	creator wise that peopled highest heaven
0	with spirits masculine create at last
0	this novelty on earth this fair defect
0	of nature and not fill the world at once
0	with men as angels without feminine 
0	or find some other way to generate
0	mankind this mischief had not been befallen 
0	and more that shall befall innumerable
0	disturbances on earth through female snares 
0	and strait conjunction with this sex for either
0	he never shall find out fit mate but such
0	as some misfortune brings him or mistake 
0	or whom he wishes most shall seldom gain
0	through her perverseness but shall see her gained
0	by a far worse or if she love withheld
0	by parents or his happiest choice too late
0	shall meet already linked and wedlock bound
0	to a fell adversary his hate or shame 
0	which infinite calamity shall cause
0	to human life and houshold peace confound 
0	he added not and from her turned but eve 
0	not so repulsed with tears that ceased not flowing
0	and tresses all disordered at his feet
0	fell humble and embracing them besought
