0	forsake me not thus adam witness heaven
0	what love sincere and reverence in my heart
0	i bear thee and unweeting have offended 
0	unhappily deceived thy suppliant
0	i beg and clasp thy knees bereave me not 
0	whereon i live thy gentle looks thy aid 
0	thy counsel in this uttermost distress 
0	my only strength and stay forlorn of thee 
0	whither shall i betake me where subsist 
0	while yet we live scarce one short hour perhaps 
0	between us two let there be peace both joining 
0	as joined in injuries one enmity
0	against a foe by doom express assigned us 
0	that cruel serpent on me exercise not
0	thy hatred for this misery befallen 
0	on me already lost me than thyself
0	more miserable both have sinned but thou
0	against god only i against god and thee 
0	and to the place of judgement will return 
0	there with my cries importune heaven that all
0	the sentence from thy head removed may light
0	on me sole cause to thee of all this woe 
0	me me only just object of his ire 
0	she ended weeping and her lowly plight 
0	immoveable till peace obtained from fault
0	acknowledged and deplored in adam wrought
0	commiseration soon his heart relented
0	towards her his life so late and sole delight 
0	now at his feet submissive in distress 
0	creature so fair his reconcilement seeking 
0	his counsel whom she had displeased his aid 
0	as one disarmed his anger all he lost 
0	and thus with peaceful words upraised her soon 
0	unwary and too desirous as before 
0	so now of what thou knowest not who desirest
0	the punishment all on thyself alas 
0	bear thine own first ill able to sustain
0	his full wrath whose thou feelest as yet least part 
0	and my displeasure bearest so ill if prayers
0	could alter high decrees i to that place
