0	that on my head all might be visited 
0	thy frailty and infirmer sex forgiven 
0	to me committed and by me exposed 
0	but rise let us no more contend nor blame
0	each other blamed enough elsewhere but strive
0	in offices of love how we may lighten
0	each other s burden in our share of woe 
0	since this day s death denounced if aught i see 
0	will prove no sudden but a slow paced evil 
0	a long day s dying to augment our pain 
0	and to our seed o hapless seed derived 
0	to whom thus eve recovering heart replied 
0	adam by sad experiment i know
0	how little weight my words with thee can find 
0	found so erroneous thence by just event
0	found so unfortunate nevertheless 
0	restored by thee vile as i am to place
0	of new acceptance hopeful to regain
0	thy love the sole contentment of my heart
0	living or dying from thee i will not hide
0	what thoughts in my unquiet breast are risen 
0	tending to some relief of our extremes 
0	or end though sharp and sad yet tolerable 
0	as in our evils and of easier choice 
0	if care of our descent perplex us most 
0	which must be born to certain woe devoured
0	by death at last and miserable it is
0	to be to others cause of misery 
0	our own begotten and of our loins to bring
0	into this cursed world a woeful race 
0	that after wretched life must be at last
0	food for so foul a monster in thy power
0	it lies yet ere conception to prevent
0	the race unblest to being yet unbegot 
0	childless thou art childless remain so death
0	shall be deceived his glut and with us two
0	be forced to satisfy his ravenous maw 
0	but if thou judge it hard and difficult 
0	conversing looking loving to abstain
0	from love s due rights nuptial embraces sweet 
0	and with desire to languish without hope 
0	before the present object languishing
0	with like desire which would be misery
0	and torment less than none of what we dread 
0	then both ourselves and seed at once to free
0	from what we fear for both let us make short 
0	let us seek death or he not found supply
0	with our own hands his office on ourselves 
0	why stand we longer shivering under fears 
0	that show no end but death and have the power 
0	of many ways to die the shortest choosing 
0	destruction with destruction to destroy 
0	she ended here or vehement despair
0	broke off the rest so much of death her thoughts
0	had entertained as dyed her cheeks with pale 
0	but adam with such counsel nothing swayed 
0	to better hopes his more attentive mind
0	labouring had raised and thus to eve replied 
0	eve thy contempt of life and pleasure seems
0	to argue in thee something more sublime
0	and excellent than what thy mind contemns 
0	but self destruction therefore sought refutes
0	that excellence thought in thee and implies 
0	not thy contempt but anguish and regret
0	for loss of life and pleasure overloved 
0	or if thou covet death as utmost end
0	of misery so thinking to evade
0	the penalty pronounced doubt not but god
0	hath wiselier armed his vengeful ire than so
0	to be forestalled much more i fear lest death 
0	so snatched will not exempt us from the pain
0	we are by doom to pay rather such acts
0	of contumacy will provoke the highest
0	to make death in us live then let us seek
0	some safer resolution which methinks
0	i have in view calling to mind with heed
0	part of our sentence that thy seed shall bruise
0	the serpent s head piteous amends unless
0	be meant whom i conjecture our grand foe 
0	satan who in the serpent hath contrived
0	against us this deceit to crush his head
0	would be revenge indeed which will be lost
0	by death brought on ourselves or childless days
0	resolved as thou proposest so our foe
0	shal scape his punishment ordained and we
0	instead shall double ours upon our heads 
0	no more be mentioned then of violence
0	against ourselves and wilful barrenness 
0	that cuts us off from hope and savours only
