0	repairing where he judged them prostrate fell
0	before him reverent and both confessed
0	humbly their faults and pardon begged with tears
0	watering the ground and with their sighs the air
0	frequenting sent from hearts contrite in sign
0	of sorrow unfeigned and humiliation meek 
0	thus they in lowliest plight repentant stood
0	praying for from the mercy seat above
0	prevenient grace descending had removed
0	the stony from their hearts and made new flesh
0	regenerate grow instead that sighs now breathed
0	unutterable which the spirit of prayer
0	inspired and winged for heaven with speedier flight
0	than loudest oratory yet their port
0	not of mean suitors nor important less
0	seemed their petition than when the ancient pair
