0	by their great intercessour came in sight
0	before the father s throne them the glad son
0	presenting thus to intercede began 
0	see father what first fruits on earth are sprung
0	from thy implanted grace in man these sighs
0	and prayers which in this golden censer mixed
0	with incense i thy priest before thee bring 
0	fruits of more pleasing savour from thy seed
0	sown with contrition in his heart than those
0	which his own hand manuring all the trees
0	of paradise could have produced ere fallen
0	from innocence now therefore bend thine ear
0	to supplication hear his sighs though mute 
0	unskilful with what words to pray let me
