0	and propitiation all his works on me 
0	good or not good ingraft my merit those
0	shall perfect and for these my death shall pay 
0	accept me and in me from these receive
0	the smell of peace toward mankind let him live
0	before thee reconciled at least his days
0	numbered though sad till death his doom which i
0	to mitigate thus plead not to reverse 
0	to better life shall yield him where with me
0	all my redeemed may dwell in joy and bliss 
0	made one with me as i with thee am one 
0	to whom the father without cloud serene 
0	all thy request for man accepted son 
0	obtain all thy request was my decree 
0	but longer in that paradise to dwell 
0	the law i gave to nature him forbids 
0	those pure immortal elements that know 
0	no gross no unharmonious mixture foul 
0	eject him tainted now and purge him off 
0	as a distemper gross to air as gross 
0	and mortal food as may dispose him best
0	for dissolution wrought by sin that first
0	distempered all things and of incorrupt
0	corrupted i at first with two fair gifts
0	created him endowed with happiness 
