0	which then not minded in dismay yet now
0	assures me that the bitterness of death
0	is past and we shall live whence hail to thee 
0	eve rightly called mother of all mankind 
0	mother of all things living since by thee
0	man is to live and all things live for man 
0	to whom thus eve with sad demeanour meek 
0	ill worthy i such title should belong
0	to me transgressour who for thee ordained
0	a help became thy snare to me reproach
0	rather belongs distrust and all dispraise 
