0	how shall i part and whither wander down
0	into a lower world to this obscure
0	and wild how shall we breathe in other air
0	less pure accustomed to immortal fruits 
0	whom thus the angel interrupted mild 
0	lament not eve but patiently resign
0	what justly thou hast lost nor set thy heart 
0	thus over fond on that which is not thine 
0	thy going is not lonely with thee goes
0	thy husband whom to follow thou art bound 
0	where he abides think there thy native soil 
0	adam by this from the cold sudden damp
0	recovering and his scattered spirits returned 
0	to michael thus his humble words addressed 
0	celestial whether among the thrones or named
0	of them the highest for such of shape may seem
0	prince above princes gently hast thou told
0	thy message which might else in telling wound 
0	and in performing end us what besides
0	of sorrow and dejection and despair 
0	our frailty can sustain thy tidings bring 
0	departure from this happy place our sweet
0	recess and only consolation left
0	familiar to our eyes all places else
0	inhospitable appear and desolate 
0	nor knowing us nor known and if by prayer
0	incessant i could hope to change the will
0	of him who all things can i would not cease
0	to weary him with my assiduous cries 
0	but prayer against his absolute decree
0	no more avails than breath against the wind 
0	blown stifling back on him that breathes it forth 
0	therefore to his great bidding i submit 
0	this most afflicts me that departing hence 
0	as from his face i shall be hid deprived
0	his blessed countenance here i could frequent
0	with worship place by place where he vouchsafed
0	presence divine and to my sons relate 
0	on this mount he appeared under this tree
0	stood visible among these pines his voice
0	i heard here with him at this fountain talked 
0	so many grateful altars i would rear
0	of grassy turf and pile up every stone
0	of lustre from the brook in memory 
0	or monument to ages and theron
0	offer sweet smelling gums and fruits and flowers 
0	in yonder nether world where shall i seek
0	his bright appearances or foot step trace 
0	for though i fled him angry yet recalled
0	to life prolonged and promised race i now
0	gladly behold though but his utmost skirts
0	of glory and far off his steps adore 
0	to whom thus michael with regard benign 
0	adam thou knowest heaven his and all the earth 
0	not this rock only his omnipresence fills
0	land sea and air and every kind that lives 
0	fomented by his virtual power and warmed 
0	all the earth he gave thee to possess and rule 
0	no despicable gift surmise not then
0	his presence to these narrow bounds confined
0	of paradise or eden this had been
0	perhaps thy capital seat from whence had spread
0	all generations and had hither come
0	from all the ends of the earth to celebrate
0	and reverence thee their great progenitor 
0	but this pre eminence thou hast lost brought down
0	to dwell on even ground now with thy sons 
0	yet doubt not but in valley and in plain 
0	god is as here and will be found alike
0	present and of his presence many a sign
0	still following thee still compassing thee round
0	with goodness and paternal love his face
0	express and of his steps the track divine 
0	which that thou mayest believe and be confirmed
0	ere thou from hence depart know i am sent
0	to show thee what shall come in future days
0	to thee and to thy offspring good with bad
0	expect to hear supernal grace contending
0	with sinfulness of men thereby to learn
0	true patience and to temper joy with fear
0	and pious sorrow equally inured
0	by moderation either state to bear 
0	prosperous or adverse so shalt thou lead
0	safest thy life and best prepared endure
0	thy mortal passage when it comes ascend
0	this hill let eve for i have drenched her eyes 
0	here sleep below while thou to foresight wakest 
0	as once thou sleptst while she to life was formed 
0	to whom thus adam gratefully replied 
0	ascend i follow thee safe guide the path
0	thou leadest me and to the hand of heaven submit 
0	however chastening to the evil turn
0	my obvious breast arming to overcome
0	by suffering and earn rest from labour won 
0	if so i may attain so both ascend
0	in the visions of god it was a hill 
0	of paradise the highest from whose top
0	the hemisphere of earth in clearest ken 
0	stretched out to the amplest reach of prospect lay 
0	not higher that hill nor wider looking round 
0	whereon for different cause the tempter set
0	our second adam in the wilderness 
0	to show him all earth s kingdoms and their glory 
0	his eye might there command wherever stood
0	city of old or modern fame the seat
0	of mightiest empire from the destined walls
0	of cambalu seat of cathaian can 
0	and samarchand by oxus temir s throne 
0	to paquin of sinaean kings and thence
0	to agra and lahor of great mogul 
0	down to the golden chersonese or where
0	the persian in ecbatan sat or since
0	in hispahan or where the russian ksar
0	turchestan born nor could his eye not ken
0	the empire of negus to his utmost port
0	ercoco and the less maritim kings
0	and sofala thought ophir to the realm
0	of congo and angola farthest south 
0	or thence from niger flood to atlas mount
0	the kingdoms of almansor fez and sus 
0	on europe thence and where rome was to sway
0	the world in spirit perhaps he also saw
0	rich mexico the seat of montezume 
0	and cusco in peru the richer seat
0	of atabalipa and yet unspoiled
0	guiana whose great city geryon s sons
0	call el dorado but to nobler sights
0	michael from adam s eyes the film removed 
0	which that false fruit that promised clearer sight
0	had bred then purged with euphrasy and rue
0	the visual nerve for he had much to see 
0	and from the well of life three drops instilled 
0	so deep the power of these ingredients pierced 
0	even to the inmost seat of mental sight 
0	that adam now enforced to close his eyes 
0	sunk down and all his spirits became entranced 
0	but him the gentle angel by the hand
0	soon raised and his attention thus recalled 
0	adam now ope thine eyes and first behold
0	the effects which thy original crime hath wrought
0	in some to spring from thee who never touched
0	the excepted tree nor with the snake conspired 
0	nor sinned thy sin yet from that sin derive
0	corruption to bring forth more violent deeds 
0	his eyes he opened and beheld a field 
0	part arable and tilth whereon were sheaves
0	new reaped the other part sheep walks and folds 
0	i the midst an altar as the land mark stood 
0	rustick of grassy sord thither anon
0	a sweaty reaper from his tillage brought
0	first fruits the green ear and the yellow sheaf 
0	unculled as came to hand a shepherd next 
0	more meek came with the firstlings of his flock 
0	choicest and best then sacrificing laid
0	the inwards and their fat with incense strowed 
0	on the cleft wood and all due rights performed 
0	his offering soon propitious fire from heaven
0	consumed with nimble glance and grateful steam 
0	the other s not for his was not sincere 
0	whereat he inly raged and as they talked 
0	smote him into the midriff with a stone
0	that beat out life he fell and deadly pale 
0	groaned out his soul with gushing blood effused 
0	much at that sight was adam in his heart
0	dismayed and thus in haste to the angel cried 
0	o teacher some great mischief hath befallen
0	to that meek man who well had sacrificed 
0	is piety thus and pure devotion paid 
0	to whom michael thus he also moved replied 
0	these two are brethren adam and to come
0	out of thy loins the unjust the just hath slain 
0	for envy that his brother s offering found
0	from heaven acceptance but the bloody fact
0	will be avenged and the other s faith approved 
0	lose no reward though here thou see him die 
0	rolling in dust and gore to which our sire 
0	alas both for the deed and for the cause 
0	but have i now seen death is this the way
0	i must return to native dust o sight
0	of terrour foul and ugly to behold 
0	horrid to think how horrible to feel 
0	to whom thus michael death thou hast seen
0	in his first shape on man but many shapes
0	of death and many are the ways that lead
0	to his grim cave all dismal yet to sense
0	more terrible at the entrance than within 
0	some as thou sawest by violent stroke shall die 
0	by fire flood famine by intemperance more
0	in meats and drinks which on the earth shall bring
0	diseases dire of which a monstrous crew
0	before thee shall appear that thou mayest know
0	what misery the inabstinence of eve
0	shall bring on men immediately a place
0	before his eyes appeared sad noisome dark 
0	a lazar house it seemed wherein were laid
0	numbers of all diseased all maladies
0	of ghastly spasm or racking torture qualms
0	of heart sick agony all feverous kinds 
0	convulsions epilepsies fierce catarrhs 
0	intestine stone and ulcer colick pangs 
0	demoniack phrenzy moaping melancholy 
0	and moon struck madness pining atrophy 
0	marasmus and wide wasting pestilence 
0	dropsies and asthmas and joint racking rheums 
0	dire was the tossing deep the groans despair
0	tended the sick busiest from couch to couch 
0	and over them triumphant death his dart
0	shook but delayed to strike though oft invoked
0	with vows as their chief good and final hope 
0	sight so deform what heart of rock could long
0	dry eyed behold adam could not but wept 
0	though not of woman born compassion quelled
0	his best of man and gave him up to tears
0	a space till firmer thoughts restrained excess 
0	and scarce recovering words his plaint renewed 
0	o miserable mankind to what fall
0	degraded to what wretched state reserved 
0	better end here unborn why is life given
0	to be thus wrested from us rather why
0	obtruded on us thus who if we knew
0	what we receive would either no accept
0	life offered or soon beg to lay it down 
0	glad to be so dismissed in peace can thus
0	the image of god in man created once
0	so goodly and erect though faulty since 
0	to such unsightly sufferings be debased
0	under inhuman pains why should not man 
0	retaining still divine similitude
0	in part from such deformities be free 
0	and for his maker s image sake exempt 
0	their maker s image answered michael then
0	forsook them when themselves they vilified
0	to serve ungoverned appetite and took
0	his image whom they served a brutish vice 
0	inductive mainly to the sin of eve 
0	therefore so abject is their punishment 
0	disfiguring not god s likeness but their own 
0	or if his likeness by themselves defaced 
0	while they pervert pure nature s healthful rules
0	to loathsome sickness worthily since they
0	god s image did not reverence in themselves 
0	i yield it just said adam and submit 
0	but is there yet no other way besides
0	these painful passages how we may come
0	to death and mix with our connatural dust 
0	there is said michael if thou well observe
0	the rule of not too much by temperance taught 
0	in what thou eatest and drinkest seeking from thence
0	due nourishment not gluttonous delight 
0	till many years over thy head return 
0	so mayest thou live till like ripe fruit thou drop
0	into thy mother s lap or be with ease
0	gathered nor harshly plucked for death mature 
0	this is old age but then thou must outlive
0	thy youth thy strength thy beauty which will change
0	to withered weak and gray thy senses then 
0	obtuse all taste of pleasure must forego 
0	to what thou hast and for the air of youth 
0	hopeful and cheerful in thy blood will reign
0	a melancholy damp of cold and dry
0	to weigh thy spirits down and last consume
0	the balm of life to whom our ancestor 
0	henceforth i fly not death nor would prolong
0	life much bent rather how i may be quit 
0	fairest and easiest of this cumbrous charge 
0	which i must keep till my appointed day
0	of rendering up and patiently attend
0	my dissolution michael replied 
0	nor love thy life nor hate but what thou livest
0	live well how long or short permit to heaven 
0	and now prepare thee for another sight 
0	he looked and saw a spacious plain whereon
0	were tents of various hue by some were herds
0	of cattle grazing others whence the sound
0	of instruments that made melodious chime 
0	was heard of harp and organ and who moved
0	their stops and chords was seen his volant touch 
0	instinct through all proportions low and high 
0	fled and pursued transverse the resonant fugue 
0	in other part stood one who at the forge
0	labouring two massy clods of iron and brass
0	had melted whether found where casual fire
0	had wasted woods on mountain or in vale 
0	down to the veins of earth thence gliding hot
0	to some cave s mouth or whether washed by stream
0	from underground the liquid ore he drained
0	into fit moulds prepared from which he formed
0	first his own tools then what might else be wrought
0	fusil or graven in metal after these 
0	but on the hither side a different sort
0	from the high neighbouring hills which was their seat 
0	down to the plain descended by their guise
0	just men they seemed and all their study bent
0	to worship god aright and know his works
0	not hid nor those things last which might preserve
0	freedom and peace to men they on the plain
0	long had not walked when from the tents behold 
0	a bevy of fair women richly gay
0	in gems and wanton dress to the harp they sung
0	soft amorous ditties and in dance came on 
0	the men though grave eyed them and let their eyes
0	rove without rein till in the amorous net
0	fast caught they liked and each his liking chose 
0	and now of love they treat till the evening star 
0	love s harbinger appeared then all in heat
0	they light the nuptial torch and bid invoke
0	hymen then first to marriage rites invoked 
0	with feast and musick all the tents resound 
0	such happy interview and fair event
0	of love and youth not lost songs garlands flowers 
0	and charming symphonies attached the heart
0	of adam soon inclined to admit delight 
0	the bent of nature which he thus expressed 
0	true opener of mine eyes prime angel blest 
0	much better seems this vision and more hope
0	of peaceful days portends than those two past 
0	those were of hate and death or pain much worse 
0	here nature seems fulfilled in all her ends 
0	to whom thus michael judge not what is best
0	by pleasure though to nature seeming meet 
0	created as thou art to nobler end
0	holy and pure conformity divine 
0	those tents thou sawest so pleasant were the tents
0	of wickedness wherein shall dwell his race
0	who slew his brother studious they appear
0	of arts that polish life inventers rare 
0	unmindful of their maker though his spirit
0	taught them but they his gifts acknowledged none 
0	yet they a beauteous offspring shall beget 
0	for that fair female troop thou sawest that seemed
0	of goddesses so blithe so smooth so gay 
0	yet empty of all good wherein consists
0	woman s domestick honour and chief praise 
0	bred only and completed to the taste
0	of lustful appetence to sing to dance 
0	to dress and troll the tongue and roll the eye 
0	to these that sober race of men whose lives
0	religious titled them the sons of god 
0	shall yield up all their virtue all their fame
0	ignobly to the trains and to the smiles
0	of these fair atheists and now swim in joy 
0	erelong to swim at large and laugh for which
0	the world erelong a world of tears must weep 
0	to whom thus adam of short joy bereft 
0	o pity and shame that they who to live well
0	entered so fair should turn aside to tread
0	paths indirect or in the mid way faint 
0	but still i see the tenour of man s woe
0	holds on the same from woman to begin 
0	from man s effeminate slackness it begins 
0	said the angel who should better hold his place
0	by wisdom and superiour gifts received 
0	but now prepare thee for another scene 
0	he looked and saw wide territory spread
0	before him towns and rural works between 
0	cities of men with lofty gates and towers 
0	concourse in arms fierce faces threatening war 
0	giants of mighty bone and bold emprise 
0	part wield their arms part curb the foaming steed 
0	single or in array of battle ranged
0	both horse and foot nor idly mustering stood 
0	one way a band select from forage drives
0	a herd of beeves fair oxen and fair kine 
0	from a fat meadow ground or fleecy flock 
0	ewes and their bleating lambs over the plain 
0	their booty scarce with life the shepherds fly 
0	but call in aid which makes a bloody fray 
0	with cruel tournament the squadrons join 
0	where cattle pastured late now scattered lies
0	with carcasses and arms the ensanguined field 
0	deserted others to a city strong
0	lay siege encamped by battery scale and mine 
0	assaulting others from the wall defend
0	with dart and javelin stones and sulphurous fire 
0	on each hand slaughter and gigantick deeds 
0	in other part the sceptered heralds call
0	to council in the city gates anon
0	gray headed men and grave with warriours mixed 
0	assemble and harangues are heard but soon 
0	in factious opposition till at last 
0	of middle age one rising eminent
0	in wise deport spake much of right and wrong 
0	of justice or religion truth and peace 
0	and judgement from above him old and young
0	exploded and had seized with violent hands 
0	had not a cloud descending snatched him thence
0	unseen amid the throng so violence
0	proceeded and oppression and sword law 
0	through all the plain and refuge none was found 
0	adam was all in tears and to his guide
0	lamenting turned full sad o what are these 
0	death s ministers not men who thus deal death
0	inhumanly to men and multiply
0	ten thousandfold the sin of him who slew
0	his brother for of whom such massacre
0	make they but of their brethren men of men
0	but who was that just man whom had not heaven
0	rescued had in his righteousness been lost 
0	to whom thus michael these are the product
0	of those ill mated marriages thou sawest 
0	where good with bad were matched who of themselves
0	abhor to join and by imprudence mixed 
0	produce prodigious births of body or mind 
0	such were these giants men of high renown 
0	for in those days might only shall be admired 
0	and valour and heroick virtue called 
0	to overcome in battle and subdue
0	nations and bring home spoils with infinite
0	man slaughter shall be held the highest pitch
0	of human glory and for glory done
0	of triumph to be styled great conquerours
0	patrons of mankind gods and sons of gods 
0	destroyers rightlier called and plagues of men 
0	thus fame shall be achieved renown on earth 
0	and what most merits fame in silence hid 
0	but he the seventh from thee whom thou beheldst
0	the only righteous in a world preverse 
0	and therefore hated therefore so beset
0	with foes for daring single to be just 
0	and utter odious truth that god would come
0	to judge them with his saints him the most high
0	rapt in a balmy cloud with winged steeds
0	did as thou sawest receive to walk with god
0	high in salvation and the climes of bliss 
0	exempt from death to show thee what reward
0	awaits the good the rest what punishment 
0	which now direct thine eyes and soon behold 
0	he looked and saw the face of things quite changed 
0	the brazen throat of war had ceased to roar 
0	all now was turned to jollity and game 
0	to luxury and riot feast and dance 
0	marrying or prostituting as befel 
0	rape or adultery where passing fair
0	allured them thence from cups to civil broils 
0	at length a reverend sire among them came 
0	and of their doings great dislike declared 
0	and testified against their ways he oft
0	frequented their assemblies whereso met 
0	triumphs or festivals and to them preached
0	conversion and repentance as to souls
0	in prison under judgements imminent 
0	but all in vain which when he saw he ceased
0	contending and removed his tents far off 
0	then from the mountain hewing timber tall 
0	began to build a vessel of huge bulk 
0	measured by cubit length and breadth and highth 
0	smeared round with pitch and in the side a door
0	contrived and of provisions laid in large 
0	for man and beast when lo a wonder strange 
0	of every beast and bird and insect small 
0	came sevens and pairs and entered in as taught
0	their order last the sire and his three sons 
0	with their four wives and god made fast the door 
0	mean while the south wind rose and with black wings
0	wide hovering all the clouds together drove
0	from under heaven the hills to their supply
0	vapour and exhalation dusk and moist 
0	sent up amain and now the thickened sky
0	like a dark ceiling stood down rushed the rain
0	impetuous and continued till the earth
0	no more was seen the floating vessel swum
0	uplifted and secure with beaked prow
0	rode tilting o er the waves all dwellings else
0	flood overwhelmed and them with all their pomp
0	deep under water rolled sea covered sea 
0	sea without shore and in their palaces 
0	where luxury late reigned sea monsters whelped
0	and stabled of mankind so numerous late 
0	all left in one small bottom swum imbarked 
0	how didst thou grieve then adam to behold
0	the end of all thy offspring end so sad 
0	depopulation thee another flood 
0	of tears and sorrow a flood thee also drowned 
0	and sunk thee as thy sons till gently reared
0	by the angel on thy feet thou stoodest at last 
0	though comfortless as when a father mourns
0	his children all in view destroyed at once 
0	and scarce to the angel utter dst thus thy plaint 
0	o visions ill foreseen better had i
0	lived ignorant of future so had borne
0	my part of evil only each day s lot
0	enough to bear those now that were dispensed
0	the burden of many ages on me light
0	at once by my foreknowledge gaining birth
0	abortive to torment me ere their being 
0	with thought that they must be let no man seek
0	henceforth to be foretold what shall befall
0	him or his children evil he may be sure 
0	which neither his foreknowing can prevent 
0	and he the future evil shall no less
0	in apprehension than in substance feel 
0	grievous to bear but that care now is past 
0	man is not whom to warn those few escaped
0	famine and anguish will at last consume 
0	wandering that watery desart i had hope 
0	when violence was ceased and war on earth 
0	all would have then gone well peace would have crowned
0	with length of happy days the race of man 
0	but i was far deceived for now i see
0	peace to corrupt no less than war to waste 
0	how comes it thus unfold celestial guide 
0	and whether here the race of man will end 
0	to whom thus michael those whom last thou sawest
0	in triumph and luxurious wealth are they
0	first seen in acts of prowess eminent
0	and great exploits but of true virtue void 
0	who having spilt much blood and done much wast
0	subduing nations and achieved thereby
0	fame in the world high titles and rich prey 
0	shall change their course to pleasure ease and sloth 
0	surfeit and lust till wantonness and pride
0	raise out of friendship hostile deeds in peace 
0	the conquered also and enslaved by war 
0	shall with their freedom lost all virtue lose
0	and fear of god from whom their piety feigned
0	in sharp contest of battle found no aid
0	against invaders therefore cooled in zeal 
0	thenceforth shall practice how to live secure 
0	worldly or dissolute on what their lords
0	shall leave them to enjoy for the earth shall bear
0	more than enough that temperance may be tried 
0	so all shall turn degenerate all depraved 
0	justice and temperance truth and faith forgot 
0	one man except the only son of light
0	in a dark age against example good 
0	against allurement custom and a world
0	offended fearless of reproach and scorn 
0	or violence he of their wicked ways
0	shall them admonish and before them set
0	the paths of righteousness how much more safe
0	and full of peace denouncing wrath to come
0	on their impenitence and shall return
0	of them derided but of god observed
0	the one just man alive by his command
0	shall build a wonderous ark as thou beheldst 
0	to save himself and houshold from amidst
0	a world devote to universal wrack 
0	no sooner he with them of man and beast
0	select for life shall in the ark be lodged 
0	and sheltered round but all the cataracts
0	of heaven set open on the earth shall pour
0	rain day and night all fountains of the deep 
0	broke up shall heave the ocean to usurp
0	beyond all bounds till inundation rise
0	above the highest hills then shall this mount
0	of paradise by might of waves be moved
0	out of his place pushed by the horned flood 
0	with all his verdure spoiled and trees adrift 
0	down the great river to the opening gulf 
0	and there take root an island salt and bare 
0	the haunt of seals and orcs and sea mews clang 
0	to teach thee that god attributes to place
0	no sanctity if none be thither brought
0	by men who there frequent or therein dwell 
0	and now what further shall ensue behold 
0	he looked and saw the ark hull on the flood 
0	which now abated for the clouds were fled 
0	driven by a keen north wind that blowing dry 
0	wrinkled the face of deluge as decayed 
0	and the clear sun on his wide watery glass
0	gazed hot and of the fresh wave largely drew 
0	as after thirst which made their flowing shrink
0	from standing lake to tripping ebb that stole
0	with soft foot towards the deep who now had stopt
0	his sluces as the heaven his windows shut 
0	the ark no more now floats but seems on ground 
0	fast on the top of some high mountain fixed 
0	and now the tops of hills as rocks appear 
0	with clamour thence the rapid currents drive 
0	towards the retreating sea their furious tide 
0	forthwith from out the ark a raven flies 
0	and after him the surer messenger 
0	a dove sent forth once and again to spy
0	green tree or ground whereon his foot may light 
0	the second time returning in his bill
0	an olive leaf he brings pacifick sign 
0	anon dry ground appears and from his ark
0	the ancient sire descends with all his train 
0	then with uplifted hands and eyes devout 
0	grateful to heaven over his head beholds
0	a dewy cloud and in the cloud a bow
0	conspicuous with three lifted colours gay 
0	betokening peace from god and covenant new 
0	whereat the heart of adam erst so sad 
0	greatly rejoiced and thus his joy broke forth 
0	o thou who future things canst represent
0	as present heavenly instructer i revive
0	at this last sight assured that man shall live 
0	with all the creatures and their seed preserve 
0	far less i now lament for one whole world
0	of wicked sons destroyed than i rejoice
0	for one man found so perfect and so just 
0	that god vouchsafes to raise another world
0	from him and all his anger to forget 
0	but say what mean those coloured streaks in heaven
0	distended as the brow of god appeased 
0	or serve they as a flowery verge to bind
0	the fluid skirts of that same watery cloud 
0	lest it again dissolve and shower the earth 
0	to whom the arch angel dextrously thou aimest 
0	so willingly doth god remit his ire 
0	though late repenting him of man depraved 
0	grieved at his heart when looking down he saw
0	the whole earth filled with violence and all flesh
0	corrupting each their way yet those removed 
0	such grace shall one just man find in his sight 
0	that he relents not to blot out mankind 
0	and makes a covenant never to destroy
0	the earth again by flood nor let the sea
0	surpass his bounds nor rain to drown the world 
0	with man therein or beast but when he brings
0	over the earth a cloud will therein set
0	his triple coloured bow whereon to look 
0	and call to mind his covenant day and night 
0	seed time and harvest heat and hoary frost 
0	shall hold their course till fire purge all things new 
0	both heaven and earth wherein the just shall dwell 
0	as one who in his journey bates at noon 
0	though bent on speed so here the arch angel paused
0	betwixt the world destroyed and world restored 
0	if adam aught perhaps might interpose 
0	then with transition sweet new speech resumes 
0	thus thou hast seen one world begin and end 
0	and man as from a second stock proceed 
0	much thou hast yet to see but i perceive
0	thy mortal sight to fail objects divine
0	must needs impair and weary human sense 
0	henceforth what is to come i will relate 
0	thou therefore give due audience and attend 
0	this second source of men while yet but few 
0	and while the dread of judgement past remains
0	fresh in their minds fearing the deity 
0	with some regard to what is just and right
0	shall lead their lives and multiply apace 
0	labouring the soil and reaping plenteous crop 
0	corn wine and oil and from the herd or flock 
0	oft sacrificing bullock lamb or kid 
0	with large wine offerings poured and sacred feast 
0	shall spend their days in joy unblamed and dwell
0	long time in peace by families and tribes 
0	under paternal rule till one shall rise
0	of proud ambitious heart who not content
0	with fair equality fraternal state 
0	will arrogate dominion undeserved
0	over his brethren and quite dispossess
0	concord and law of nature from the earth 
0	hunting and men not beasts shall be his game 
0	with war and hostile snare such as refuse
0	subjection to his empire tyrannous 
0	a mighty hunter thence he shall be styled
0	before the lord as in despite of heaven 
0	or from heaven claiming second sovranty 
0	and from rebellion shall derive his name 
0	though of rebellion others he accuse 
0	he with a crew whom like ambition joins
0	with him or under him to tyrannize 
0	marching from eden towards the west shall find
0	the plain wherein a black bituminous gurge
0	boils out from under ground the mouth of hell 
0	of brick and of that stuff they cast to build
0	a city and tower whose top may reach to heaven 
0	and get themselves a name lest far dispersed
0	in foreign lands their memory be lost 
0	regardless whether good or evil fame 
0	but god who oft descends to visit men
0	unseen and through their habitations walks
0	to mark their doings them beholding soon 
0	comes down to see their city ere the tower
0	obstruct heaven towers and in derision sets
0	upon their tongues a various spirit to rase
0	quite out their native language and instead 
0	to sow a jangling noise of words unknown 
0	forthwith a hideous gabble rises loud 
0	among the builders each to other calls
0	not understood till hoarse and all in rage 
0	as mocked they storm great laughter was in heaven 
0	and looking down to see the hubbub strange 
0	and hear the din thus was the building left
0	ridiculous and the work confusion named 
0	whereto thus adam fatherly displeased 
0	o execrable son so to aspire
0	above his brethren to himself assuming
0	authority usurped from god not given 
0	he gave us only over beast fish fowl 
0	dominion absolute that right we hold
0	by his donation but man over men
0	he made not lord such title to himself
0	reserving human left from human free 
0	but this usurper his encroachment proud
0	stays not on man to god his tower intends
0	siege and defiance wretched man what food
0	will he convey up thither to sustain
0	himself and his rash army where thin air
0	above the clouds will pine his entrails gross 
0	and famish him of breath if not of bread 
0	to whom thus michael justly thou abhorrest
0	that son who on the quiet state of men
0	such trouble brought affecting to subdue
0	rational liberty yet know withal 
0	since thy original lapse true liberty
0	is lost which always with right reason dwells
0	twinned and from her hath no dividual being 
0	reason in man obscured or not obeyed 
0	immediately inordinate desires 
0	and upstart passions catch the government
0	from reason and to servitude reduce
0	man till then free therefore since he permits
0	within himself unworthy powers to reign
0	over free reason god in judgement just 
0	subjects him from without to violent lords 
0	who oft as undeservedly enthrall
0	his outward freedom tyranny must be 
0	though to the tyrant thereby no excuse 
0	yet sometimes nations will decline so low
0	from virtue which is reason that no wrong 
0	but justice and some fatal curse annexed 
0	deprives them of their outward liberty 
0	their inward lost witness the irreverent son
0	of him who built the ark who for the shame
0	done to his father heard this heavy curse 
0	servant of servants on his vicious race 
0	thus will this latter as the former world 
0	still tend from bad to worse till god at last 
0	wearied with their iniquities withdraw
0	his presence from among them and avert
0	his holy eyes resolving from thenceforth
0	to leave them to their own polluted ways 
0	and one peculiar nation to select
0	from all the rest of whom to be invoked 
0	a nation from one faithful man to spring 
0	him on this side euphrates yet residing 
0	bred up in idol worship o that men
0	 canst thou believe should be so stupid grown 
0	while yet the patriarch lived who scaped the flood 
0	as to forsake the living god and fall
0	to worship their own work in wood and stone
0	for gods yet him god the most high vouchsafes
0	to call by vision from his father s house 
0	his kindred and false gods into a land
0	which he will show him and from him will raise
0	a mighty nation and upon him shower
0	his benediction so that in his seed
0	all nations shall be blest he straight obeys 
0	not knowing to what land yet firm believes 
0	i see him but thou canst not with what faith
0	he leaves his gods his friends and native soil 
0	ur of chaldaea passing now the ford
0	to haran after him a cumbrous train
0	of herds and flocks and numerous servitude 
0	not wandering poor but trusting all his wealth
0	with god who called him in a land unknown 
0	canaan he now attains i see his tents
0	pitched about sechem and the neighbouring plain
0	of moreh there by promise he receives
0	gift to his progeny of all that land 
0	from hameth northward to the desart south 
0	 things by their names i call though yet unnamed 
0	from hermon east to the great western sea 
0	mount hermon yonder sea each place behold
0	in prospect as i point them on the shore
0	mount carmel here the double founted stream 
0	jordan true limit eastward but his sons
0	shall dwell to senir that long ridge of hills 
0	this ponder that all nations of the earth
0	shall in his seed be blessed by that seed
0	is meant thy great deliverer who shall bruise
0	the serpent s head whereof to thee anon
0	plainlier shall be revealed this patriarch blest 
0	whom faithful abraham due time shall call 
0	a son and of his son a grand child leaves 
0	like him in faith in wisdom and renown 
0	the grandchild with twelve sons increased departs
0	from canaan to a land hereafter called
0	see where it flows disgorging at seven mouths
0	into the sea to sojourn in that land
0	he comes invited by a younger son
0	in time of dearth a son whose worthy deeds
0	raise him to be the second in that realm
0	of pharaoh there he dies and leaves his race
0	growing into a nation and now grown
0	suspected to a sequent king who seeks
0	to stop their overgrowth as inmate guests
0	too numerous whence of guests he makes them slaves
0	inhospitably and kills their infant males 
0	till by two brethren these two brethren call
0	moses and aaron sent from god to claim
0	his people from enthralment they return 
0	with glory and spoil back to their promised land 
0	but first the lawless tyrant who denies
0	to know their god or message to regard 
0	must be compelled by signs and judgements dire 
0	to blood unshed the rivers must be turned 
0	frogs lice and flies must all his palace fill
0	with loathed intrusion and fill all the land 
0	his cattle must of rot and murren die 
0	botches and blains must all his flesh emboss 
0	and all his people thunder mixed with hail 
0	and wheel on the earth devouring where it rolls 
0	what it devours not herb or fruit or grain 
0	a darksome cloud of locusts swarming down
0	must eat and on the ground leave nothing green 
0	darkness must overshadow all his bounds 
0	palpable darkness and blot out three days 
0	last with one midnight stroke all the first born
0	the river dragon tamed at length submits
0	to let his sojourners depart and oft
0	humbles his stubborn heart but still as ice
0	more hardened after thaw till in his rage
0	pursuing whom he late dismissed the sea
0	swallows him with his host but them lets pass 
0	as on dry land between two crystal walls 
0	awed by the rod of moses so to stand
0	divided till his rescued gain their shore 
0	such wondrous power god to his saint will lend 
0	though present in his angel who shall go
0	before them in a cloud and pillar of fire 
0	by day a cloud by night a pillar of fire 
0	to guide them in their journey and remove
0	behind them while the obdurate king pursues 
0	all night he will pursue but his approach
0	darkness defends between till morning watch 
0	then through the fiery pillar and the cloud 
0	god looking forth will trouble all his host 
0	and craze their chariot wheels when by command
0	moses once more his potent rod extends
0	over the sea the sea his rod obeys 
0	on their embattled ranks the waves return 
0	and overwhelm their war the race elect
0	safe toward canaan from the shore advance
0	through the wild desart not the readiest way 
0	lest entering on the canaanite alarmed 
0	war terrify them inexpert and fear
0	inglorious life with servitude for life
0	to noble and ignoble is more sweet
0	untrained in arms where rashness leads not on 
0	this also shall they gain by their delay
0	in the wide wilderness there they shall found
0	their government and their great senate choose
0	through the twelve tribes to rule by laws ordained 
0	god from the mount of sinai whose gray top
0	shall tremble he descending will himself
0	in thunder lightning and loud trumpets sound 
0	ordain them laws part such as appertain
0	to civil justice part religious rites
0	of sacrifice informing them by types
0	and shadows of that destined seed to bruise
0	the serpent by what means he shall achieve
0	mankind s deliverance but the voice of god
0	to mortal ear is dreadful they beseech
0	that moses might report to them his will 
0	and terrour cease he grants what they besought 
0	instructed that to god is no access
0	without mediator whose high office now
0	moses in figure bears to introduce
0	one greater of whose day he shall foretel 
0	and all the prophets in their age the times
0	of great messiah shall sing thus laws and rites
0	established such delight hath god in men
0	obedient to his will that he vouchsafes
0	among them to set up his tabernacle 
0	the holy one with mortal men to dwell 
0	by his prescript a sanctuary is framed
0	of cedar overlaid with gold therein
0	an ark and in the ark his testimony 
0	the records of his covenant over these
0	a mercy seat of gold between the wings
0	of two bright cherubim before him burn
0	seven lamps as in a zodiack representing
0	the heavenly fires over the tent a cloud
0	shall rest by day a fiery gleam by night 
0	save when they journey and at length they come 
0	conducted by his angel to the land
0	promised to abraham and his seed the rest
0	were long to tell how many battles fought
0	how many kings destroyed and kingdoms won 
0	or how the sun shall in mid heaven stand still
0	a day entire and night s due course adjourn 
0	man s voice commanding sun in gibeon stand 
0	and thou moon in the vale of aialon 
0	till israel overcome so call the third
0	from abraham son of isaac and from him
0	his whole descent who thus shall canaan win 
0	here adam interposed o sent from heaven 
0	enlightener of my darkness gracious things
0	thou hast revealed those chiefly which concern
0	just abraham and his seed now first i find
0	mine eyes true opening and my heart much eased 
0	erewhile perplexed with thoughts what would become
0	of me and all mankind but now i see
0	his day in whom all nations shall be blest 
0	favour unmerited by me who sought
0	forbidden knowledge by forbidden means 
0	this yet i apprehend not why to those
0	among whom god will deign to dwell on earth
0	so many and so various laws are given 
0	so many laws argue so many sins
0	among them how can god with such reside 
0	to whom thus michael doubt not but that sin
0	will reign among them as of thee begot 
0	and therefore was law given them to evince
0	their natural pravity by stirring up
0	sin against law to fight that when they see
0	law can discover sin but not remove 
0	save by those shadowy expiations weak 
0	the blood of bulls and goats they may conclude
0	some blood more precious must be paid for man 
0	just for unjust that in such righteousness
0	to them by faith imputed they may find
0	justification towards god and peace
0	of conscience which the law by ceremonies
0	cannot appease nor man the mortal part
0	perform and not performing cannot live 
0	so law appears imperfect and but given
0	with purpose to resign them in full time 
0	up to a better covenant disciplined
0	from shadowy types to truth from flesh to spirit 
0	from imposition of strict laws to free
0	acceptance of large grace from servile fear
0	to filial works of law to works of faith 
0	and therefore shall not moses though of god
0	highly beloved being but the minister
0	of law his people into canaan lead 
0	but joshua whom the gentiles jesus call 
0	his name and office bearing who shall quell
0	the adversary serpent and bring back
0	through the world s wilderness long wandered man
0	safe to eternal paradise of rest 
0	mean while they in their earthly canaan placed 
0	long time shall dwell and prosper but when sins
0	national interrupt their publick peace 
0	provoking god to raise them enemies 
0	from whom as oft he saves them penitent
0	by judges first then under kings of whom
0	the second both for piety renowned
0	and puissant deeds a promise shall receive
0	irrevocable that his regal throne
0	for ever shall endure the like shall sing
0	all prophecy that of the royal stock
0	of david so i name this king shall rise
0	a son the woman s seed to thee foretold 
0	foretold to abraham as in whom shall trust
0	all nations and to kings foretold of kings
0	the last for of his reign shall be no end 
0	but first a long succession must ensue 
0	and his next son for wealth and wisdom famed 
0	the clouded ark of god till then in tents
0	wandering shall in a glorious temple enshrine 
0	such follow him as shall be registered
0	part good part bad of bad the longer scroll 
0	whose foul idolatries and other faults
0	heaped to the popular sum will so incense
0	god as to leave them and expose their land 
0	their city his temple and his holy ark 
0	with all his sacred things a scorn and prey
0	to that proud city whose high walls thou sawest
0	left in confusion babylon thence called 
0	there in captivity he lets them dwell
0	the space of seventy years then brings them back 
0	remembering mercy and his covenant sworn
0	to david stablished as the days of heaven 
0	returned from babylon by leave of kings
0	their lords whom god disposed the house of god
0	they first re edify and for a while
0	in mean estate live moderate till grown
0	in wealth and multitude factious they grow 
0	but first among the priests dissention springs 
0	men who attend the altar and should most
0	endeavour peace their strife pollution brings
0	upon the temple itself at last they seise
0	the scepter and regard not david s sons 
0	then lose it to a stranger that the true
0	anointed king messiah might be born
0	barred of his right yet at his birth a star 
0	unseen before in heaven proclaims him come 
0	and guides the eastern sages who inquire
0	his place to offer incense myrrh and gold 
0	his place of birth a solemn angel tells
0	to simple shepherds keeping watch by night 
0	they gladly thither haste and by a quire
0	of squadroned angels hear his carol sung 
0	a virgin is his mother but his sire
0	the power of the most high he shall ascend
0	the throne hereditary and bound his reign
0	with earth s wide bounds his glory with the heavens 
0	he ceased discerning adam with such joy
0	surcharged as had like grief been dewed in tears 
0	without the vent of words which these he breathed 
0	o prophet of glad tidings finisher
0	of utmost hope now clear i understand
0	what oft my steadiest thoughts have searched in vain 
0	why our great expectation should be called
0	the seed of woman virgin mother hail 
0	high in the love of heaven yet from my loins
0	thou shalt proceed and from thy womb the son
0	of god most high so god with man unites 
0	needs must the serpent now his capital bruise
0	expect with mortal pain say where and when
0	their fight what stroke shall bruise the victor s heel 
0	to whom thus michael dream not of their fight 
0	as of a duel or the local wounds
0	of head or heel not therefore joins the son
0	manhood to godhead with more strength to foil
0	thy enemy nor so is overcome
0	satan whose fall from heaven a deadlier bruise 
0	disabled not to give thee thy death s wound 
0	which he who comes thy saviour shall recure 
0	not by destroying satan but his works
0	in thee and in thy seed nor can this be 
0	but by fulfilling that which thou didst want 
0	obedience to the law of god imposed
0	on penalty of death and suffering death 
0	the penalty to thy transgression due 
0	and due to theirs which out of thine will grow 
0	so only can high justice rest appaid 
0	the law of god exact he shall fulfil
0	both by obedience and by love though love
0	alone fulfil the law thy punishment
0	he shall endure by coming in the flesh
0	to a reproachful life and cursed death 
0	proclaiming life to all who shall believe
0	in his redemption and that his obedience 
0	imputed becomes theirs by faith his merits
0	to save them not their own though legal works 
0	for this he shall live hated be blasphemed 
0	seised on by force judged and to death condemned
0	a shameful and accursed nailed to the cross
0	by his own nation slain for bringing life 
0	but to the cross he nails thy enemies 
0	the law that is against thee and the sins
0	of all mankind with him there crucified 
0	never to hurt them more who rightly trust
0	in this his satisfaction so he dies 
0	but soon revives death over him no power
0	shall long usurp ere the third dawning light
0	return the stars of morn shall see him rise
0	out of his grave fresh as the dawning light 
0	thy ransom paid which man from death redeems 
0	his death for man as many as offered life
0	neglect not and the benefit embrace
0	by faith not void of works this god like act
0	annuls thy doom the death thou shouldest have died 
0	in sin for ever lost from life this act
0	shall bruise the head of satan crush his strength 
0	defeating sin and death his two main arms 
0	and fix far deeper in his head their stings
0	than temporal death shall bruise the victor s heel 
0	or theirs whom he redeems a death like sleep 
0	a gentle wafting to immortal life 
0	nor after resurrection shall he stay
0	longer on earth than certain times to appear
0	to his disciples men who in his life
0	still followed him to them shall leave in charge
0	to teach all nations what of him they learned
0	and his salvation them who shall believe
0	baptizing in the profluent stream the sign
0	of washing them from guilt of sin to life
0	pure and in mind prepared if so befall 
0	for death like that which the redeemer died 
0	all nations they shall teach for from that day 
0	not only to the sons of abraham s loins
0	salvation shall be preached but to the sons
0	of abraham s faith wherever through the world 
0	so in his seed all nations shall be blest 
0	then to the heaven of heavens he shall ascend
0	with victory triumphing through the air
0	over his foes and thine there shall surprise
0	the serpent prince of air and drag in chains
0	through all his realm and there confounded leave 
0	then enter into glory and resume
0	his seat at god s right hand exalted high
0	above all names in heaven and thence shall come 
0	when this world s dissolution shall be ripe 
0	with glory and power to judge both quick and dead 
0	to judge the unfaithful dead but to reward
0	his faithful and receive them into bliss 
0	whether in heaven or earth for then the earth
0	shall all be paradise far happier place
0	than this of eden and far happier days 
0	so spake the arch angel michael then paused 
0	as at the world s great period and our sire 
0	replete with joy and wonder thus replied 
0	o goodness infinite goodness immense 
0	that all this good of evil shall produce 
0	and evil turn to good more wonderful
0	than that which by creation first brought forth
0	light out of darkness full of doubt i stand 
0	whether i should repent me now of sin
0	by me done and occasioned or rejoice
0	much more that much more good thereof shall spring 
0	to god more glory more good will to men
0	from god and over wrath grace shall abound 
0	but say if our deliverer up to heaven
0	must re ascend what will betide the few
0	his faithful left among the unfaithful herd 
0	the enemies of truth who then shall guide
0	his people who defend will they not deal
0	worse with his followers than with him they dealt 
0	be sure they will said the angel but from heaven
0	he to his own a comforter will send 
0	the promise of the father who shall dwell
0	his spirit within them and the law of faith 
0	working through love upon their hearts shall write 
0	to guide them in all truth and also arm
0	with spiritual armour able to resist
0	satan s assaults and quench his fiery darts 
0	what man can do against them not afraid 
0	though to the death against such cruelties
0	with inward consolations recompensed 
0	and oft supported so as shall amaze
0	their proudest persecutors for the spirit 
0	poured first on his apostles whom he sends
0	to evangelize the nations then on all
0	baptized shall them with wonderous gifts endue
0	to speak all tongues and do all miracles 
0	as did their lord before them thus they win
0	great numbers of each nation to receive
0	with joy the tidings brought from heaven at length
0	their ministry performed and race well run 
0	their doctrine and their story written left 
0	they die but in their room as they forewarn 
0	wolves shall succeed for teachers grievous wolves 
0	who all the sacred mysteries of heaven
0	to their own vile advantages shall turn
0	of lucre and ambition and the truth
0	with superstitions and traditions taint 
0	left only in those written records pure 
0	though not but by the spirit understood 
0	then shall they seek to avail themselves of names 
0	places and titles and with these to join
0	secular power though feigning still to act
0	by spiritual to themselves appropriating
0	the spirit of god promised alike and given
0	to all believers and from that pretence 
0	spiritual laws by carnal power shall force
0	on every conscience laws which none shall find
0	left them inrolled or what the spirit within
0	shall on the heart engrave what will they then
0	but force the spirit of grace itself and bind
0	his consort liberty what but unbuild
0	his living temples built by faith to stand 
0	their own faith not another s for on earth 
0	who against faith and conscience can be heard
0	infallible yet many will presume 
0	whence heavy persecution shall arise
0	on all who in the worship persevere
0	of spirit and truth the rest far greater part 
0	will deem in outward rites and specious forms
0	religion satisfied truth shall retire
0	bestuck with slanderous darts and works of faith
0	rarely be found so shall the world go on 
0	to good malignant to bad men benign 
0	under her own weight groaning till the day
0	appear of respiration to the just 
0	and vengeance to the wicked at return
0	of him so lately promised to thy aid 
0	the woman s seed obscurely then foretold 
0	now ampler known thy saviour and thy lord 
0	last in the clouds from heaven to be revealed
0	in glory of the father to dissolve
0	satan with his perverted world then raise
0	from the conflagrant mass purged and refined 
0	new heavens new earth ages of endless date 
0	founded in righteousness and peace and love 
0	to bring forth fruits joy and eternal bliss 
0	he ended and thus adam last replied 
0	how soon hath thy prediction seer blest 
0	measured this transient world the race of time 
0	till time stand fixed beyond is all abyss 
0	eternity whose end no eye can reach 
0	greatly instructed i shall hence depart 
0	greatly in peace of thought and have my fill
0	of knowledge what this vessel can contain 
0	beyond which was my folly to aspire 
0	henceforth i learn that to obey is best 
0	and love with fear the only god to walk
0	as in his presence ever to observe
0	his providence and on him sole depend 
0	merciful over all his works with good
0	still overcoming evil and by small
0	accomplishing great things by things deemed weak
0	subverting worldly strong and worldly wise
0	by simply meek that suffering for truth s sake
0	is fortitude to highest victory 
0	and to the faithful death the gate of life 
0	taught this by his example whom i now
0	acknowledge my redeemer ever blest 
0	to whom thus also the angel last replied 
0	this having learned thou hast attained the sum
0	of wisdom hope no higher though all the stars
0	thou knewest by name and all the ethereal powers 
0	all secrets of the deep all nature s works 
0	or works of god in heaven air earth or sea 
0	and all the riches of this world enjoyedst 
0	and all the rule one empire only add
0	deeds to thy knowledge answerable add faith 
0	add virtue patience temperance add love 
0	by name to come called charity the soul
0	of all the rest then wilt thou not be loth
0	to leave this paradise but shalt possess
0	a paradise within thee happier far 
0	let us descend now therefore from this top
0	of speculation for the hour precise
0	exacts our parting hence and see the guards 
0	by me encamped on yonder hill expect
0	their motion at whose front a flaming sword 
0	in signal of remove waves fiercely round 
0	we may no longer stay go waken eve 
0	her also i with gentle dreams have calmed
0	portending good and all her spirits composed
0	to meek submission thou at season fit 
0	let her with thee partake what thou hast heard 
0	chiefly what may concern her faith to know 
0	the great deliverance by her seed to come
0	 for by the woman s seed on all mankind 
0	that ye may live which will be many days 
0	both in one faith unanimous though sad 
0	with cause for evils past yet much more cheered
0	with meditation on the happy end 
0	he ended and they both descend the hill 
0	descended adam to the bower where eve
0	lay sleeping ran before but found her waked 
0	and thus with words not sad she him received 
0	whence thou returnest and whither wentest i know 
0	for god is also in sleep and dreams advise 
0	which he hath sent propitious some great good
0	presaging since with sorrow and heart s distress
0	wearied i fell asleep but now lead on 
0	in me is no delay with thee to go 
0	is to stay here without thee here to stay 
0	is to go hence unwilling thou to me
0	art all things under heaven all places thou 
0	who for my wilful crime art banished hence 
0	this further consolation yet secure
0	i carry hence though all by me is lost 
0	such favour i unworthy am vouchsafed 
0	by me the promised seed shall all restore 
0	so spake our mother eve and adam heard
0	well pleased but answered not for now too nigh
0	the arch angel stood and from the other hill
0	to their fixed station all in bright array
0	the cherubim descended on the ground
0	gliding meteorous as evening mist
0	risen from a river o er the marish glides 
0	and gathers ground fast at the labourer s heel
0	homeward returning high in front advanced 
0	the brandished sword of god before them blazed 
0	fierce as a comet which with torrid heat 
0	and vapour as the libyan air adust 
0	began to parch that temperate clime whereat
0	in either hand the hastening angel caught
0	our lingering parents and to the eastern gate
0	led them direct and down the cliff as fast
0	to the subjected plain then disappeared 
0	they looking back all the eastern side beheld
0	of paradise so late their happy seat 
0	waved over by that flaming brand the gate
0	with dreadful faces thronged and fiery arms 
0	some natural tears they dropt but wiped them soon 
0	the world was all before them where to choose
0	their place of rest and providence their guide 
0	they hand in hand with wandering steps and slow 
0	through eden took their solitary way 
0	 of cerberus and blackest midnight born
0	in stygian cave forlorn
0	unholy 
0	find out some uncouth cell 
0	 where brooding darkness spreads his jealous wings 
0	and the night raven sings 
0	as ragged as thy locks 
0	but come thou goddess fair and free 
0	in heaven yclept euphrosyne 
0	and by men heart easing mirth 
0	whom lovely venus at a birth 
0	with two sister graces more 
0	to ivy crowned bacchus bore 
0	hence loathed melancholy 
0	or whether as some sager sing 
0	the frolic wind that breathes the spring 
0	zephyr with aurora playing 
0	as he met her once a maying 
0	there on beds of violets blue 
0	and fresh blown roses washed in dew 
0	filled her with thee a daughter fair 
0	so buxom blithe and debonair 
0	haste thee nymph and bring with thee
0	jest and youthful jollity 
0	quips and cranks and wanton wiles 
0	nods and becks and wreathed smiles
0	such as hang on hebe s cheek 
0	and love to live in dimple sleek 
0	sport that wrinkled care derides 
0	and laughter holding both his sides 
0	come and trip it as you go 
0	on the light fantastic toe 
0	and in thy right hand lead with thee
0	the mountain nymph sweet liberty 
0	and if i give thee honour due 
0	mirth admit me of thy crew 
0	to live with her and live with thee 
0	in unreproved pleasures free 
0	to hear the lark begin his flight 
0	and singing startle the dull night 
0	from his watch tower in the skies 
0	till the dappled dawn doth rise 
0	then to come in spite of sorrow 
0	and at my window bid good morrow 
0	through the sweet briar or the vine 
0	or the twisted eglantine 
0	while the cock with lively din 
0	scatters the rear of darkness thin 
0	and to the stack or the barn door 
0	stoutly struts his dames before 
0	oft listening how the hounds and horn
0	cheerly rouse the slumbering morn 
0	from the side of some hoar hill 
0	through the high wood echoing shrill 
0	sometime walking not unseen 
0	by hedgerow elms on hillocks green 
0	right against the eastern gate
0	where the great sun begins his state 
0	robed in flames and amber light 
0	the clouds in thousand liveries dight 
0	while the ploughman near at hand 
0	whistles o er the furrowed land 
0	and the milkmaid singeth blithe 
0	and the mower whets his scythe 
0	and every shepherd tells his tale
0	under the hawthorn in the dale 
0	straight mine eye hath caught new pleasures 
0	whilst the landskip round it measures 
0	russet lawns and fallows grey 
0	where the nibbling flocks do stray 
0	mountains on whose barren breast
0	the labouring clouds do often rest 
0	meadows trim with daisies pied 
0	shallow brooks and rivers wide 
0	towers and battlements it sees
0	bosomed high in tufted trees 
0	where perhaps some beauty lies 
0	the cynosure of neighbouring eyes 
0	hard by a cottage chimney smokes
0	from betwixt two aged oaks 
0	are at their savoury dinner set
0	of herbs and other country messes 
0	which the neat handed phyllis dresses 
0	and then in haste her bower she leaves 
0	with thestylis to bind the sheaves 
0	or if the earlier season lead 
0	to the tanned haycock in the mead 
0	sometimes with secure delight 
0	the upland hamlets will invite 
0	when the merry bells ring round 
0	and the jocund rebecks sound
0	to many a youth and many a maid
0	dancing in the chequered shade 
0	and young and old come forth to play
0	on a sunshine holiday 
0	till the livelong daylight fail 
0	then to the spicy nut brown ale 
0	with stories told of many a feat 
0	how faery mab the junkets eat 
0	she was pinched and pulled she said 
0	and he by friar s lantern led 
0	tells how the drudging goblin sweat
0	to earn his cream bowl duly set 
0	when in one night ere glimpse of morn 
0	his shadowy flail hath threshed the corn
0	that ten day labourers could not end 
0	then lies him down the lubber fiend 
0	and stretched out all the chimney s length 
0	basks at the fire his hairy strength 
0	and crop full out of doors he flings 
0	ere the first cock his matin rings 
0	thus done the tales to bed they creep 
0	by whispering winds soon lulled asleep 
0	towered cities please us then 
0	and the busy hum of men 
0	where throngs of knights and barons bold 
0	in weeds of peace high triumphs hold
0	with store of ladies whose bright eyes
0	rain influence and judge the prize
0	of wit or arms while both contend
0	to win her grace whom all commend 
0	there let hymen oft appear
0	in saffron robe with taper clear 
0	and pomp and feast and revelry 
