0	wandring that watrie desert i had hope
0	when violence was ceas t and warr on earth 
0	all would have then gon well peace would have crownd
0	with length of happy days the race of man 
0	but i was farr deceav d for now i see
0	peace to corrupt no less then warr to waste 
0	how comes it thus unfould celestial guide 
0	and whether here the race of man will end 
0	to whom thus michael those whom last thou sawst
0	in triumph and luxurious wealth are they
0	first seen in acts of prowess eminent
0	and great exploits but of true vertu void 
