0	not by destroying satan but his works
0	in thee and in thy seed nor can this be 
0	but by fulfilling that which thou didst want 
0	obedience to the law of god impos d
0	on penaltie of death and suffering death 
0	the penaltie to thy transgression due 
0	and due to theirs which out of thine will grow 
0	so onely can high justice rest appaid 
0	the law of god exact he shall fulfill
0	both by obedience and by love though love
0	alone fulfill the law thy punishment
0	he shall endure by coming in the flesh
0	to a reproachful life and cursed death 
0	proclaiming life to all who shall believe
0	in his redemption and that his obedience
0	imputed becomes theirs by faith his merits
0	to save them not thir own though legal works 
0	for this he shall live hated be blasphem d 
0	seis d on by force judg d and to death condemnd
0	a shameful and accurst naild to the cross
0	by his own nation slaine for bringing life 
0	but to the cross he nailes thy enemies 
0	the law that is against thee and the sins
0	of all mankinde with him there crucifi d 
0	never to hurt them more who rightly trust
0	in this his satisfaction so he dies 
0	but soon revives death over him no power
0	shall long usurp ere the third dawning light
0	returne the starres of morn shall see him rise
0	out of his grave fresh as the dawning light 
0	thy ransom paid which man from death redeems 
